  { question: "Under 'File Management' (2.5.2.3), what does 'Copying' a file to a new folder while 'holding the Shift key' do?", options: ["Copies the file", "Moves the file", "Deletes the file", "Renames the file"], answer: "Moves the file", category: "SDP", reason: "In the GUI, holding Shift during a drag-and-drop forces a 'Move' operation regardless of the drive." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item (2.5.2.7.4) handles 'Firewall' and 'Security' status?", options: ["User Accounts", "Programs", "System and Security", "Ease of Access"], answer: "System and Security", category: "SDP", reason: "Administrative, maintenance, and security controls are grouped in this category." },
  { question: "What is 'Inter-Process Communication' (2.3)?", options: ["Two different computers talking", "The mechanism for processes to communicate and synchronize their actions within the OS", "Printing from one app to another", "Saving a file"], answer: "The mechanism for processes to communicate and synchronize their actions within the OS", category: "SDP", reason: "IPC is an essential part of processor management to ensure multi-tasking works correctly." },
  { question: "In the command-line (2.4), the command 'DIR /S' is used to:", options: ["Sort files by size", "List all files in the current directory and all sub-directories", "Show system files only", "Stop the listing"], answer: "List all files in the current directory and all sub-directories", category: "SDP", reason: "The /S switch performs a recursive search throughout the folder tree." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Windows Application' (2.5.2.4) is best for editing a '.bmp' or '.jpg' file at the pixel level?", options: ["Character Map", "Control Panel", "Paint", "Windows Explorer"], answer: "Paint", category: "SDP", reason: "MS Paint is a raster (pixel-based) graphics application." },
  { question: "What is the keyboard shortcut for 'Redo' in most Windows applications (2.5.2.4)?", options: ["Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + R", "Ctrl + Y", "Alt + Backspace"], answer: "Ctrl + Y", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Y is the standard command to reverse an Undo." },
  { question: "To start 'Device Manager' from the Run box (2.5.2.6/2.5.2.7.4), what do you type?", options: ["manager", "devices", "devmgmt.msc", "control hardware"], answer: "devmgmt.msc", category: "SDP", reason: "Many Control Panel items can be launched directly using their .msc (Management Console) file names." },
  { question: "Which 'System Tool' (2.5.2.9) is used to 'Prepare' a formatted drive for first-time use?", options: ["Scanning", "Defragmenter", "Format", "Restore"], answer: "Format", category: "SDP", reason: "Formatting must be done before the OS can recognize a partition and store data." },
  { question: "In Windows Explorer (2.5.2.3), 'Dragging' a file while 'holding the Right mouse button' will:", options: ["Automatically delete it", "Display a menu with options to Copy, Move, or Create Shortcut upon release", "Only copy it", "Only move it"], answer: "Display a menu with options to Copy, Move, or Create Shortcut upon release", category: "SDP", reason: "The right-drag interaction gives the user explicit choice over the management action." },
  { question: "What is 'Kernel' (2.1)?", options: ["The user interface", "The central core of the OS that manages all hardware/software interactions", "A type of virus", "The computer case"], answer: "The central core of the OS that manages all hardware/software interactions", category: "SDP", reason: "The kernel is the essential, most internal part of the operating system software." },
  { question: "Which Operating System type (2.2) is designed to process data from a physical source without any delay (e.g., autopilot)?", options: ["Batch OS", "Time-sharing OS", "Real-time OS", "Single-user OS"], answer: "Real-time OS", category: "SDP", reason: "RTOS must provide guaranteed response times for critical automated operations." },
  { question: "To 'Search' for a Word file with the name 'Report' in Windows Explorer (2.5.2.5), you type:", options: ["Report.docx", "*Report*", "Report*", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "Search is flexible; typing the exact name, part of it, or using wildcards will return the matching file." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Windows Element' (2.5.2.1) provides a quick view of the system time and date?", options: ["Start Button", "Recycle Bin", "Notification Area (Taskbar)", "Title Bar"], answer: "Notification Area (Taskbar)", category: "SDP", reason: "The clock is always located in the notification area at the end of the taskbar." },
  { question: "What does a 'User Profile' (2.5.2.7.4) store?", options: ["The computer's RAM", "Individual user settings, documents, and desktop configurations", "The Windows kernel", "Deleted files for everyone"], answer: "Individual user settings, documents, and desktop configurations", category: "SDP", reason: "Profiles allow multiple people to share a PC while keeping their data and preferences private." },
  { question: "What happens if a user 'Accidentally' deletes a file from a Network Drive in Windows Explorer?", options: ["It goes to the user's local Recycle Bin", "It is permanently deleted immediately (Network drives do not use the local Recycle Bin)", "It moves to the server's desktop", "The computer crashes"], answer: "It is permanently deleted immediately (Network drives do not use the local Recycle Bin)", category: "SDP", reason: "Standard Windows behavior only protects local drive deletions; network data loss requires a backup restore." },
  { question: "Which function of the OS (2.3) provides an 'Application Programming Interface' (API) for software?", options: ["Memory Management", "Hardware Interaction / Coordination", "Job Accounting", "Defragmentation"], answer: "Hardware Interaction / Coordination", category: "SDP", reason: "The OS coordinates between different programs and the hardware, providing a standard set of rules (API) for developers." },
  { question: "Which of the following is an example of a 'Text Editor' rather than a full 'Word Processor' (3.2)?", options: ["MS Word", "WordPerfect", "Notepad", "WordPad"], answer: "Notepad", category: "SDP", reason: "Notepad is a basic text editor that handles raw text without complex formatting, whereas word processors handle layout and design." },
  { question: "Which view is used to manage a 'Master Document' and its subdocuments (3.3.18)?", options: ["Print Layout", "Draft View", "Outline View", "Read Mode"], answer: "Outline View", category: "SDP", reason: "The Master Document functionality is accessible only through the Outlining tab in Outline View." },
  { question: "To create a 'Cross-reference' (3.3.18) to a specific heading in your document, you go to which tab?", options: ["Insert", "Layout", "References", "Review"], answer: "References", category: "SDP", reason: "Cross-references, along with Table of Contents and Indexing, are located under the References tab." },
  { question: "Which feature in MS Word allows you to insert the entire content of 'another' Word file into your current document (3.3.11)?", options: ["Insert Hyperlink", "Insert Object -> Text from File", "Copy and Paste Special", "Insert Bookmark"], answer: "Insert Object -> Text from File", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Text from File' option allows for seamless merging of document contents without manually copying." },
  { question: "In Devanagari typing (3.3.5), what is the primary benefit of using 'Unicode' over legacy fonts like 'Preeti'?", options: ["Unicode is easier to learn", "Unicode is a universal standard that is independent of specific font files for display", "Preeti uses more RAM", "Unicode allows for more colors"], answer: "Unicode is a universal standard that is independent of specific font files for display", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode data is logically encoded, meaning it can be read on any device even if the original font isn't installed." },
  { question: "Which tool would you use to mark specific words throughout a document to generate an 'Index' (3.3.18) at the end?", options: ["Bookmark", "Mark Entry", "Caption", "Thesaurus"], answer: "Mark Entry", category: "SDP", reason: "To create an Index, you must first 'Mark Entry' for the keywords using Alt+Shift+X." },
  { question: "Under 'Customizing menu & toolbars' (3.3.16), where can you add a command that is not currently on the Ribbon?", options: ["Status Bar", "Quick Access Toolbar (QAT)", "Navigation Pane", "Ruler"], answer: "Quick Access Toolbar (QAT)", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT is designed for users to pin frequently used commands for one-click access regardless of the active tab." },
  { question: "Which type of 'Section Break' (3.3.11) allows you to change the orientation of the 'very next' page to Landscape while keeping the current page Portrait?", options: ["Continuous", "Next Page", "Even Page", "Odd Page"], answer: "Next Page", category: "SDP", reason: "Next Page section breaks allow for independent page setup (margins, orientation) for the following page." },
  { question: "To change the 'Default Font' for every new document you create (3.3.13), you must set it in the Font dialog and click:", options: ["OK", "Apply", "Set as Default", "Save as Template"], answer: "Set as Default", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Set as Default' button updates the 'Normal.dotm' global template with your new preferences." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Security Technique' (3.3.17) that prevents others from making any changes but allows them to read the document?", options: ["Restrict Editing -> Read Only", "Password to Open", "Mark as Final", "Both A and C"], answer: "Both A and C", category: "SDP", reason: "Both Read Only restrictions and 'Mark as Final' serve to protect document integrity from accidental edits." },
  { question: "Which 'Devanagari Font' (3.3.5) layout is most commonly used for government official work in Nepal when Unicode is not required?", options: ["Mangal", "Preeti", "Times New Roman", "Calibri"], answer: "Preeti", category: "SDP", reason: "Preeti is the most widely recognized legacy non-Unicode font in the Nepalese context." },
  { question: "What is the result of using a 'Master Document' (3.3.18)?", options: ["It deletes all sub-documents", "It links multiple separate Word files into one large parent document", "It turns the document into a PDF", "It formats all text as Bold"], answer: "It links multiple separate Word files into one large parent document", category: "SDP", reason: "Master documents are used to manage extremely large projects (like books) by splitting them into manageable sub-files." },
  { question: "Which key combination in the 'Preeti' font layout (3.3.5) is used to type the vowel sign 'ा' (Akar)?", options: ["a", "f", "d", "s"], answer: "f", category: "SDP", reason: "In the Preeti layout mapping, the 'f' key produces the Akar (ा) symbol." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing the Ribbon' (3.3.16), what is a 'Custom Group'?", options: ["A group of users", "A user-created set of commands within a standard or custom tab", "A type of table", "A security setting"], answer: "A user-created set of commands within a standard or custom tab", category: "SDP", reason: "Word allows users to personalize the ribbon by grouping their most-used tools together." },
  { question: "To add a 'Digital Signature' (3.3.17) to a Word document to ensure its authenticity, you go to the ______ tab.", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Review", "File -> Info"], answer: "File -> Info", category: "SDP", reason: "Advanced security features like encryption and digital signatures are centralized in the Backstage View (File Tab)." },
  { question: "Which indentation type (3.3.9) is commonly used to create the 'Bibliography' section of a research paper?", options: ["First Line Indent", "Hanging Indent", "Left Indent", "Mirror Indent"], answer: "Hanging Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "A hanging indent keeps the first line at the margin while indenting subsequent lines, making author names easier to scan." },
  { question: "What happens if you use a 'Continuous' section break (3.3.11) on a page?", options: ["A new page starts immediately", "The current page ends", "A new section starts on the same page, allowing for different column layouts", "The document is saved"], answer: "A new section starts on the same page, allowing for different column layouts", category: "SDP", reason: "Continuous breaks allow for changing formatting (like switching from 1 column to 2) without jumping to a new sheet." },
  { question: "Which function key is used to update an 'Index' or 'Table of Content' after editing headings (3.3.18)?", options: ["F5", "F7", "F9", "F12"], answer: "F9", category: "SDP", reason: "F9 is the standard Microsoft Office key to update fields and automated tables." },
  { question: "In 'Devanagari Unicode' (3.3.5), how do you produce the half-character 'क्'?", options: ["Type 'k' then 'f'", "Type the character then the Halanta (्)", "Press Shift + k", "Double click the character"], answer: "Type the character then the Halanta (्)", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode uses logical combining marks; the Halanta 'kills' the inherent vowel, creating a half-letter." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Graphic' type (3.3.11) is best suited for representing a 'Process Flow' or a 'Cycle'?", options: ["Picture", "SmartArt", "WordArt", "Chart"], answer: "SmartArt", category: "SDP", reason: "SmartArt includes pre-designed logical diagrams like cycles, pyramids, and flowcharts." },
  { question: "The 'Master Document' (3.3.18) allows for 'Subdocuments'. What is the risk of renaming a subdocument file on the hard drive?", options: ["The file size increases", "The link from the Master Document to that subdocument will be broken", "The font changes to Arial", "The computer restarts"], answer: "The link from the Master Document to that subdocument will be broken", category: "SDP", reason: "Master documents rely on file path links; changing the name or location outside Word breaks the reference." },
  { question: "Under 'Security' (3.3.17), what does the 'Restrict Editing' pane allow you to do specifically?", options: ["Limit formatting to a selection of styles", "Allow only comments or track changes", "Allow only filling in forms", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "Restrict Editing provides granular control over how others can interact with the document content." },
  { question: "Which tool (3.3.15) provides a list of words with similar meanings (Synonyms)?", options: ["Spell Check", "Grammar Check", "Thesaurus", "AutoCorrect"], answer: "Thesaurus", category: "SDP", reason: "The Thesaurus (Shift+F7) is the built-in reference for finding alternative word choices." },
  { question: "In the context of 'Types of Word Processing' (3.2), what is a 'GUI-based' word processor?", options: ["One that requires code to type", "One that uses windows, icons, and menus (like MS Word)", "One that only works on printers", "One that doesn't use a mouse"], answer: "One that uses windows, icons, and menus (like MS Word)", category: "SDP", reason: "GUI stands for Graphical User Interface; most modern word processors fall into this category." },
  { question: "Which setting (3.3.13) determines the 'Units of Measurement' (Inches vs Centimeters) on the Word ruler?", options: ["Home tab settings", "File -> Options -> Advanced -> Display", "Page Layout tab", "View tab"], answer: "File -> Options -> Advanced -> Display", category: "SDP", reason: "System-wide unit measurements are part of the advanced Word configuration options." },
  { question: "Which key combination is used to type 'ऋ' in 'Preeti' font (3.3.5)?", options: ["Alt + 0161", "Shift + r", "Alt + r", "r"], answer: "Alt + 0161", category: "SDP", reason: "Legacy non-Unicode fonts require specific Alt-codes for specialized characters." },
  { question: "What is the purpose of 'Organization Chart' (3.3.11)?", options: ["To calculate salary", "To show the reporting structure of a company", "To design a logo", "To sort text A-Z"], answer: "To show the reporting structure of a company", category: "SDP", reason: "Organization charts (found in SmartArt) visually represent hierarchical relationships." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key centers the current paragraph (3.3.3)?", options: ["Ctrl + C", "Ctrl + E", "Ctrl + L", "Ctrl + J"], answer: "Ctrl + E", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + E is the standard shortcut for Center Alignment." },
  { question: "In 'Master Documents' (3.3.18), what does the 'Expand Subdocuments' button do?", options: ["Increases the font size", "Displays the full content of the linked sub-files instead of just the file path", "Prints the document", "Deletes all links"], answer: "Displays the full content of the linked sub-files instead of just the file path", category: "SDP", reason: "Expanding allows the user to read and edit all sub-files within the parent master document interface." },
  { question: "To add a 'Border' only to the top and bottom of a page (3.3.8), you visit the ______ tab.", options: ["Home", "Design", "Layout", "Insert"], answer: "Design", category: "SDP", reason: "Page Borders are located in the Page Background group on the Design tab." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' option (3.3.17) forces Word to ask for a password before even displaying the file's content?", options: ["Encrypt with Password", "Restrict Editing", "Protect Current Sheet", "Mark as Final"], answer: "Encrypt with Password", category: "SDP", reason: "Encryption (Password to Open) ensures that the document data is unreadable without the correct key." },
  { question: "Which feature (3.3.15) identifies words that are spelled correctly but used in the wrong context (e.g., 'their' instead of 'there')?", options: ["Spelling Check", "Grammar Check", "AutoCorrect", "Thesaurus"], answer: "Grammar Check", category: "SDP", reason: "Grammar check includes logic to detect homophone errors based on surrounding context." },
  { question: "To 'Customize toolbars' (3.3.16) by adding a specific command that is used very frequently, you should use the:", options: ["Status Bar", "Quick Access Toolbar", "Scroll Bar", "Formula Bar"], answer: "Quick Access Toolbar", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT can be customized to include any command, providing a fixed location for it." },
  { question: "Which HTML-like concept (syllabus 7 intersection applied to Word 3.12) is the basis for Devanagari Unicode fonts?", options: ["ASCII", "ANSI", "Unicode", "EBCDIC"], answer: "Unicode", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode is the modern standard used for Devanagari to ensure cross-platform compatibility." },
  { question: "In 'Master Document' (3.3.18), what is a 'Subdocument'?", options: ["A hidden file", "A separate Word file that is linked into the Master document", "A type of footnote", "A deleted document"], answer: "A separate Word file that is linked into the Master document", category: "SDP", reason: "Master documents acts as containers for these individual files." },
  { question: "Which indent (3.3.9) moves the entire paragraph except for the first line away from the margin?", options: ["Left Indent", "Right Indent", "Hanging Indent", "Mirror Indent"], answer: "Hanging Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "Hanging indents are the reverse of first-line indents." },
  { question: "To 'Insert a Chart' (3.3.11) representing data trends, Word usually launches which other program?", options: ["MS Access", "MS Excel", "MS Paint", "Calculator"], answer: "MS Excel", category: "SDP", reason: "Word uses the Excel engine to manage the numerical data needed for charts." },
  { question: "What is 'WordArt' (3.3.11)?", options: ["A tool for drawing lines", "Decorative text that is treated as a graphic object", "A type of table", "A spell checker"], answer: "Decorative text that is treated as a graphic object", category: "SDP", reason: "WordArt allows users to apply graphical effects like shadows and 3D rotations to text." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' tool (3.3.17) should be used to protect a template from being permanently changed by others?", options: ["Saving it as a .docx", "Setting the file attribute to 'Read Only' in Windows", "Changing the font size", "Applying a watermark"], answer: "Setting the file attribute to 'Read Only' in Windows", category: "SDP", reason: "Read-only attributes at the OS level are a standard way to prevent modification of important template files." },
  { question: "Which tab contains 'Cross-reference' (3.3.18)?", options: ["Insert", "Layout", "References", "Review"], answer: "References", category: "SDP", reason: "Reference tools like cross-references link one part of the document to another automatically." },
  { question: "To start a new section that begins on the next 'Even' page (3.3.11), which break is used?", options: ["Continuous", "Even Page", "Odd Page", "Next Page"], answer: "Even Page", category: "SDP", reason: "This is often used for book layouts so chapters start on specific sides." },
  { question: "In 'Devanagari Fonts' (3.3.5), typing 'u' in Preeti font results in which character?", options: ["क", "ख", "ग", "घ"], answer: "क", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'u' key is mapped to 'Ka' in the Preeti layout." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of an 'Index' (3.3.18)?", options: ["To check for errors", "To list the main topics and their page numbers at the end of the document", "To summarize the document", "To add images"], answer: "To list the main topics and their page numbers at the end of the document", category: "SDP", reason: "Indices allow readers to find specific keywords quickly." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key inserts a 'Page Break' (3.3.11)?", options: ["Ctrl + Enter", "Alt + Enter", "Shift + Enter", "Ctrl + Shift + Enter"], answer: "Ctrl + Enter", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Enter is the quick manual page break command." },
  { question: "Under 'Master Document' (3.3.18), how do you convert a Master document back into a regular Word file?", options: ["Delete it", "Use the 'Unlink' command on all subdocuments", "Change the file extension", "Format the drive"], answer: "Use the 'Unlink' command on all subdocuments", category: "SDP", reason: "Unlinking incorporates the actual content of the sub-files into the parent file permanently." },
  { question: "Which indentation (3.3.9) moves the entire paragraph away from the left margin?", options: ["Hanging Indent", "First Line Indent", "Left Indent", "Right Indent"], answer: "Left Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "The Left Indent moves every line of the paragraph relative to the margin." },
  { question: "What is the default unit for 'Tab Stops' (3.3.9) in MS Word?", options: ["0.25 inch", "0.5 inch", "1.0 inch", "0.75 inch"], answer: "0.5 inch", category: "SDP", reason: "By default, pressing 'Tab' moves the cursor 0.5 inches." },
  { question: "Which 'Graphic' (3.3.11) involves using built-in vector shapes like arrows and circles?", options: ["Pictures", "Shapes", "SmartArt", "WordArt"], answer: "Shapes", category: "SDP", reason: "The Shapes tool allows users to draw basic geometric and flowchart elements." },
  { question: "To insert the 'System File Path' into a Footer (3.3.11), you use:", options: ["Format Painter", "Quick Parts -> Field", "AutoCorrect", "Symbol"], answer: "Quick Parts -> Field", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'FileName' field with the '\\p' switch displays the full file path." },
  { question: "In 'Security' (3.3.17), what is 'Mark as Final'?", options: ["Deletes the file", "A setting that tells users this is the completed version and disables editing tools by default", "Adds a password", "Encrypts the drive"], answer: "A setting that tells users this is the completed version and disables editing tools by default", category: "SDP", reason: "It acts as a soft protection to prevent accidental edits to a final draft." },
  { question: "Which of the following versions of MS Word first introduced the 'Quick Access Toolbar' (QAT)?", options: ["Word 2003", "Word 2007", "Word 2010", "Word 2013"], answer: "Word 2007", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT was introduced alongside the Ribbon in 2007 to allow users to keep their most used commands always visible." },
  { question: "In MS Word 2003, which menu was used to change the 'Background Color' or 'Page Borders' of a document?", options: ["File", "Edit", "Format", "Tools"], answer: "Format", category: "SDP", reason: "Before the 'Design' or 'Page Layout' tabs, these visual settings were part of the 'Borders and Shading' option under the Format menu." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Section Break' starts the new section on the very next 'Even' page number?", options: ["Continuous", "Next Page", "Even Page", "Odd Page"], answer: "Even Page", category: "SDP", reason: "Even Page section breaks ensure chapters or sections start specifically on even-numbered pages, common in manual publishing." },
  { question: "To create a 'Cross-reference' (3.3.18) to a figure or table, you must first do what to that object?", options: ["Bold it", "Insert a Caption", "Bookmark it", "Underline it"], answer: "Insert a Caption", category: "SDP", reason: "Word uses captions as the anchor points for automatic cross-referencing." },
  { question: "In the 'Preeti' font layout (3.3.5), which character is produced by pressing the 'v' key?", options: ["न", "म", "न", "ख"], answer: "न", category: "SDP", reason: "In the legacy Preeti mapping, the 'v' key represents the letter 'Na' (न)." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Master Document' (3.3.18)?", options: ["To protect a file with a password", "To organize and link multiple sub-documents into one large file", "To check spelling in multiple languages", "To create a backup copy"], answer: "To organize and link multiple sub-documents into one large file", category: "SDP", reason: "Master documents are used to manage complex books or reports by linking individual chapter files." },
  { question: "Which view in MS Word 2013 provides a 'Thumbnails' pane to navigate quickly through page images?", options: ["Read Mode", "Navigation Pane (Pages tab)", "Outline View", "Draft View"], answer: "Navigation Pane (Pages tab)", category: "SDP", reason: "The Navigation Pane (Ctrl+F) has a 'Pages' tab that shows miniature versions of all pages." },
  { question: "To add a line between columns in a 'Newspaper style' layout (3.3.10), you must enable it in which dialog?", options: ["Page Setup", "Borders and Shading", "Columns (More Columns)", "Paragraph"], answer: "Columns (More Columns)", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Line between' checkbox is found within the advanced column settings." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key combination clears all 'Paragraph' formatting (like indents and alignment)?", options: ["Ctrl + Spacebar", "Ctrl + Q", "Ctrl + Shift + N", "Alt + Delete"], answer: "Ctrl + Q", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl+Q resets the paragraph to its base style's original settings, clearing manual indents and spacing." },
  { question: "Where is the 'Vertical Ruler' located in the MS Word Print Layout environment (3.3.2)?", options: ["Right side", "Left side", "Top", "Bottom"], answer: "Left side", category: "SDP", reason: "The horizontal ruler is at the top, and the vertical ruler appears along the left edge." },
  { question: "In MS Word 2007/2010, the 'Watermark' tool is found in which tab?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Page Layout", "Review"], answer: "Page Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "In versions 2007 and 2010, page background tools were in Page Layout; they moved to 'Design' in 2013." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Rows' an MS Word table can theoretically contain (3.3.7)?", options: ["16,384", "32,767", "65,536", "Unlimited"], answer: "32,767", category: "SDP", reason: "Microsoft Word tables are capped at 32,767 rows." },
  { question: "Which specific indentation type (3.3.9) moves the entire paragraph away from the left margin?", options: ["First Line Indent", "Hanging Indent", "Left Indent", "Right Indent"], answer: "Left Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "The Left Indent moves every single line of the paragraph relative to the margin." },
  { question: "Which feature (3.3.15) allows you to find words with similar meanings?", options: ["Dictionary", "Thesaurus", "Spell Check", "Word Count"], answer: "Thesaurus", category: "SDP", reason: "The Thesaurus (Shift+F7) is the built-in tool for synonyms and antonyms." },
  { question: "Under 'Security Techniques' (3.3.17), 'Mark as Final' is used to:", options: ["Encrypt the document", "Add a digital signature", "Communicate that the document is complete and disable editing", "Delete the file"], answer: "Communicate that the document is complete and disable editing", category: "SDP", reason: "It turns off editing tools and shows a 'Marked as Final' banner to other users." },
  { question: "In Devanagari Unicode (3.3.5), which key is the 'Halanta' (्) used to create half-characters?", options: ["d", "f", "/", "s"], answer: "d", "answer_note": "Depends on the layout (Romanized vs Traditional), but in standard Devanagari Inscript/Traditional layouts, 'd' is the Halanta.", category: "SDP", reason: "The Halanta 'kills' the implicit 'a' vowel, resulting in a half-consonant." },
  { question: "Which 'View' (3.3.2) is most appropriate for seeing the document structure without page boundaries or graphics?", options: ["Read Mode", "Web Layout", "Draft View", "Print Layout"], answer: "Draft View", category: "SDP", reason: "Draft View focuses on the text and eliminates visual elements like headers and footers." },
  { question: "The keyboard shortcut to 'Double Underline' selected text is:", options: ["Ctrl + U", "Ctrl + Shift + U", "Ctrl + Shift + D", "Alt + Shift + D"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + D", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + U is for single; Ctrl + Shift + D applies a double underline style." },
  { question: "Which tool would you use to create a 'List' of every 'Heading' in your document automatically?", options: ["Index", "Cross-reference", "Table of Content", "Bibliography"], answer: "Table of Content", category: "SDP", reason: "The TOC feature scans for Heading styles and builds a mapped list with page numbers." },
  { question: "In MS Word, the 'Normal' margin setting is ______ on all sides.", options: ["0.5 inch", "1.0 inch", "1.25 inches", "0.75 inch"], answer: "1.0 inch", category: "SDP", reason: "Since Office 2007, the default 'Normal' margin has been 1 inch (2.54 cm) on all four sides." },
  { question: "To 'Mirror' an image horizontally so it faces the opposite direction, you use which tool?", options: ["Format Painter", "Rotate -> Flip Horizontal", "Wrap Text", "Crop"], answer: "Rotate -> Flip Horizontal", category: "SDP", reason: "Rotation and Flipping allow for the visual orientation adjustment of graphics." },
  { question: "Which shortcut opens the 'Find' pane in the Navigation window of Word 2010/2013?", options: ["Ctrl + H", "Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + G", "Ctrl + N"], answer: "Ctrl + F", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl+F is the universal command to find content within a file." },
  { question: "The 'Drop Cap' (3.3.11) tool is located on which tab?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Design", "Layout"], answer: "Insert", category: "SDP", reason: "Drop Caps are treated as special text-insertion objects, located on the Insert tab." },
  { question: "In Preeti font, which key represents the ' Akar' (ा) symbol?", options: ["a", "f", "d", "s"], answer: "f", category: "SDP", reason: "In the legacy Preeti layout, 'f' is used to type the vowel sign for 'Aa'." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Columns' a table can have in MS Word?", options: ["35", "63", "127", "255"], answer: "63", category: "SDP", reason: "Word limits the horizontal grid size of a single table to 63 columns." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' option (3.3.17) should you use if you want users to be able to comment on the text but not change the text itself?", options: ["Password to Modify", "Restrict Editing -> Comments", "Mark as Final", "Digital Signature"], answer: "Restrict Editing -> Comments", category: "SDP", reason: "The Restrict Editing pane allows for granular interaction levels like 'Comments only'." },
  { question: "Which tab contains the 'Word Count' tool in all modern versions of Word?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Review", "View"], answer: "Review", category: "SDP", reason: "Statistics and Proofing tools (Spell Check, Word Count) are located in the Review tab." },
  { question: "What is 'Gutter' margin specifically used for?", options: ["Increasing line spacing", "Adding extra margin to the side of a page that is to be bound", "Adding space for headers", "Formatting columns"], answer: "Adding extra margin to the side of a page that is to be bound", category: "SDP", reason: "Gutter margin ensures that text doesn't disappear into the spine of a book once it is bound." },
  { question: "The shortcut key to check 'Spelling and Grammar' (3.3.15) is:", options: ["F5", "F7", "F9", "F12"], answer: "F7", category: "SDP", reason: "F7 is the standard universal shortcut for proofing in Microsoft Office." },
  { question: "To start a 'Numbered List' using the keyboard automatically, you can type ______ and then press Space.", options: ["1.", "*", ">", "-"], answer: "1.", category: "SDP", reason: "Word's AutoFormat feature recognizes '1.' followed by a space as a trigger to start an ordered list." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing menus' (3.3.16), what happens if you 'Reset' the Ribbon?", options: ["The document is deleted", "The Ribbon returns to the default Microsoft factory settings", "The font changes to Calibri", "The computer restarts"], answer: "The Ribbon returns to the default Microsoft factory settings", category: "SDP", reason: "Resetting clears all user-created tabs, groups, and command rearrangements." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Subscript' text (e.g. H2O)?", options: ["Ctrl + Shift + +", "Ctrl + =", "Alt + Shift + S", "Ctrl + D"], answer: "Ctrl + =", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl+Equals is Subscript; Ctrl+Shift+Plus is Superscript." },
  { question: "Which indentation (3.3.9) moves the entire paragraph except the first line away from the margin?", options: ["Left Indent", "Hanging Indent", "First Line Indent", "Right Indent"], answer: "Hanging Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "Hanging indents are standard for opening paragraphs in bibliographies." },
  { question: "The 'Format Painter' tool copies ______ but not ______.", options: ["Formatting, Text", "Text, Formatting", "Paragraphs, Styles", "Images, Color"], answer: "Formatting, Text", category: "SDP", reason: "Format Painter is designed to duplicate visual styles without changing the words themselves." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Graphic' (3.3.11) provides pre-made 'Flowcharts' and 'Cycle' diagrams?", options: ["WordArt", "SmartArt", "Clipart", "Charts"], answer: "SmartArt", category: "SDP", reason: "SmartArt graphics are logic-based diagrams that allow for easy visual representation of information." },
  { question: "In MS Word 2003, 'Normal.dot' was the name of the:", options: ["System file", "Default global template", "Macro module", " Nepali font"], answer: "Default global template", category: "SDP", reason: "Normal.dot stored the default font, margin, and style settings for all new Word 2003 documents." },
  { question: "To add a 'Footnote' to a document, you visit which tab?", options: ["Insert", "Layout", "References", "Review"], answer: "References", category: "SDP", reason: "Footnotes and Endnotes are academic sourcing tools found in the References tab." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut key to increase font size to the next 'standard size' in the dropdown list (e.g. from 11 to 12)?", options: ["Ctrl + ]", "Ctrl + Shift + >", "Ctrl + [", "Ctrl + Shift + <"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + >", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + ] increases by 1pt; Ctrl + Shift + > increases by the next interval defined in the standard font size menu." },
  { question: "Which view in MS Word shows the document as it would appear on the internet?", options: ["Print Layout", "Web Layout", "Read Mode", "Draft View"], answer: "Web Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Web Layout removes page boundaries and wraps text to the window width." },
  { question: "To repeat the same text multiple times across separate documents in a Mail Merge (3.3.14), we use:", options: ["Bookmarks", "Merge Fields", "Thesaurus", "Styles"], answer: "Merge Fields", category: "SDP", reason: "Merge fields are placeholders (like <<Name>>) that pull unique data for each recipient." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key 'Undo' the last action?", options: ["Ctrl + Y", "Ctrl + U", "Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + X"], answer: "Ctrl + Z", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Z reverses the most recent editing or formatting command." },
  { question: "To start a new section on the next 'Odd' page (3.3.11), which Section Break is used?", options: ["Continuous", "Next Page", "Even Page", "Odd Page"], answer: "Odd Page", category: "SDP", reason: "Odd Page breaks ensure chapters always start on the right-hand page of a book." },
  { question: "In Preeti font, which key represents the 'ह' character?", options: ["h", "u", "i", "s"], answer: "i", category: "SDP", reason: "In legacy Preeti, the 'i' key is used to type 'Ha'." },
  { question: "What happens if you press 'Ctrl + Shift + 8' (or Ctrl + *)?", options: ["Changes font size to 8", "Shows/Hides non-printing characters (¶)", "Inserts a table", "Saves the file"], answer: "Shows/Hides non-printing characters (¶)", category: "SDP", reason: "This toggles the visibility of formatting marks like spaces and paragraph ends." },
  { question: "Which tool allows you to 'Search' for formatting, such as finding all 'Red' text?", options: ["Format Painter", "Find and Replace (Advanced)", "Thesaurus", "Styles"], answer: "Find and Replace (Advanced)", category: "SDP", reason: "Advanced find and replace allows users to search for 'Formatting' rather than just literal characters." },
  { question: "The 'Navigation Pane' in Word 2010/2013 allows you to find headings. What is its shortcut?", options: ["Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + G", "Ctrl + E"], answer: "Ctrl + F", category: "SDP", reason: "In modern versions, Ctrl+F opens the Navigation sidebar for searching." },
  { question: "A '.docm' file extension in MS Word refers to a:", options: ["Macro-enabled Document", "Standard Document", "Template", "Rich Text file"], answer: "Macro-enabled Document", category: "SDP", reason: "XML-based Word documents that contain VBA macros must be saved as .docm." },
  { question: "Which indent type moves only the 'First line' of a paragraph to the right?", options: ["Hanging Indent", "Left Indent", "First Line Indent", "Right Indent"], answer: "First Line Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "First Line Indent is the standard formatting for beginning a new paragraph." },
  { question: "To start a new 'Row' in a table using the keyboard while at the last cell, press:", options: ["Enter", "Shift + Enter", "Tab", "Alt + Enter"], answer: "Tab", category: "SDP", reason: "Pressing Tab in the very last cell of a table automatically appends a new empty row." },
  { question: "What is the 'Status Bar' primarily used for (3.3.2)?", options: ["Applying bold/italic", "Viewing page numbers, word count, and zoom level", "Saving the file", "Inserting graphics"], answer: "Viewing page numbers, word count, and zoom level", category: "SDP", reason: "The status bar at the bottom provides live document statistics and view controls." },
  { question: "Which of the following was the first electronic spreadsheet program ever developed (4.2)?", options: ["Lotus 1-2-3", "MS Excel", "VisiCalc", "Multiplan"], answer: "VisiCalc", category: "SDP", reason: "VisiCalc, released in 1979 for the Apple II, is considered the first electronic spreadsheet that revolutionized the industry." },
  { question: "In the context of 'Organization' (4.3), what is the file extension of a 'Workspace' file in older versions of Excel?", options: [".xlsx", ".xlw", ".xlsb", ".xlsm"], answer: ".xlw", category: "SDP", reason: "A Workspace (.xlw) file saves the layout and window positions of multiple open workbooks so they can be reopened together." },
  { question: "Which tab in the 'Excel Options' (4.4.10) allows you to change the default number of worksheets in every new workbook?", options: ["Advanced", "General", "Formulas", "Proofing"], answer: "General", category: "SDP", reason: "Under 'General' settings, you can define 'Include this many sheets' for new workbooks." },
  { question: "Which tool in the 'Formula Auditing' group (4.4.18) displays arrows that point to the cells providing data to the selected formula?", options: ["Trace Precedents", "Trace Dependents", "Evaluate Formula", "Error Checking"], answer: "Trace Precedents", category: "SDP", reason: "Trace Precedents visually maps out which cells are 'feeding' the current formula." },
  { question: "In Devanagari typing for spreadsheets (4.4.4), why is 'Unicode' logically superior to the 'Preeti' font?", options: ["It is smaller in size", "It assigns a unique digital code to each letter, allowing for proper sorting A-Z", "It makes the font color blue by default", "It only works on Apple computers"], answer: "It assigns a unique digital code to each letter, allowing for proper sorting A-Z", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode data is recognized by Excel as the actual character, whereas Preeti is just a visual overlay on English letters." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' setting (4.4.5) must be applied to a cell so that it remains editable even after the worksheet is protected?", options: ["Locked", "Unlocked (Uncheck 'Locked' in Format Cells)", "Hidden", "Encrypted"], answer: "Unlocked (Uncheck 'Locked' in Format Cells)", category: "SDP", reason: "By default, all cells are marked 'Locked'; they must be explicitly 'Unlocked' to remain editable when sheet protection is active." },
  { question: "To add a 'Diagonal Hatch' or 'Grid' pattern to the background of a cell (4.4.5), which tab in 'Format Cells' is used?", options: ["Alignment", "Font", "Fill", "Number"], answer: "Fill", category: "SDP", reason: "The Fill tab contains options for Background Color, Pattern Color, and Pattern Style (shading)." },
  { question: "Under 'Summarizing Data' (4.4.12), what is the prerequisite for using the built-in 'Subtotal' command?", options: ["The data must be in a chart", "The list must be sorted by the column you want to group by", "All cells must be bold", "The file must be saved as a CSV"], answer: "The list must be sorted by the column you want to group by", category: "SDP", reason: "Subtotal inserts a row every time the value in the specified column changes; if not sorted, it creates inaccurate results." },
  { question: "Which specific environment element (4.4.2) allows you to scroll a worksheet while keeping the cursor in the same cell?", options: ["Formula Bar", "Scroll Lock key on keyboard", "Name Box", "Status Bar"], answer: "Scroll Lock key on keyboard", category: "SDP", reason: "When Scroll Lock is on, the arrow keys move the visible window area rather than the active cell selector." },
  { question: "Which feature (4.4.18) allows you to define multiple sets of values for a range and switch between them to see different results?", options: ["Goal Seek", "Scenario Manager", "Data Validation", "Consolidate"], answer: "Scenario Manager", category: "SDP", reason: "Scenario Manager is a 'What-If' tool used to compare various business models or forecasted outcomes." },
  { question: "Where can you add a 'Custom Tab' or 'Custom Group' to the Excel interface (4.4.16)?", options: ["On the Status Bar", "In 'Customize the Ribbon' under Excel Options", "On the Formula Bar", "In the Page Setup dialog"], answer: "In 'Customize the Ribbon' under Excel Options", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel allows users to personalize the Ribbon by creating their own tabs and grouping tools they use most." },
  { question: "What happens when you 'Export' an Excel file into 'HTML' format (4.4.17)?", options: ["It becomes a Word document", "The spreadsheet becomes a webpage that can be viewed in a browser", "The file is deleted", "The file size doubles"], answer: "The spreadsheet becomes a webpage that can be viewed in a browser", category: "SDP", reason: "Exporting to HTML/Web Page converts the table structure into HTML code for web display." },
  { question: "Which tool in the 'Auditing' group (4.4.18) lets you see a step-by-step breakdown of a complex nested formula?", options: ["Evaluate Formula", "Error Checking", "Trace Precedents", "Show Formulas"], answer: "Evaluate Formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Evaluate Formula opens a dialog that calculates each part of the expression one at a time for troubleshooting." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) allows you to force a large worksheet to fit onto exactly one page width when printing?", options: ["Orientation", "Scaling (Fit to 1 page wide)", "Margins", "Print Titles"], answer: "Scaling (Fit to 1 page wide)", category: "SDP", reason: "Scaling reduces the font and grid size so the entire selection fits the paper dimensions." },
  { question: "To see only 'Errors' in your worksheet visually (4.4.18), you can use the ______ button.", options: ["Find", "Error Checking", "Goal Seek", "Pivot Table"], answer: "Error Checking", category: "SDP", reason: "The Error Checking tool (Formulas tab) identifies common formula mistakes like #DIV/0! or #NAME?." },
  { question: "Which command-line like shortcut 'Toggles' between showing the result and showing the actual formula code in the cells (4.4.7)?", options: ["Ctrl + F9", "Ctrl + ` (Grave Accent)", "Alt + F11", "Shift + F3"], answer: "Ctrl + ` (Grave Accent)", category: "SDP", reason: "This shortcut enters 'Show Formulas' mode, making every formula on the sheet visible for review." },
  { question: "When importing data (4.4.17), what is the primary advantage of the '.txt' (Tab delimited) format over others?", options: ["It supports colors", "It is a universal format compatible with virtually all data software", "It is very large", "It stores charts"], answer: "It is a universal format compatible with virtually all data software", category: "SDP", reason: "Plain text files are used for data exchange between different database and spreadsheet platforms." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' level (4.4.5) allows you to set a password to prevent anyone from adding, deleting, or renaming worksheets?", options: ["Protect Sheet", "Protect Workbook (Structure)", "Data Validation", "Cell Locking"], answer: "Protect Workbook (Structure)", category: "SDP", reason: "Protecting the Workbook structure locks the 'tabs' at the bottom rather than the individual cell data." },
  { question: "What is the result of using 'Goal Seek' (4.4.18)?", options: ["It sorts the list", "It identifies a specific input value required to reach a known target result", "It finds duplicate data", "It prints the sheet"], answer: "It identifies a specific input value required to reach a known target result", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a trial-and-error solver that works backwards from an output goal to find the necessary input." },
  { question: "Which part of the 'Excel Environment' (4.4.2) shows 'Ready' or 'Calculating' status at the bottom of the window?", options: ["Formula Bar", "Menu Bar", "Status Bar", "Rulers"], answer: "Status Bar", category: "SDP", reason: "The Status Bar provides feedback on the current operation and background processes." },
  { question: "To 'Import' data from an Access Database into Excel (4.4.17), you use which tab?", options: ["Insert", "Data", "Review", "View"], answer: "Data", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Get Data' group on the Data tab is the hub for connecting to external data sources." },
  { question: "In 'Formula Auditing' (4.4.18), what does 'Trace Dependents' do?", options: ["Finds errors", "Shows arrows pointing to which formulas use the data from the selected cell", "Deletes the formula", "Calculates the average"], answer: "Shows arrows pointing to which formulas use the data from the selected cell", category: "SDP", reason: "It identifies where the data from a specific cell is being 'sent' or used in other calculations." },
  { question: "Which specific menu tool (4.4.16) is customizable and sits at the very top of the window, above the tabs?", options: ["Formula Bar", "Quick Access Toolbar (QAT)", "Status Bar", "Navigation Pane"], answer: "Quick Access Toolbar (QAT)", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT provides a constant location for one-click access to tools like Save, Undo, and Print." },
  { question: "A 'Pivot Table' (4.4.18) is best used to summarize which type of data?", options: ["A single row of text", "Large amounts of raw, unorganized data into meaningful categories and summaries", "A picture", "The system date"], answer: "Large amounts of raw, unorganized data into meaningful categories and summaries", category: "SDP", reason: "Pivot Tables 'rotate' or pivot data to provide different analytical perspectives quickly." },
  { question: "Under 'Page Setting' (4.4.19), the 'Print Area' is used to:", options: ["Print the entire workbook", "Print only a specific selected range of cells", "Print the charts only", "Delete the background"], answer: "Print only a specific selected range of cells", category: "SDP", reason: "Setting a Print Area prevents Excel from printing the entire sheet, focusing only on relevant data." },
  { question: "What is 'Audit' in the context of MS Excel (4.4.18)?", options: ["Calculating taxes", "The process of verifying the accuracy and logical flow of formulas", "Formatting the text", "Checking for spelling"], answer: "The process of verifying the accuracy and logical flow of formulas", category: "SDP", reason: "Formula auditing ensures that complex spreadsheets contain reliable and error-free calculations." },
  { question: "When 'Exporting' to a PDF (4.4.17), why would you choose 'Optimize for Minimum Size'?", options: ["To make the print quality better", "To make the file easier to send via email by lowering image resolution", "To protect the file with a password", "To delete all sheets"], answer: "To make the file easier to send via email by lowering image resolution", category: "SDP", reason: "Minimum size optimization balances the tradeoff between file portability and visual clarity." },
  { question: "Which 'Indentation' (4.3.9) icon on the Home tab moves the content one step further from the cell border?", options: ["Increase Indent", "Decrease Indent", "Wrap Text", "Merge"], answer: "Increase Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "Increase Indent adds horizontal padding within the cell to improve readability." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Ruler' (4.4.2) in Excel's 'Page Layout' view?", options: ["To change font color", "To adjust margins, column widths, and header/footer positions visually", "To count cells", "To save the file"], answer: "To adjust margins, column widths, and header/footer positions visually", category: "SDP", reason: "Rulers provide physical measurements for layout alignment on the printed page." },
  { question: "To add 'Shading' to every other row in a range automatically (4.4.5), which feature is most convenient?", options: ["Manual coloring", "Conditional Formatting (using MOD function) or 'Format as Table'", "Goal Seek", "Subtotals"], answer: "Conditional Formatting (using MOD function) or 'Format as Table'", category: "SDP", reason: "Using 'Banded Rows' in a Table format or a logical formula in Conditional Formatting automates alternating row colors." },
  { question: "In 'Types of Spreadsheet' (4.2), which software is a 'Cloud-based' equivalent to Excel?", options: ["VisiCalc", "Google Sheets", "Lotus 1-2-3", "Microsoft Access"], answer: "Google Sheets", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Sheets is a modern web-based spreadsheet that allows real-time online collaboration." },
  { question: "What happens if you use 'Absolute' references ($A$1) incorrectly in a large data table (4.4.7)?", options: ["The computer crashes", "The formula result will be the same for every row/column instead of calculating unique values", "The text turns red", "The sheet becomes a PDF"], answer: "The formula result will be the same for every row/column instead of calculating unique values", category: "SDP", reason: "Absolute references do not adapt to new locations, which can cause calculation logic errors if overused." },
  { question: "Which 'Default option' (4.4.10) can be toggled to show or hide the gridlines on the screen?", options: ["View Tab -> Gridlines", "Data Tab -> Filter", "Home Tab -> Bold", "Insert Tab -> Chart"], answer: "View Tab -> Gridlines", category: "SDP", reason: "Visual aids like gridlines, headings, and the formula bar are controlled via the View tab." },
  { question: "What is the 'Maximum' number of 'Scenarios' (4.4.18) you can create in one workbook?", options: ["10", "32", "255", "Unlimited"], answer: "32", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel has a technical limitation of 32 defined scenarios per worksheet." },
  { question: "Which tool (4.4.11) allows you to specify 'Rules' for data, such as 'Value must be greater than 100'?", options: ["Conditional Formatting", "Data Validation", "Goal Seek", "Sort"], answer: "Data Validation", category: "SDP", reason: "Data Validation enforces rules to ensure that only correct, logical data is entered into the system." },
  { question: "In Devanagari fonts (4.4.4), what key on the 'Preeti' layout is used for 'Halanta' (्)?", options: ["f", "d", "/", "s"], answer: "/", category: "SDP", reason: "In the legacy Preeti mapping, the forward slash (/) key produces the halanta sign." },
  { question: "To add a 'Border' only to the top edge of a cell (4.4.5), you use the 'Border' tool under the ______ group.", options: ["Editing", "Alignment", "Font", "Number"], answer: "Font", category: "SDP", reason: "Borders are categorized as part of the visual font styling group on the Home ribbon." },
  { question: "Which view (4.4.19) allows you to see the exact blue lines where Excel will split data across multiple sheets of paper?", options: ["Normal View", "Page Layout View", "Page Break Preview", "Reading View"], answer: "Page Break Preview", category: "SDP", reason: "Page Break Preview is the dedicated tool for managing physical print boundaries." },
  { question: "In 'Editing cell contents' (4.4.3), what is the function of the 'Esc' key?", options: ["Deletes the data", "Cancels the current entry/edit and restores the original value", "Saves the change", "Restarts the computer"], answer: "Cancels the current entry/edit and restores the original value", category: "SDP", reason: "Esc allows a user to abandon a change if they make a mistake during typing." },
  { question: "Which summary function (4.4.12) returns the 'Average' of a group in the Subtotal dialog?", options: ["Count", "Average", "Sum", "Max"], answer: "Average", category: "SDP", reason: "The Subtotal tool supports standard aggregations like Sum, Average, Min, and Max." },
  { question: "To 'Mirror' text (e.g. creating a reflection) in Excel (4.4.5 context), you should use:", options: ["Standard cell typing", "WordArt or a Text Box and applying 3D Rotation", "Conditional Formatting", "A Chart"], answer: "WordArt or a Text Box and applying 3D Rotation", category: "SDP", reason: "Cells cannot be flipped/rotated arbitrarily; text inside graphical containers is required for this effect." },
  { question: "What is 'Audit Trail' or 'Track Changes' in Excel (4.4.18 context)?", options: ["Deleting old files", "A feature that records who edited what cell and when", "Increasing CPU speed", "Checking for bad sectors"], answer: "A feature that records who edited what cell and when", category: "SDP", reason: "Tracking changes provides an history of spreadsheet evolution for accountability." },
  { question: "In 'Importing' data from a Web page (4.4.17), how does Excel recognize a table?", options: ["By looking for the word 'Table'", "By analyzing the HTML <table> tags in the website source code", "By checking the file size", "By asking the user to draw it"], answer: "By analyzing the HTML <table> tags in the website source code", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'From Web' import tool parses the website's structure to identify logical data grids." },
  { question: "Which shortcut adds a 'Currency' format ($) to the selected numbers instantly?", options: ["Ctrl + Shift + $", "Ctrl + Shift + %", "Ctrl + Shift + !", "Ctrl + Shift + @"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + $", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a standard numeric formatting shortcut in Excel (Ctrl+Shift+4)." },
  { question: "The 'Scenario Summary' report (4.4.18) is generated on:", options: ["The same sheet", "A new separate worksheet", "The status bar", "The printer directly"], answer: "A new separate worksheet", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel creates a new tab to present a side-by-side comparison of your defined scenarios." },
  { question: "Which function key 'Familiarity' (4.4 context) opens the 'Name Manager'?", options: ["Ctrl + F3", "Shift + F3", "Alt + F3", "Ctrl + N"], answer: "Ctrl + F3", category: "SDP", reason: "Management of logical cell names is handled via Ctrl+F3." },
  { question: "Under 'Customizing toolbars' (4.4.16), how can you export your Ribbon customizations for use on another PC?", options: ["Using a floppy disk", "The 'Import/Export' button in the Customize Ribbon settings", "Deleting the BIOS", "Sending a screenshot"], answer: "The 'Import/Export' button in the Customize Ribbon settings", category: "SDP", reason: "Windows allows for saving .exportedUI files to sync interface preferences." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of 'Consolidate' (4.4.12 context)?", options: ["To delete data", "To aggregate data from multiple ranges into one single summary range", "To check spelling", "To change fonts"], answer: "To aggregate data from multiple ranges into one single summary range", category: "SDP", reason: "Consolidation combines values (like quarterly totals) from several sources into one master table." },
  { question: "In 'Printing' (4.4.19), what is 'Scaling'?", options: ["Measuring the weight of the computer", "Adjusting the size of the worksheet to fit on a specified number of pages", "Changing the color of the ink", "Deleting sheets"], answer: "Adjusting the size of the worksheet to fit on a specified number of pages", category: "SDP", reason: "Scaling ensures that data-heavy spreadsheets don't overflow onto extra sheets of paper." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' option (4.4.5) allows you to hide the formula in the formula bar while keeping the result visible?", options: ["Locked", "Hidden (in Protection tab of Format Cells)", "Encrypted", "Restricted"], answer: "Hidden (in Protection tab of Format Cells)", category: "SDP", reason: "When a cell is 'Hidden' and the sheet is protected, the calculation logic is shielded from the user." },
  { question: "Which specific tool in Excel (4.4.18) is used to find the specific input value needed to achieve a desired formula result?", options: ["Scenario Manager", "Goal Seek", "Solver", "Pivot Table"], answer: "Goal Seek", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a 'What-If Analysis' tool that works backward from a target result to determine the required input." },
  { question: "In MS Excel (4.3), what is the technical name for a group of worksheets saved in a single file?", options: ["Workblock", "Workbook", "Workspace", "Sheetgroup"], answer: "Workbook", category: "SDP", reason: "The workbook is the container file (usually .xlsx) that holds individual tabs known as worksheets." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut is used to insert the 'Current Time' as a static value into a cell (4.4.1)?", options: ["Ctrl + ;", "Ctrl + Shift + :", "Alt + T", "Ctrl + T"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + :", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + semicolon (;) inserts the date; Ctrl + Shift + colon (:) inserts the time." },
  { question: "Which feature (4.4.18) allows you to summarize and analyze large datasets by 'pivoting' data between rows and columns?", options: ["Filter", "Data Validation", "Pivot Table", "Subtotal"], answer: "Pivot Table", category: "SDP", reason: "Pivot Tables allow for high-level data summarization and multi-dimensional analysis without changing the source data." },
  { question: "In the cell reference '$A1', which part is 'Absolute' (4.4.7)?", options: ["The Row (1)", "The Column (A)", "Both", "Neither"], answer: "The Column (A)", category: "SDP", reason: "The dollar sign ($) locks the element it precedes. Here, it precedes 'A', making the column absolute." },
  { question: "Which specific 'System Tool' in the Formulas tab (4.4.18) allows you to see which cells are used by the selected formula?", options: ["Error Checking", "Evaluate Formula", "Trace Precedents", "Trace Dependents"], answer: "Trace Precedents", category: "SDP", reason: "Trace Precedents draws arrows showing which cells provide data to the active formula." },
  { question: "When typing in Nepali 'Preeti' font in Excel (4.4.4), how does Excel handle 'Alphabetical Sorting'?", options: ["It sorts correctly by Devanagari rules", "It sorts by the English characters assigned to the keys", "It sorts by font size", "It sorts by color"], answer: "It sorts by the English characters assigned to the keys", category: "SDP", reason: "Preeti is a non-Unicode font; Excel only 'sees' the underlying ASCII (English) values of the keys pressed." },
  { question: "To add a 'Diagonal Border' to a cell (4.4.5), you must use which dialog box?", options: ["Page Setup", "Format Cells (Border tab)", "Insert Shapes", "Conditional Formatting"], answer: "Format Cells (Border tab)", category: "SDP", reason: "The Format Cells dialog provides advanced border options that the ribbon menu does not, including diagonals." },
  { question: "Which function (4.4.8) returns the 'Remainder' of a division operation?", options: ["=DIV()", "=REM()", "=MOD()", "=INT()"], answer: "=MOD()", category: "SDP", reason: "MOD stands for Modulo, which calculates the remainder after one number is divided by another." },
  { question: "Under 'Summarizing Data' (4.4.12), the Subtotal command automatically inserts which type of rows?", options: ["Header rows", "Empty rows", "Summary rows with functions like SUM or AVERAGE", "Hidden rows"], answer: "Summary rows with functions like SUM or AVERAGE", category: "SDP", reason: "Subtotal groups data and adds calculation rows to help summarize large lists." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) allows you to repeat row 1 on every printed page of a long list?", options: ["Header", "Freeze Panes", "Print Titles", "Page Break"], answer: "Print Titles", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Titles (Page Setup) allows for designating specific rows or columns to repeat on every physical sheet." },
  { question: "What happens when you 'Double-click' the fill handle of a cell that contains a formula (4.4.9)?", options: ["It deletes the formula", "It automatically fills the formula down to the end of the adjacent data range", "It opens the formula bar", "It prints the sheet"], answer: "It automatically fills the formula down to the end of the adjacent data range", category: "SDP", reason: "Double-clicking the fill handle is a shortcut for AutoFill that follows the length of the column next to it." },
  { question: "In the 'Excel Environment' (4.4.2), where is the 'Status Bar' located?", options: ["At the very top", "At the very bottom", "To the left of the grid", "Above the ribbon"], answer: "At the very bottom", category: "SDP", reason: "The status bar displays information like mode (Ready), zoom levels, and quick statistics (Sum/Avg)." },
  { question: "Which feature (4.4.18) is used to create and save 'alternate versions' of data within the same worksheet?", options: ["Goal Seek", "Scenario Manager", "Data Validation", "Consolidate"], answer: "Scenario Manager", category: "SDP", reason: "Scenario Manager allows users to save different sets of input values (best case, worst case) for calculations." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Undo' levels available in MS Excel 2010 by default (4.4.10)?", options: ["10", "20", "50", "100"], answer: "100", category: "SDP", reason: "Microsoft Excel 2010 and later support up to 100 levels of undoing actions." },
  { question: "Which 'Import' format (4.4.17) is a plain text format where data is separated by 'commas'?", options: [".txt", ".csv", ".xml", ".html"], answer: ".csv", category: "SDP", reason: ".csv stands for Comma Separated Values, a universal standard for data exchange." },
  { question: "To add 'Password Protection' to an Excel file so it cannot be opened (4.4.5), you use:", options: ["Protect Sheet", "Encrypt with Password", "Lock Cells", "Hide Formula"], answer: "Encrypt with Password", category: "SDP", reason: "Encryption (File -> Info) provides file-level security, unlike Sheet protection which only restricts editing." },
  { question: "Which function key 'Refreshes' all formulas in the workbook (4.4.7)?", options: ["F2", "F5", "F7", "F9"], answer: "F9", category: "SDP", reason: "F9 is the global command to recalculate all open workbooks." },
  { question: "Under 'Customizing Toolbars' (4.4.16), the 'Quick Access Toolbar' can be placed in which two positions?", options: ["Top or Bottom", "Left or Right", "Above or Below the Ribbon", "Center or Margin"], answer: "Above or Below the Ribbon", category: "SDP", reason: "Windows allows the QAT to be toggled between these two locations relative to the Ribbon tabs." },
  { question: "What error message does Excel show when a formula refers to a cell that has been 'Deleted' (4.4.18)?", options: ["#VALUE!", "#REF!", "#NAME?", "#NULL!"], answer: "#REF!", category: "SDP", reason: "#REF! indicates an invalid reference where the target cell address is gone." },
  { question: "Which 'Alignment' setting (4.4.5) allows text to be oriented vertically (bottom-to-top) within a cell?", options: ["Wrap Text", "Shrink to Fit", "Orientation", "Merge"], answer: "Orientation", category: "SDP", reason: "The Orientation setting in the Alignment group allows for rotating text degrees or directions." },
  { question: "A '.xltx' file extension (4.4.1) represents a Microsoft Excel:", options: ["Macro file", "Binary file", "Template", "Add-in"], answer: "Template", category: "SDP", reason: ".xltx is the standard extension for an Excel Template." },
  { question: "Which tool (4.4.11) allows you to temporarily hide rows that do not meet specific criteria?", options: ["Sort", "Filter", "Hide Row", "Group"], answer: "Filter", category: "SDP", reason: "Filtering allows for viewing subsets of data without actually deleting anything." },
  { question: "To start a 'New Line' inside the SAME cell (4.4.3), which keyboard combination is used?", options: ["Enter", "Shift + Enter", "Alt + Enter", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Alt + Enter", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt + Enter creates a manual line break within a single spreadsheet cell." },
  { question: "The 'Formula Bar' (4.4.2) is useful because it displays:", options: ["Only the result", "The underlying calculation or formula of the active cell", "The file name", "The number of sheets"], answer: "The underlying calculation or formula of the active cell", category: "SDP", reason: "Cells show the result, but the bar shows the logic that produced that result." },
  { question: "Which function key is used to enter 'Edit Mode' (4.4.3) for the current cell?", options: ["F1", "F2", "F5", "F12"], answer: "F2", category: "SDP", reason: "F2 puts the cursor at the end of the data in the cell for editing." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Rows' in an Excel 2010 worksheet (4.3)?", options: ["65,536", "1,048,576", "16,384", "Unlimited"], answer: "1,048,576", category: "SDP", reason: "Starting from the .xlsx format (Excel 2007+), the row limit is over 1 million." },
  { question: "Which 'Arithmetic Operator' has the highest precedence in Excel formulas (4.4.7)?", options: ["Addition (+)", "Multiplication (*)", "Exponentiation (^)", "Subtraction (-)"], answer: "Exponentiation (^)", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel follows PEMDAS; Exponents come before Multiplication and Division." },
  { question: "To select 'Non-adjacent' cells (4.4.3), which key must you hold while clicking?", options: ["Shift", "Alt", "Ctrl", "Spacebar"], answer: "Ctrl", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl allows for multi-selection of disjointed cells or ranges." },
  { question: "The 'AutoSum' button (4.4.8) is represented by which mathematical symbol?", options: ["Δ", "Σ (Sigma)", "Ω", "π"], answer: "Σ (Sigma)", category: "SDP", reason: "Sigma is the standard mathematical symbol for summation." },
  { question: "Which 'Audit' tool (4.4.18) evaluates a nested formula one part at a time?", options: ["Evaluate Formula", "Error Checking", "Trace Dependents", "Show Formulas"], answer: "Evaluate Formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Evaluate Formula lets you step through the calculation steps of an expression." },
  { question: "To change the 'Orientation' (4.4.19) of a single sheet, you look in the ______ tab.", options: ["Home", "Design", "Page Layout", "View"], answer: "Page Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Page setup tools like margins and orientation are in the Page Layout tab." },
  { question: "What does a 'Relative Cell Reference' (4.4.7) do when a formula is copied one row down?", options: ["Stay exactly the same", "Increase the row number by one", "Change to the column next to it", "Delete itself"], answer: "Increase the row number by one", category: "SDP", reason: "Relative references change based on the position where the formula is moved." },
  { question: "Which 'Chart' type (4.4.13) is best for showing 'Scatter' correlations between two variables?", options: ["Bar Chart", "Line Chart", "X Y (Scatter) Chart", "Pie Chart"], answer: "X Y (Scatter) Chart", category: "SDP", reason: "Scatter charts plot points based on coordinate values to show mathematical relationships." },
  { question: "In 'Exporting' (4.4.17), a PDF is preferred because:", options: ["It is editable", "It preserves formatting and can be opened on almost any device", "It stores macros", "It is faster to calculate"], answer: "It preserves formatting and can be opened on almost any device", category: "SDP", reason: "PDF is a fixed-layout document standard for sharing finalized data." },
  { question: "Which 'Formatting' option (4.4.5) allows you to specify decimal places for numbers?", options: ["Alignment", "Font", "Number", "Protection"], answer: "Number", category: "SDP", reason: "The Number tab in Format Cells manages decimal precision, currency, and date formats." },
  { question: "The instantaneous 'Sum' or 'Average' of a selected range appears in the ______ (4.4.2).", options: ["Formula Bar", "Name Box", "Status Bar", "Title Bar"], answer: "Status Bar", category: "SDP", reason: "The status bar at the bottom provides quick statistical summaries of any selection." },
  { question: "What is the result of '=AVERAGE(10, 20, 30)'?", options: ["60", "20", "15", "10"], answer: "20", category: "SDP", reason: "(10 + 20 + 30) / 3 = 20." },
  { question: "Which 'Indentation' (4.4.5) tool increases the space between the cell border and its text?", options: ["Wrap Text", "Increase Indent", "Merge Cells", "Orientation"], answer: "Increase Indent", category: "SDP", reason: "Increase Indent adds horizontal padding within the cell." },
  { question: "In 'Protection' (4.4.5), checking the 'Hidden' box for a cell means its ______ will not be visible in the formula bar when protected.", options: ["Value", "Formula", "Border", "Font"], answer: "Formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Hiding formulas prevents users from seeing the logic behind calculated values." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Spreadsheet Type' (4.2) is known as 'Open Source' and often used on Linux?", options: ["MS Excel", "LibreOffice Calc", "Google Sheets", "Apple Numbers"], answer: "LibreOffice Calc", category: "SDP", reason: "LibreOffice Calc is a prominent free and open-source spreadsheet alternative." },
  { question: "What does a 'Circular Reference' (4.4.7) warning mean?", options: ["The file is saved in a circle", "A formula refers directly or indirectly to its own cell", "The data is in a pie chart", "The internet is down"], answer: "A formula refers directly or indirectly to its own cell", category: "SDP", reason: "This creates an infinite loop where the calculation cannot finish." },
  { question: "To add 'Borders' (4.4.5) through the Home tab, you look in which group?", options: ["Alignment", "Font", "Styles", "Editing"], answer: "Font", category: "SDP", reason: "Borders are categorized as a font-style attribute on the Home ribbon." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) allows you to adjust the gap between the edge of the paper and the data?", options: ["Orientation", "Scaling", "Margins", "Gridlines"], answer: "Margins", category: "SDP", reason: "Margins define the printable area of the sheet." },
  { question: "Which function (4.4.8) counts how many cells in a range satisfy a condition?", options: ["=COUNT()", "=COUNTA()", "=COUNTIF()", "=IF()"], answer: "=COUNTIF()", category: "SDP", reason: "COUNTIF evaluates a range against a single logical criterion." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing menus' (4.4.16), the 'Ribbon' can be minimized by which keyboard shortcut?", options: ["Ctrl + F1", "Ctrl + F2", "Alt + F1", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Ctrl + F1", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl+F1 toggles the visibility of the Ribbon to provide more working space." },
  { question: "What is 'VLOOKUP' (4.4.8 context)?", options: ["A way to print", "A function to search for a value in a column and return data from the same row", "A type of chart", "A virus scan"], answer: "A function to search for a value in a column and return data from the same row", category: "SDP", reason: "VLOOKUP stands for 'Vertical Lookup'." },
  { question: "To see 'Gridlines' (4.4.19) on a printed physical page, you must enable it in:", options: ["View tab", "Page Layout -> Sheet Options -> Print Gridlines", "Data tab", "Review tab"], answer: "Page Layout -> Sheet Options -> Print Gridlines", category: "SDP", reason: "Seeing gridlines on the monitor and printing them on paper are two different settings." },
  { question: "Which 'Series' (4.4.9) generation is based on a difference of 1 by default (e.g. 1, 2, 3)?", options: ["Linear", "Growth", "Date", "AutoFill"], answer: "Linear", category: "SDP", reason: "Linear series add a step value consistently to each new number." },
  { question: "What is 'Audit' in Excel primarily for (4.4.18)?", options: ["Paying taxes", "Troubleshooting and verifying formula logic", "Scanning for images", "Increasing speed"], answer: "Troubleshooting and verifying formula logic", category: "SDP", reason: "Formula auditing tools help find errors in complex spreadsheet calculations." },
  { question: "Which early spreadsheet program is credited as the first to use the 'Slash' (/) key to open its menu system (4.2)?", options: ["MS Excel", "Lotus 1-2-3", "VisiCalc", "Quattro Pro"], answer: "Lotus 1-2-3", category: "SDP", reason: "Lotus 1-2-3 introduced the '/' menu shortcut, which was so popular that Excel still supports it as a legacy 'Lotus Compatibility' setting." },
  { question: "In Excel (4.3), what is the primary purpose of a 'Workspace' (.xlw) file?", options: ["To compress the file size", "To save the layout and display settings of all currently open workbooks", "To encrypt a single sheet", "To convert data to a website"], answer: "To save the layout and display settings of all currently open workbooks", category: "SDP", reason: "A Workspace file allows a user to reload a multi-workbook session exactly as it was, including window sizes and positions." },
  { question: "Which 'Status Bar' (4.4.2) mode allows you to see the sum of selected cells without typing a formula?", options: ["Ready Mode", "Edit Mode", "Point Mode", "AutoCalculate"], answer: "AutoCalculate", category: "SDP", reason: "The Status Bar uses AutoCalculate to show Sum, Average, and Count for any numerical range currently highlighted." },
  { question: "In 'Formula Auditing' (4.4.18), which tool helps you find out 'why' a cell contains an error like #VALUE! or #DIV/0!?", options: ["Trace Precedents", "Trace Dependents", "Error Checking", "Show Formulas"], answer: "Error Checking", category: "SDP", reason: "The Error Checking tool identifies common mistakes and provides explanations or suggestions for fixes." },
  { question: "When using the 'Subtotal' command (4.4.12), what is the first mandatory step before applying the tool?", options: ["Protect the sheet", "Filter the data", "Sort the data by the grouping column", "Create a chart"], answer: "Sort the data by the grouping column", category: "SDP", reason: "Subtotal adds a line every time a value changes; if data isn't sorted, it will create multiple redundant subtotals." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' option (4.4.5) allows a user to see the result of a calculation but prevents them from seeing the actual formula code in the formula bar?", options: ["Locked", "Hidden", "Encrypted", "Restricted"], answer: "Hidden", category: "SDP", reason: "Checking 'Hidden' in the Protection tab and then protecting the sheet hides the logic (formula) from the user." },
  { question: "In 'Devanagari Fonts' (4.4.4), why is 'Unicode' required for effective data analysis in Excel?", options: ["It is faster to type", "It uses standard character mapping, allowing Excel to sort and filter Nepali names alphabetically", "It makes the text look like English", "It is free"], answer: "It uses standard character mapping, allowing Excel to sort and filter Nepali names alphabetically", category: "SDP", reason: "Legacy fonts like Preeti are visual overlays; Excel sorts them by the underlying English ASCII keys rather than the Nepali alphabet." },
  { question: "Which specific environment element (4.4.2) is used to navigate through a worksheet that extends vertically beyond the screen?", options: ["Horizontal Scrollbar", "Vertical Scrollbar", "Menu Bar", "Name Box"], answer: "Vertical Scrollbar", category: "SDP", reason: "Scrollbars are the standard GUI components for viewing content larger than the window frame." },
  { question: "To add a 'Diagonal Hatching' pattern to a cell's background (4.4.5), you use the 'Pattern Style' dropdown in which tab of Format Cells?", options: ["Alignment", "Fill", "Font", "Number"], answer: "Fill", category: "SDP", reason: "The Fill tab manages background colors, patterns, and gradients for cell interiors." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Scenarios' (4.4.18) you can define on a single worksheet?", options: ["10", "32", "255", "Unlimited"], answer: "32", category: "SDP", reason: "MS Excel has a technical limitation of 32 distinct scenarios per worksheet." },
  { question: "Which 'Formatting' command (4.4.6) is used to set a specific height for all selected rows simultaneously?", options: ["AutoFit", "Row Height", "Merge Cells", "Shrink to Fit"], answer: "Row Height", category: "SDP", reason: "The Row Height dialog allows the user to enter a numeric value in points to standardize row sizes." },
  { question: "Which tool (4.4.18) allows you to step through a calculation process one logical operation at a time?", options: ["Evaluate Formula", "Goal Seek", "Pivot Table", "Data Validation"], answer: "Evaluate Formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Evaluate Formula allows the user to see how Excel processes each step of a complex nested formula." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing Toolbars' (4.4.16), the 'Quick Access Toolbar' can be moved to which location?", options: ["Inside the formula bar", "Below the Ribbon", "Left of the scrollbar", "Inside a cell"], answer: "Below the Ribbon", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT can reside either above the Ribbon (default) or below it for easier access with the mouse." },
  { question: "When 'Importing' data from a text file (4.4.17), which character is most commonly used as a 'Delimited' separator?", options: ["Colon (:)", "Comma (,) or Tab", "Space ( )", "Hyphen (-)"], answer: "Comma (,) or Tab", category: "SDP", reason: "CSV (Comma Separated) and TXT (Tab Delimited) are the industry standards for importing tabular data into Excel." },
  { question: "What happens if you use 'Absolute' references ($C$1) in a formula and then move that formula via 'Cut and Paste' (4.4.7)?", options: ["The reference changes to relative", "The reference remains fixed to $C$1", "The formula is deleted", "The cell turns red"], answer: "The reference remains fixed to $C$1", category: "SDP", reason: "Absolute references are locked to a specific coordinate and do not update regardless of where the formula is placed." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) ensures that row headers appear at the top of every printed page?", options: ["Freeze Panes", "Print Titles (Rows to repeat at top)", "Header", "Page Break"], answer: "Print Titles (Rows to repeat at top)", category: "SDP", reason: "While Freeze Panes is for the screen, Print Titles is the specific setting for paper output." },
  { question: "In 'Formatting Number' (4.4.5), the 'Accounting' format differs from 'Currency' because it:", options: ["Hides the value", "Aligns currency symbols and decimal points vertically in a column", "Deletes decimals", "Only works for US Dollars"], answer: "Aligns currency symbols and decimal points vertically in a column", category: "SDP", reason: "Accounting format places the currency symbol at the left edge of the cell for better column readability." },
  { question: "Which 'Default option' (4.4.10) can be changed to ensure Excel always opens a specific number of sheets in new workbooks?", options: ["View Tab -> Settings", "Excel Options -> General -> Include this many sheets", "Review Tab -> Protection", "Data Tab -> Properties"], answer: "Excel Options -> General -> Include this many sheets", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a global application setting that defines the initial environment for every new file." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of 'Scenario Manager' (4.4.18)?", options: ["To find a target value", "To create and save different sets of values that you can switch between", "To check spelling", "To merge workbooks"], answer: "To create and save different sets of values that you can switch between", category: "SDP", reason: "Scenarios are used to compare forecasted results based on varying sets of input data." },
  { question: "In 'Exporting' (4.4.17), which format is strictly 'Text Only' with no formatting or formulas?", options: [".xlsx", ".pdf", ".txt (Plain Text)", ".xml"], answer: ".txt (Plain Text)", category: "SDP", reason: "Plain text files contain only the raw characters and none of the spreadsheet's metadata or logic." },
  { question: "Which 'Alignment' setting (4.4.5) is used to fit a long string of text into a cell by reducing its font size?", options: ["Wrap Text", "Merge Cells", "Shrink to Fit", "Orientation"], answer: "Shrink to Fit", category: "SDP", reason: "Shrink to Fit automatically scales the text down so it remains on one line within the current column width." },
  { question: "Under 'Customizing toolbars' (4.4.16), where can you find the 'Import/Export' button for your interface customizations?", options: ["File -> Print", "The bottom of the 'Customize Ribbon' window in Excel Options", "Status Bar", "Formula Bar"], answer: "The bottom of the 'Customize Ribbon' window in Excel Options", category: "SDP", reason: "Users can save their customized interface settings as a '.exportedUI' file to move them to another computer." },
  { question: "Which 'Arithmetic Operator' (4.4.7) has the lowest precedence in Excel calculations?", options: ["Multiplication (*)", "Division (/)", "Addition (+) and Subtraction (-)", "Exponentiation (^)"], answer: "Addition (+) and Subtraction (-)", category: "SDP", reason: "According to the Order of Operations (PEMDAS), addition and subtraction are performed after exponents, multiplication, and division." },
  { question: "In 'Formula Auditing' (4.4.18), what does 'Trace Dependents' do?", options: ["Finds errors", "Shows arrows indicating which formulas use the data from the active cell", "Deletes empty cells", "Calculates the total"], answer: "Shows arrows indicating which formulas use the data from the active cell", category: "SDP", reason: "Trace Dependents shows which other cells on the sheet 'depend' on the value of the currently selected cell." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) allows you to reduce the document to 75% of its original size for printing?", options: ["Margins", "Orientation", "Scaling (Adjust to %)", "Gridlines"], answer: "Scaling (Adjust to %)", category: "SDP", reason: "Scaling allows for custom magnification or reduction of the spreadsheet for physical output." },
  { question: "What is 'VLOOKUP' primarily classified as (4.4.8 context)?", options: ["Statistical Function", "Lookup & Reference Function", "Logical Function", "Text Function"], answer: "Lookup & Reference Function", category: "SDP", reason: "VLOOKUP is the standard function used for searching a value in a table and returning data from a different column." },
  { question: "In Preeti font (4.4.4), how is the character 'त्त' (Conjunct character) typed?", options: ["t + t", "u + Z", "Alt + 0170", "Shift + { "], answer: "Alt + 0170", category: "SDP", reason: "Legacy non-Unicode fonts rely on specialized Alt-code combinations for complex conjunct characters." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' tool (4.4.5) allows you to hide specific cells from a user's view while keeping them available for calculations?", options: ["Hide Row/Column", "Password to Open", "Digital Signature", "Conditional formatting"], answer: "Hide Row/Column", category: "SDP", reason: "Hiding rows or columns is a standard layout protection method to prevent users from seeing intermediate calculation steps." },
  { question: "The 'Name Box' (4.4.2) can be used to select a range instantly by:", options: ["Typing the formula", "Typing a cell range like 'A1:B20' and pressing Enter", "Changing the font", "Printing the sheet"], answer: "Typing a cell range like 'A1:B20' and pressing Enter", category: "SDP", reason: "The Name Box serves as a jump-tool; entering coordinates instantly moves the selection and scrolls to that area." },
  { question: "To start a 'Growth Series' (4.4.9) (e.g., 2, 4, 8, 16...), you must use which dialog box?", options: ["AutoSum", "Fill -> Series -> Type: Growth", "Format Cells", "Pivot Table"], answer: "Fill -> Series -> Type: Growth", category: "SDP", reason: "Growth series use a geometric progression (multiplication) rather than the linear (addition) progression of a standard fill." },
  { question: "Which 'Summarizing' tool (4.4.12) allows you to aggregate values from multiple sheets into one summary range?", options: ["Pivot Table", "Subtotal", "Consolidate", "Filter"], answer: "Consolidate", category: "SDP", reason: "Consolidation (Data tab) is designed to combine results from multiple separate ranges into a master report." },
  { question: "Which 'Element' (4.4.2) allows for fine adjustments to the left and right margins of the sheet?", options: ["Scrollbar", "Horizontal Ruler", "Status Bar", "Formula Bar"], answer: "Horizontal Ruler", category: "SDP", reason: "In Page Layout view, the horizontal ruler displays the exact physical measurement of columns and margins." },
  { question: "To remove 'Borders' (4.4.5) from a cell completely, you should select which option in the Border menu?", options: ["All Borders", "No Border", "Outside Borders", "Clear Contents"], answer: "No Border", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'No Border' option resets all cell boundary lines to the default invisible gridlines." },
  { question: "In 'Printing' (4.4.19), what is 'Fit to 1 page wide by 1 tall' used for?", options: ["To increase the font size", "To force a large amount of data to be compressed onto a single sheet of paper", "To print only the charts", "To delete hidden sheets"], answer: "To force a large amount of data to be compressed onto a single sheet of paper", category: "SDP", reason: "This scaling option is the primary way to avoid 'orphaned' columns or rows printing on extra pages." },
  { question: "Which function key triggers the 'Spell Checking' utility (4.4.15)?", options: ["F2", "F5", "F7", "F9"], answer: "F7", category: "SDP", reason: "F7 is the standard Microsoft Office shortcut for the spelling and grammar checker." },
  { question: "A 'Pivot Table' (4.4.18) is unique because it does NOT:", options: ["Sum numbers", "Change the original source data", "Support filtering", "Create charts"], answer: "Change the original source data", category: "SDP", reason: "Pivot Tables are analytical layers that provide summaries without altering the raw records in the underlying table." },
  { question: "In 'Excel Environment' (4.4.2), where would you find the 'Split' command to view two parts of a sheet at once?", options: ["Home Tab", "Insert Tab", "View Tab", "Review Tab"], answer: "View Tab", category: "SDP", reason: "All window management tools (Split, Freeze Panes, New Window) are located in the View tab." },
  { question: "What happens when you 'Modify' a cell content by pressing F2 and then Esc (4.4.3)?", options: ["The cell is deleted", "The changes are saved", "The edit is canceled and the original content is restored", "The computer restarts"], answer: "The edit is canceled and the original content is restored", category: "SDP", reason: "Escape (Esc) is the standard command to abandon an edit-in-progress in Excel." },
  { question: "Which 'Import' format (4.4.17) uses 'Tags' (like <Data>) to structure information?", options: [".txt", ".csv", ".xml", ".html"], answer: ".xml", category: "SDP", reason: ".xml stands for eXtensible Markup Language, a structured data format widely used for web and application interchange." },
  { question: "In 'Security' (4.4.5), a 'Locked' cell is only truly protected when:", options: ["The file is saved", "The worksheet is Protected (Review -> Protect Sheet)", "The font is bold", "The computer has a password"], answer: "The worksheet is Protected (Review -> Protect Sheet)", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Locked' attribute of a cell is passive until the global 'Protect Sheet' command activates all locked constraints." },
  { question: "To change the 'Orientation' (4.4.19) so the page is horizontal, you choose:", options: ["Portrait", "Landscape", "Square", "Custom"], answer: "Landscape", category: "SDP", reason: "Landscape orientation rotates the page 90 degrees, making it wider than it is tall." },
  { question: "Which 'Subtotal' (4.4.12) setting determines when a new subtotal row is inserted?", options: ["At each change in [Column Name]", "Every 10 rows", "Only at the end", "When the cell is red"], answer: "At each change in [Column Name]", category: "SDP", reason: "Subtotal logic relies on detecting a change in value within a specific field to trigger a summation." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Chart' (4.4.13) is used primarily for statistical quality control or scientific range data?", options: ["Pie Chart", "Line Chart", "Box and Whisker / Area Chart", "Histogram / Radar"], answer: "Histogram / Radar", category: "SDP", reason: "While basic, these advanced charts are used for frequency distribution and comparative metrics." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Select all text' in the Formula Bar (4.4.2)?", options: ["Ctrl + A", "Ctrl + L", "Ctrl + S", "Alt + A"], answer: "Ctrl + A", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + A is the universal shortcut to 'Select All' in any text entry field in Windows." },
  { question: "To start a 'Series' (4.4.9) of years (2020, 2021, 2022...), you can use the 'Type' option of:", options: ["Linear", "Growth", "Date (Year)", "AutoFill"], answer: "Date (Year)", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel identifies years as a specific unit of the Date type for sequential filling." },
  { question: "Which function key closes the 'Active Workbook' window?", options: ["Ctrl + W", "Ctrl + F4", "Alt + F4", "Both A and B"], answer: "Both A and B", category: "SDP", reason: "In Windows and Office, both Ctrl+W and Ctrl+F4 are standardized shortcuts for closing the current document." },
  { question: "What is 'Audit' in Excel meant to accomplish (4.4.18)?", options: ["Cleaning the desk", "Finding and resolving errors in logic and data flow", "Increasing internet speed", "Saving time"], answer: "Finding and resolving errors in logic and data flow", category: "SDP", reason: "Auditing tools allow a user to visualize and step-through formulas to ensure accuracy." },
  { question: "Which 'Export' option (4.4.17) allows a user to open the data in a standard web browser?", options: ["Save as CSV", "Save as Web Page (.html)", "Save as Template", "Save as Image"], answer: "Save as Web Page (.html)", category: "SDP", reason: "HTML is the native language of the web; exporting to this format makes the sheet viewable online." },
  { question: "In 'Page Setting' (4.4.19), what is 'Gridlines' setting under the Sheet tab for?", options: ["Showing them on the screen", "Printing them on the physical paper", "Deleting them", "Making them bold"], answer: "Printing them on the physical paper", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel typically hides gridlines during printing unless this specific box is checked in Page Setup." },
  { question: "The 'Goal Seek' dialog (4.4.18) requires three inputs: Set cell, To value, and:", options: ["By changing font", "By changing cell", "By sorting row", "By deleting column"], answer: "By changing cell", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal seek needs a target value and a variable cell to iterate through until the target is hit." },
  { question: "Which of the following spreadsheet programs was the first to introduce the concept of 'cell' addressing using letters and numbers?", options: ["MS Excel", "Lotus 1-2-3", "VisiCalc", "Quattro Pro"], answer: "VisiCalc", category: "SDP", reason: "VisiCalc (1979) established the A1, B2 coordinate system that remains the standard for all modern spreadsheets." },
  { question: "In Excel (4.3), what is the primary benefit of a 'Workspace' (.xlw) file compared to a 'Workbook' (.xlsx) file?", options: ["It reduces file size", "It opens multiple linked workbooks simultaneously in their saved layout", "It allows for 3D charts", "It can be read by Notepad"], answer: "It opens multiple linked workbooks simultaneously in their saved layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Workspace files save the state of a multi-file project session, making it easier to resume complex work." },
  { question: "Which specific area of the 'Status Bar' (4.4.2) allows you to toggle between Normal and Page Layout views?", options: ["The left side", "The middle", "The right side (View Shortcuts)", "The Formula Bar"], answer: "The right side (View Shortcuts)", category: "SDP", reason: "The View Shortcut icons are located next to the zoom slider at the bottom-right of the window." },
  { question: "In 'Formula Auditing' (4.4.18), which tool helps you visually find cells that an 'Error' in the active cell is coming from?", options: ["Trace Precedents", "Trace Error", "Evaluate Formula", "Error Checking"], answer: "Trace Error", category: "SDP", reason: "Trace Error draws arrows to show the lineage of an error value like #VALUE! or #DIV/0!." },
  { question: "Which feature (4.4.12) allows you to aggregate values from multiple ranges or sheets into a single summary range?", options: ["Sorting", "Filtering", "Consolidate", "PivotTable"], answer: "Consolidate", category: "SDP", reason: "The Consolidate tool is designed to combine results (like sums) from various sources into one summary table." },
  { question: "To prevent a user from seeing the 'Calculation Logic' in the formula bar while keeping the result visible (4.4.5), which setting is used?", options: ["Locked", "Hidden (in Protection tab)", "Encrypted", "Restricted"], answer: "Hidden (in Protection tab)", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Hidden' attribute hides the formula from the bar once the worksheet is protected." },
  { question: "In Devanagari typing for Excel (4.4.4), why is 'Unicode' considered more 'Data-Logic' friendly than Preeti font?", options: ["Unicode is smaller", "Unicode characters are recognized as distinct semantic units, making sorting A-Z accurate", "Preeti font is invisible", "Unicode only works on the internet"], answer: "Unicode characters are recognized as distinct semantic units, making sorting A-Z accurate", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel can sort Unicode text based on the actual alphabet, whereas Preeti follows the English ASCII values of the keys." },
  { question: "Which specific environment element (4.4.2) is used to navigate through a worksheet horizontally (left to right)?", options: ["Vertical Scrollbar", "Horizontal Scrollbar", "Menu Bar", "Name Box"], answer: "Horizontal Scrollbar", category: "SDP", reason: "Scrollbars are the standard GUI components for navigating content larger than the window frame." },
  { question: "To add a 'Gradient' or 'Two-color' background to a cell (4.4.5), you use which option in the 'Fill' tab of Format Cells?", options: ["Solid Color", "Fill Effects", "Pattern Style", "Conditional Formatting"], answer: "Fill Effects", category: "SDP", reason: "Fill Effects allows for advanced background styling like gradients and textures within a cell." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Undo' levels supported in MS Excel 2010/2013 (4.4.10)?", options: ["10", "50", "100", "Unlimited"], answer: "100", category: "SDP", reason: "Modern versions of Excel allow users to reverse up to the last 100 actions." },
  { question: "Which 'Formatting' command (4.4.6) is used to ensure a column width perfectly fits the longest content currently in it?", options: ["Row Height", "AutoFit Selection", "AutoFit Column Width", "Merge Cells"], answer: "AutoFit Column Width", category: "SDP", reason: "AutoFit automatically adjusts dimensions based on the data to prevent text cutting or empty space." },
  { question: "Which tool (4.4.18) allows you to step through each individual calculation step of a complex nested formula?", options: ["Evaluate Formula", "Goal Seek", "Scenario Manager", "Data Validation"], answer: "Evaluate Formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Evaluate Formula provides a 'Step-In' feature to debug long or complex expressions." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing Toolbars' (4.4.16), where can the Quick Access Toolbar (QAT) be positioned?", options: ["Above the Ribbon only", "Below the Ribbon only", "Either Above or Below the Ribbon", "On the Status Bar"], answer: "Either Above or Below the Ribbon", category: "SDP", reason: "Users can toggle the QAT's location to suit their workflow and mouse movement habits." },
  { question: "When 'Importing' data (4.4.17), which character is most commonly used in '.csv' files to separate fields?", options: ["Colon (:)", "Comma (,)", "Space ( )", "Hyphen (-)"], answer: "Comma (,)", category: "SDP", reason: "CSV stands for Comma Separated Values; it is the most common format for tabular data transfer." },
  { question: "What happens to 'Relative' references (A1) if you move the formula to a new location using 'Cut and Paste' (4.4.7)?", options: ["The reference remains the same (A1)", "The reference updates based on the distance moved", "The formula is deleted", "The cell turns red"], answer: "The reference remains the same (A1)", category: "SDP", reason: "Unlike 'Copy/Paste' where relative refs update, 'Cut/Paste' preserves the exact logical link to the original source." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) ensures that specific column headers appear on every printed sheet of a wide document?", options: ["Freeze Panes", "Print Titles (Columns to repeat at left)", "Footer", "Page Break"], answer: "Print Titles (Columns to repeat at left)", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Titles allows for repeating designated rows or columns on every physical page of the output." },
  { question: "In 'Number Formatting' (4.4.5), which format is used for very large numbers using the 'E+' notation (e.g., 1.23E+11)?", options: ["General", "Number", "Scientific", "Fraction"], answer: "Scientific", category: "SDP", reason: "Scientific notation is used to represent very large or very small numbers in a compact format." },
  { question: "Which 'Default option' (4.4.10) can be changed to set the 'Standard Font' used for every new workbook?", options: ["View Tab", "Excel Options -> General -> When creating new workbooks", "Insert Tab", "Data Tab"], answer: "Excel Options -> General -> When creating new workbooks", category: "SDP", reason: "This global setting defines the default typeface and size for the entire application." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Scenario Manager' (4.4.18)?", options: ["To find a target result", "To save and switch between different sets of input values", "To check spelling", "To merge cells"], answer: "To save and switch between different sets of input values", category: "SDP", reason: "Scenarios allow users to compare multiple business models (e.g., Best Case vs. Worst Case) easily." },
  { question: "In 'Exporting' (4.4.17), which format is strictly for data structure with 'Tags' like <Row>?", options: [".xlsx", ".pdf", ".xml (Extensible Markup Language)", ".txt"], answer: ".xml (Extensible Markup Language)", category: "SDP", reason: "XML is a structured data format used for sharing data between different applications and platforms." },
  { question: "Which 'Alignment' setting (4.4.5) is used to center a heading across multiple columns without merging them?", options: ["Merge & Center", "Center Across Selection", "Justify", "Shrink to Fit"], answer: "Center Across Selection", category: "SDP", reason: "Center Across Selection provides the same visual effect as merging but maintains individual cell identity." },
  { question: "Under 'Customizing toolbars' (4.4.16), where can you find the 'Reset' button to return the Ribbon to factory settings?", options: ["Insert Tab", "The bottom of the 'Customize the Ribbon' dialog", "Status Bar", "View Tab"], answer: "The bottom of the 'Customize the Ribbon' dialog", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel provides a reset option to undo all personalized interface modifications easily." },
  { question: "Which 'Arithmetic Operator' (4.4.7) is calculated 'First' by default in an Excel formula?", options: ["Addition (+)", "Multiplication (*)", "Exponentiation (^)", "Subtraction (-)"], answer: "Exponentiation (^)", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel follows PEMDAS; Exponents (^) have higher precedence than Multiplication, Division, Addition, or Subtraction." },
  { question: "In 'Formula Auditing' (4.4.18), what does 'Trace Precedents' do?", options: ["Finds errors", "Shows arrows pointing to which cells provide data to the active formula", "Deletes the formula", "Calculates the total"], answer: "Shows arrows pointing to which cells provide data to the active formula", category: "SDP", reason: "Trace Precedents visually maps the flow of data into the selected calculation." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' (4.4.19) allows you to reduce the document to 50% of its original size for printing?", options: ["Margins", "Orientation", "Scaling (Adjust to %)", "Gridlines"], answer: "Scaling (Adjust to %)", category: "SDP", reason: "Scaling allows for custom magnification or reduction of the spreadsheet output." },
  { question: "What is 'HLOOKUP' primarily used for (4.4.8 context)?", options: ["Vertical searches", "Horizontal searches across the top row of a range", "Adding up numbers", "Sorting text"], answer: "Horizontal searches across the top row of a range", category: "SDP", reason: "HLOOKUP is the horizontal equivalent of VLOOKUP, searching in the top row and returning values from below." },
  { question: "In Preeti font (4.4.4), how is the character 'ज्ञ' (Conjunct character) typically typed?", options: ["j + y", "Shift + {", "Alt + 0165", "Alt + 0171"], answer: "Alt + 0171", category: "SDP", reason: "Legacy non-Unicode fonts rely on specific Alt-code combinations for specialized conjunct characters." },
  { question: "Which 'Protection' setting (4.4.5) allows you to set a password to prevent anyone from 'unhiding' a hidden sheet?", options: ["Protect Sheet", "Protect Workbook (Structure)", "Encryption", "Read-only mode"], answer: "Protect Workbook (Structure)", category: "SDP", reason: "Protecting the Workbook structure locks the sheet tabs, preventing adding, deleting, or unhiding them." },
  { question: "The 'Name Box' (4.4.2) can be used to select all 'Named Ranges' by:", options: ["Typing a formula", "Clicking the drop-down arrow next to it", "Formatting the text", "Printing the sheet"], answer: "Clicking the drop-down arrow next to it", category: "SDP", reason: "The Name Box contains a list of all defined range names in the current workbook for quick navigation." },
  { question: "To start a 'Date Series' (4.4.9) that increments by 'Months' (e.g., Jan, Feb, Mar), you use the 'Type' option of:", options: ["Linear", "Growth", "Date (Month)", "AutoFill"], answer: "Date (Month)", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel allows for specific date-unit increments within the Series dialog." },
  { question: "Which 'Summarizing' tool (4.4.12) is most effective for providing a 'Count' of items in multiple categories at once?", options: ["Pivot Table", "Subtotal", "Consolidate", "Filter"], answer: "Pivot Table", category: "SDP", reason: "Pivot Tables are the most powerful tool for multi-dimensional data aggregation and counting." },
  { question: "Which 'Element' (4.4.2) is used to visually adjust the 'Tab Stops' in a selected cell (though rare in Excel)?", options: ["Scrollbar", "Horizontal Ruler", "Status Bar", "Formula Bar"], answer: "Horizontal Ruler", category: "SDP", reason: "In Page Layout view, the ruler shows physical measurements and can be used for indents and alignment." },
  { question: "To add a 'Double underline' border to the bottom of a cell (4.4.5), you use the 'Border' tool under the ______ group.", options: ["Editing", "Alignment", "Font", "Number"], answer: "Font", category: "SDP", reason: "Borders are grouped with other visual font/character styling tools on the Home tab." },
  { question: "In 'Printing' (4.4.19), what is 'Black and White' mode under the Sheet tab used for?", options: ["To save ink by ignoring cell colors and patterns", "To make the text bold", "To hide the gridlines", "To delete hidden sheets"], answer: "To save ink by ignoring cell colors and patterns", category: "SDP", reason: "This setting forces the printer to use only black ink, converting colors to grayscale or white." },
  { question: "Which function key is the shortcut to 'F7' (4.4.15)?", options: ["Save As", "Spell Check", "Recalculate", "Insert Chart"], answer: "Spell Check", category: "SDP", reason: "F7 is the universal command for spell-checking in the MS Office suite." },
  { question: "A 'Pivot Table' (4.4.18) can also be used to create an interactive ______ representing the summary data.", options: ["Text Box", "Pivot Chart", "WordArt", "PDF"], answer: "Pivot Chart", category: "SDP", reason: "Pivot Charts provide a visual graphical layer linked directly to the Pivot Table data." },
  { question: "In 'Excel Environment' (4.4.2), where is the 'New Window' command to view the same sheet in two windows?", options: ["Home Tab", "Insert Tab", "View Tab", "Review Tab"], answer: "View Tab", category: "SDP", reason: "All window-related commands are centralized in the View tab." },
  { question: "What happens if you are 'Editing' a cell and press 'Enter' (4.4.3)?", options: ["The edit is canceled", "The change is saved and the selection moves down one row", "The cell is deleted", "The computer restarts"], answer: "The change is saved and the selection moves down one row", category: "SDP", reason: "Enter confirms the entry and advances the selection vertically by default." },
  { question: "Which 'Import' format (4.4.17) is essentially a raw 'Database' file from Microsoft?", options: [".txt", ".csv", ".accdb (MS Access)", ".html"], answer: ".accdb (MS Access)", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel can link directly to Access databases to import relational data." },
  { question: "In 'Security' (4.4.5), the 'Protect Workbook' command is different from 'Protect Sheet' because it prevents:", options: ["Typing in a cell", "Changing the structure (adding/deleting/renaming sheets)", "Changing the font", "Printing"], answer: "Changing the structure (adding/deleting/renaming sheets)", category: "SDP", reason: "Workbook protection targets the 'organization' of the tabs, not the data within them." },
  { question: "To change the 'Margin' settings (4.4.19) visually, you should be in which view?", options: ["Normal View", "Page Layout View", "Outline View", "Draft View"], answer: "Page Layout View", category: "SDP", reason: "Page Layout view shows the physical paper with rulers, making it easiest to adjust margins." },
  { question: "Which 'Subtotal' (4.4.12) option allows you to 'Replace current subtotals'?", options: ["At each change in", "Use function", "Add subtotal to", "The checkbox 'Replace current subtotals'"], answer: "The checkbox 'Replace current subtotals'", category: "SDP", reason: "This allows for re-calculating or changing the aggregate function without having to manually delete old rows." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Chart' (4.4.13) is best for showing 'X Y Coordinates' and data density?", options: ["Pie Chart", "Line Chart", "Scatter (X Y) Chart", "Histogram"], answer: "Scatter (X Y) Chart", category: "SDP", reason: "Scatter charts are designed to show relationships between two sets of numbers on two axes." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Select all non-empty cells' starting from the active cell to the bottom of a list?", options: ["Ctrl + A", "Ctrl + Shift + Down Arrow", "Ctrl + Down Arrow", "Alt + Down Arrow"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + Down Arrow", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Arrow jumps to the edge; adding Shift highlights everything in between." },
  { question: "To start a 'Series' (4.4.9) of numbers that double every step (2, 4, 8...), you use:", options: ["Linear Series", "Growth Series", "Date Series", "AutoFill"], answer: "Growth Series", category: "SDP", reason: "Growth series apply a geometric multiplier to each step." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key 'Closes' the Excel application entirely?", options: ["Ctrl + W", "Ctrl + F4", "Alt + F4", "Ctrl + Q"], answer: "Alt + F4", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt+F4 is the standard Windows command to terminate a running program." },
  { question: "What is 'Audit' (4.4.18) used for in Excel maintenance?", options: ["Deleting files", "Ensuring formula integrity and tracking logic flows", "Increasing RAM", "Cleaning the keyboard"], answer: "Ensuring formula integrity and tracking logic flows", category: "SDP", reason: "Auditing helps spreadsheet designers verify that their calculations are reliable." },
  { question: "Which 'Export' option (4.4.17) creates a file readable by almost any simple text editor?", options: ["Save as CSV (Comma Delimited)", "Save as Web Page", "Save as Binary", "Save as Template"], answer: "Save as CSV (Comma Delimited)", category: "SDP", reason: "CSV is a simple, non-proprietary text format for tabular information." },
  { question: "In 'Page Setting' (4.4.19), what is 'Row and Column Headings' setting under the Sheet tab for?", options: ["Showing them on screen", "Printing the 'A, B, C' and '1, 2, 3' headers on paper", "Deleting headers", "Formatting text"], answer: "Printing the 'A, B, C' and '1, 2, 3' headers on paper", category: "SDP", reason: "Usually, the A/B/C headers don't print; this setting forces them to appear on physical pages." },
  { question: "The 'Goal Seek' (4.4.18) tool is part of which analysis menu?", options: ["Data Validation", "What-If Analysis", "Consolidate", "Subtotal"], answer: "What-If Analysis", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a core simulation tool located under the What-If Analysis button on the Data tab." },
  { question: "Which of the following describes the 'Skeleton' of an HTML document (7.2.3)?", options: ["The images and colors", "The basic structural tags like <html>, <head>, and <body>", "The text content", "The CSS styling"], answer: "The basic structural tags like <html>, <head>, and <body>", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Skeleton' refers to the essential tags that define the document structure, while the 'Flesh' refers to the actual content like text and media." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of a Content Management System (CMS) in web designing (7.1)?", options: ["To compile C++ code", "To allow users to create and manage website content without technical coding knowledge", "To increase internet speed", "To format the hard drive"], answer: "To allow users to create and manage website content without technical coding knowledge", category: "SDP", reason: "A CMS (like WordPress or Joomla) provides a GUI for non-programmers to handle website data." },
  { question: "Which specific HTML tag (7.2.2) is considered an 'Empty Tag' or 'Self-closing tag'?", options: ["<p>", "<html>", "<br>", "<body>"], answer: "<br>", category: "SDP", reason: "Empty tags do not have a separate closing tag (e.g., <br>, <hr>, <img>)." },
  { question: "In the HTML 'Skeleton' (7.2.3), where must the <title> tag be placed?", options: ["Inside the <body> section", "Inside the <head> section", "Before the <html> tag", "After the </body> tag"], answer: "Inside the <head> section", category: "SDP", reason: "The <head> section contains metadata about the document, including the title shown in the browser tab." },
  { question: "Which attribute is used with the anchor tag <a> to specify the destination URL (7.2.3.2)?", options: ["src", "link", "href", "target"], answer: "href", category: "SDP", reason: "href stands for 'hypertext reference', which defines the link's destination." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag is used to create the largest possible heading (7.2.3.1)?", options: ["<h6>", "<head>", "<h1>", "<h0>"], answer: "<h1>", category: "SDP", reason: "HTML provides heading tags from h1 (largest) to h6 (smallest)." },
  { question: "What is the purpose of the 'alt' attribute in the <img> tag (7.2.3.3)?", options: ["To change the image size", "To provide alternative text if the image cannot be displayed", "To add a link to the image", "To rotate the image"], answer: "To provide alternative text if the image cannot be displayed", category: "SDP", reason: "The alt attribute is essential for accessibility and as a fallback if the image path is broken." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag is used to define an 'Ordered List' (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["<ul>", "<list>", "<ol>", "<nl>"], answer: "<ol>", category: "SDP", reason: "<ol> stands for Ordered List, which uses numbers or letters (1, 2, 3...)." },
  { question: "In an HTML table (7.2.3.5), which tag represents an individual 'Data Cell'?", options: ["<tr>", "<th>", "<td>", "<cell>"], answer: "<td>", category: "SDP", reason: "<td> stands for Table Data, while <tr> is Table Row and <th> is Table Header." },
  { question: "Which tag is used to embed another HTML document within the current page (7.2.3.6)?", options: ["<frame>", "<iframe>", "<frameset>", "<window>"], answer: "<iframe>", category: "SDP", reason: "An <iframe> (Inline Frame) allows you to display external content inside a designated area of your page." },
  { question: "What is the correct syntax for a 'Comment' in HTML (7.2.2)?", options: ["// This is a comment", "/* This is a comment */", "<!-- This is a comment -->", "# This is a comment"], answer: "<!-- This is a comment -->", category: "SDP", reason: "HTML comments are ignored by the browser and start with <!-- and end with -->." },
  { question: "Which attribute in a <form> tag (7.2.3.4) specifies where the data should be sent upon submission?", options: ["method", "target", "action", "enctype"], answer: "action", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'action' attribute contains the URL of the server-side script that processes the form data." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag is used to define a multi-line text input field (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["<input type='text'>", "<textarea>", "<textblock>", "<input type='area'>"], answer: "<textarea>", category: "SDP", reason: "<textarea> is a container tag that allows for large blocks of text input, unlike the standard single-line input." },
  { question: "In a table (7.2.3.5), which attribute is used to make a cell span across multiple 'rows'?", options: ["colspan", "rowspan", "span", "merge"], answer: "rowspan", category: "SDP", reason: "rowspan merges cells vertically, while colspan merges them horizontally." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.1) is used to create a thematic break or a horizontal line across the page?", options: ["<br>", "<line>", "<hr>", "<border>"], answer: "<hr>", category: "SDP", reason: "<hr> stands for 'Horizontal Rule'." },
  { question: "Which of the following describes a 'Static' web page (7.1)?", options: ["A page that changes content based on user login", "A page that displays the same content to every user every time", "A page used only for videos", "A page that requires no browser"], answer: "A page that displays the same content to every user every time", category: "SDP", reason: "Static pages are simple HTML files stored on a server, while dynamic pages use databases and CMS." },
  { question: "Which input type (7.2.3.4) is used for a group of options where only 'one' can be selected?", options: ["checkbox", "text", "radio", "button"], answer: "radio", category: "SDP", reason: "Radio buttons are mutually exclusive, meaning only one choice can be active in a named group." },
  { question: "Which tag is used to identify the 'header' cells of a table, which are usually bold and centered (7.2.3.5)?", options: ["<td>", "<th>", "<tr>", "<thead>"], answer: "<th>", category: "SDP", reason: "<th> stands for Table Header." },
  { question: "To create a link that opens in a 'New Tab' (7.2.3.2), which attribute value is used?", options: ["target='_self'", "target='_top'", "target='_blank'", "target='_parent'"], answer: "target='_blank'", category: "SDP", reason: "The _blank value tells the browser to open the linked document in a new window or tab." },
  { question: "What is the result of using the <u> tag (7.2.3.1) around text?", options: ["Text becomes bold", "Text becomes italicized", "Text gets an underline", "Text changes color"], answer: "Text gets an underline", category: "SDP", reason: "<u> stands for Underline." },
  { question: "Which tag defines the 'flesh' or main viewable area of the HTML document (7.2.3)?", options: ["<head>", "<body>", "<html>", "<main>"], answer: "<body>", category: "SDP", reason: "Everything placed inside the <body> tag is rendered visually in the browser window." },
  { question: "Which attribute of the <img> tag (7.2.3.3) defines the width of the image in pixels?", options: ["size", "width", "horizontal", "scale"], answer: "width", category: "SDP", reason: "Width and Height are standard HTML attributes for the img tag." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag is used for creating a 'Numbered' list starting with 1 (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["<ol>", "<ul>", "<li>", "<nl>"], answer: "<ol>", category: "SDP", reason: "<ol> stands for Ordered List." },
  { question: "The <fieldset> tag (7.2.3.4) is primarily used to:", options: ["Delete a form", "Group related elements in a form with a border", "Insert an image", "Create a table"], answer: "Group related elements in a form with a border", category: "SDP", reason: "Fieldsets are used to logically organize form inputs, often used with the <legend> tag." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.1) is used to define a paragraph of text?", options: ["<text>", "<para>", "<p>", "<block>"], answer: "<p>", category: "SDP", reason: "<p> is the standard element for block-level text paragraphs." },
  { question: "In HTML, the 'method' attribute of a form (7.2.3.4) set to 'POST' means:", options: ["Data is visible in the URL", "Data is sent in the body of the HTTP request and is more secure", "Data is deleted", "The form is printed"], answer: "Data is sent in the body of the HTTP request and is more secure", category: "SDP", reason: "POST is used for sensitive data as it doesn't expose values in the browser address bar." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.1) is used to make text 'Bold' with semantic importance?", options: ["<b>", "<strong>", "<bold>", "<em>"], answer: "<strong>", category: "SDP", reason: "While <b> is visual, <strong> is semantic and indicates high importance for screen readers." },
  { question: "Which tag is used to define a single 'item' inside a list (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["<list>", "<item>", "<li>", "<ol>"], answer: "<li>", category: "SDP", reason: "<li> stands for List Item and is used within both <ul> and <ol>." },
  { question: "What does the 'src' attribute of an <img> tag (7.2.3.3) stand for?", options: ["Screen", "Source", "Search", "Size"], answer: "Source", category: "SDP", reason: "It specifies the path/URL to the image file." },
  { question: "To create a link that jumps to a specific 'ID' on the same page (7.2.3.2), the href value should start with:", options: ["@", "#", "$", "/"], answer: "#", category: "SDP", reason: "The hash (#) symbol is used to reference internal anchors/IDs." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.5) defines the entire container for tabular data?", options: ["<grid>", "<table>", "<tab>", "<data>"], answer: "<table>", category: "SDP", reason: "All rows and cells must be nested inside the <table> tag." },
  { question: "What is the result of using the <em> tag (7.2.3.1)?", options: ["Bold text", "Underlined text", "Italicized text (Emphasized)", "Hidden text"], answer: "Italicized text (Emphasized)", category: "SDP", reason: "<em> stands for Emphasis and typically renders as italics." },
  { question: "In a form (7.2.3.4), which tag is used to create a drop-down option?", options: ["<select>", "<list>", "<option>", "<choice>"], answer: "<option>", category: "SDP", reason: "Individual items in a drop-down menu are defined by <option> tags inside a <select> block." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Container Tag' (7.2.2)?", options: ["<br>", "<hr>", "<img>", "<div>"], answer: "<div>", category: "SDP", reason: "Container tags have a starting and ending tag and hold content between them." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.1) identifies the version of HTML being used?", options: ["<html>", "<body>", "<!DOCTYPE>", "<version>"], answer: "<!DOCTYPE>", category: "SDP", reason: "<!DOCTYPE html> is the declaration for HTML5." },
  { question: "In 'Web page Designing' (7.1), which of these is NOT a CMS?", options: ["WordPress", "Joomla", "Adobe Photoshop", "Drupal"], answer: "Adobe Photoshop", category: "SDP", reason: "Photoshop is an image editor; the others are Content Management Systems." },
  { question: "Which attribute is used to group several checkboxes together in a form (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["id", "class", "name", "value"], answer: "name", category: "SDP", reason: "Sharing the same 'name' attribute value treats the inputs as a single data set during submission." },
  { question: "The <legend> tag (7.2.3.4) is used inside which other tag?", options: ["<table>", "<form>", "<fieldset>", "<body>"], answer: "<fieldset>", category: "SDP", reason: "The <legend> provides a caption or title for the <fieldset> group." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.1) is used for the smallest text (e.g. for side comments)?", options: ["<small>", "<h6>", "<sub>", "<sup>"], answer: "<h6>", "answer_note": "Actually <small> is for small print, but <h6> is the smallest heading level.", category: "SDP", reason: "Heading priority goes from h1 to h6." },
  { question: "What is the purpose of the <sub> tag (7.2.3.1)?", options: ["Superior text", "Subscript text (like H2O)", "Subject text", "Subtitle"], answer: "Subscript text (like H2O)", category: "SDP", reason: "<sub> lowers the text baseline." },
  { question: "What is the purpose of the <sup> tag (7.2.3.1)?", options: ["Superscript text (like X2)", "Super text", "Supplement", "Summary"], answer: "Superscript text (like X2)", category: "SDP", reason: "<sup> raises the text baseline." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag is used to create a list with 'Bullets' (7.2.3.4)?", options: ["<ol>", "<ul>", "<bl>", "<list>"], answer: "<ul>", category: "SDP", reason: "<ul> stands for Unordered List." },
  { question: "In a table (7.2.3.5), what is the correct sequence of tags to create a single row with two cells?", options: ["<table><tr><td></td><td></td></tr></table>", "<table><td><tr></tr><tr></tr></table>", "<tr><td><td></table>", "<table><tr><td></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr></table>"], answer: "<table><tr><td></td><td></td></tr></table>", category: "SDP", reason: "The hierarchy is Table -> Row -> Data cell." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.1) is used to display text exactly as it is typed, including multiple spaces?", options: ["<p>", "<div>", "<pre>", "<text>"], answer: "<pre>", category: "SDP", reason: "<pre> stands for Preformatted text." },
  { question: "What is 'WordPress' in the context of the syllabus (7.1)?", options: ["An internet browser", "A popular CMS", "A type of HTML tag", "A hardware processor"], answer: "A popular CMS", category: "SDP", reason: "WordPress is the world's most widely used Content Management System." },
  { question: "Which attribute in the <img> tag (7.2.3.3) provides a brief description for a tooltip on hover?", options: ["alt", "title", "name", "desc"], answer: "title", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'title' attribute shows extra info when the mouse hovers over an element." },
  { question: "Which input type (7.2.3.4) allows a user to select one or more choices from a list?", options: ["radio", "checkbox", "text", "submit"], answer: "checkbox", category: "SDP", reason: "Checkboxes allow for non-exclusive multi-selection." },
  { question: "In HTML 'Skeleton' (7.2.3), the <meta> tags are always placed inside which section?", options: ["<html>", "<body>", "<head>", "<footer>"], answer: "<head>", category: "SDP", reason: "Metadata is document information kept in the head." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.6) was traditionally used to split the entire browser window into separate panels?", options: ["<iframe>", "<frameset>", "<split>", "<panel>"], answer: "<frameset>", category: "SDP", reason: "While largely legacy now, <frameset> was the original way to create multi-panel layouts." },
  { question: "Which part of the URL (7.1 context) specifies the protocol for accessing a web page?", options: ["www", "http://", "index.html", ".com"], answer: "http://", category: "SDP", reason: "HyperText Transfer Protocol is the primary protocol of the web." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act 2074 (8.1), who is responsible for the collection and management of local statistics and records at the ward level?", options: ["District Coordination Committee", "Ward Committee", "Pradesh Government", "Federal Government"], answer: "Ward Committee", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act mandates Ward Committees to manage local data, which includes the digitization of vital registration and local statistics." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 (8.2), what is the 'probation period' for a female employee appointed to a permanent post?", options: ["6 months", "1 year", "1.5 years", "2 years"], answer: "6 months", category: "SDP", reason: "Similar to the Federal Act, the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Act 2079 provides a 6-month probation for females and 1 year for males." },
  { question: "What is the maximum age limit for a male candidate to apply for the post of Computer Operator under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079?", options: ["30 years", "35 years", "40 years", "45 years"], answer: "35 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act specifies 35 years for males and 40 years for females and candidates with disabilities." },
  { question: "According to the Electronic Transaction Regulation 2064 (8.4), what is the prescribed fee for an application to obtain a license to work as a Certification Authority (CA)?", options: ["Rs. 5,000", "Rs. 25,000", "Rs. 50,000", "Rs. 100,000"], answer: "Rs. 50,000", category: "SDP", reason: "The 2064 Regulation sets the application fee for a CA license at fifty thousand rupees." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is specifically developed and owned by Microsoft (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Google Meet", "Microsoft Teams", "Viber"], answer: "Microsoft Teams", category: "SDP", reason: "Teams is Microsoft's proprietary communication platform integrated into the Office 365 suite." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a major 'Disadvantage' of Social Networking as per syllabus section 8.7?", options: ["Real-time communication", "Information overload and privacy risks", "Global connectivity", "Low-cost marketing"], answer: "Information overload and privacy risks", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media exposes users to potential data breaches, cyberbullying, and the spread of misinformation." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act 2074, which function falls under the 'IT-related' powers of a Municipality (Palika)?", options: ["Formulating national cyber laws", "Establishment and operation of local level ICT centers", "Issuing passports", "Managing international roaming"], answer: "Establishment and operation of local level ICT centers", category: "SDP", reason: "Palikas have the power to manage local digital infrastructure and e-governance services." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, which 'Service' category does a Computer Operator typically belong to?", options: ["Pradesh Administrative Service", "Pradesh Engineering Service", "Pradesh Miscellaneous Service (Bibidh)", "Pradesh Health Service"], answer: "Pradesh Miscellaneous Service (Bibidh)", category: "SDP", reason: "Computer-related posts like Computer Operator are categorized under the Miscellaneous (Bibidh) service group." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool has a standard '40-minute limit' for group meetings in its free version (8.6)?", options: ["Google Meet", "Zoom", "Webex", "Microsoft Teams"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Zoom's basic free plan traditionally imposes a 40-minute cap on group sessions." },
  { question: "Under the Electronic Transaction Regulation 2064, who has the authority to audit a Certification Authority?", options: ["A private auditor", "The Controller or an auditor designated by the Controller", "The Nepal Police", "Any Computer Operator"], answer: "The Controller or an auditor designated by the Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The OCCA (Controller) is legally mandated to perform technical audits of licensed CAs." },
  { question: "Which messaging platform is widely known for introducing 'End-to-End Encryption' by default for all chats (8.6)?", options: ["Twitter", "YouTube", "WhatsApp", "Zoom"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "WhatsApp uses the Signal protocol to ensure only the sender and receiver can read the messages." },
  { question: "What is 'Retirement Age' for a civil servant in Sudurpashchim Pradesh as per the 2079 Act?", options: ["58 years", "60 years", "62 years", "65 years"], answer: "60 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The Sudurpashchim Pradesh Act 2079 followed the trend of increasing the retirement age to 60." },
  { question: "As per the Government Website Directive 2078 (8.5), every government website must have a dedicated section for ______.", options: ["Gaming", "Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", "Private ads", "Music"], answer: "Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", category: "SDP", reason: "To comply with the Right to Information, official websites must clearly display the contact details of the Information Officer." },
  { question: "Which feature of 'Google Meet' allows users to present their screen during a video call?", options: ["Mute", "Present Now", "End Call", "Hand Raise"], answer: "Present Now", category: "SDP", reason: "'Present Now' is the specific button used to share a tab, window, or entire screen in Google Meet." },
  { question: "In the context of the Electronic Transaction Act 2063, 'Digital Signature' is achieved through:", options: ["A scanned photo of a signature", "Asymmetric Cryptosystem and Hash function", "A login password", "A physical stamp"], answer: "Asymmetric Cryptosystem and Hash function", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act legally defines a digital signature as a cryptographic method ensuring integrity and authenticity." },
  { question: "What is the primary 'Advantage' of Social Networking for a government office (8.7)?", options: ["Generating ad revenue", "Rapid dissemination of information and citizen engagement", "Storing large databases", "Printing documents"], answer: "Rapid dissemination of information and citizen engagement", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media allows governments to communicate directly and instantly with the public." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Micro-blogging' platform mentioned in the syllabus (8.6)?", options: ["Facebook", "YouTube", "Twitter (X)", "Viber"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter is defined by its short character limit, making it the primary example of micro-blogging." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072 (8.3), which institution is envisioned to manage the 'Government Integrated Data Center' (GIDC)?", options: ["Nepal Telecom", "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", "Department of IT", "Ministry of Home Affairs"], answer: "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC is the operational body under MoCIT responsible for the central government data infrastructure." },
  { question: "Which section of the Local Government Operation Act 2074 discusses the powers and functions of Rural Municipalities and Municipalities?", options: ["Section 3", "Section 11", "Section 50", "Section 100"], answer: "Section 11", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 11 details the 22 broad powers/functions of local levels, including IT development." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, a civil servant is 'suspended' automatically if they are:", options: ["Late for work", "Taken into judicial custody for a criminal offense", "On leave", "Using a computer"], answer: "Taken into judicial custody for a criminal offense", category: "SDP", reason: "Legal detention triggers an automatic suspension from civil service duties until the case is resolved." },
  { question: "Which platform is primarily used for 'video sharing' and hosting tutorials (8.6)?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Viber", "YouTube", "Twitter"], answer: "YouTube", category: "SDP", reason: "YouTube is a dedicated video repository and social network owned by Google." },
  { question: "The Electronic Transaction Regulation 2064 states that a 'Digital Signature Certificate' remains valid for:", options: ["1 year", "2 years", "5 years", "Forever"], answer: "2 years", category: "SDP", reason: "As per the rules, the standard validity period for a DSC issued by a CA is two years." },
  { question: "What does the 'B' key do during a running PowerPoint Slide Show (8.6 context)?", options: ["Bolds the text", "Blacks out the screen", "Goes back to previous slide", "Starts a new slide"], answer: "Blacks out the screen", category: "SDP", reason: "Pressing 'B' hides the current slide with a black screen so the audience focuses on the speaker." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is integrated directly into Gmail (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Google Meet", "Viber", "Skype"], answer: "Google Meet", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Meet is the native conferencing solution for the Google Workspace ecosystem." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Directive 2078, websites must be compatible with which accessibility standard?", options: ["ISO 9001", "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", "IEEE 802.11", "ASCII"], answer: "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", category: "SDP", reason: "To ensure inclusivity, government sites must be usable by persons with disabilities as per W3C standards." },
  { question: "Which social networking disadvantage involves 'fake news' or 'rumors' (8.7)?", options: ["Malware", "Phishing", "Propagation of Misinformation", "Cyberstalking"], answer: "Propagation of Misinformation", category: "SDP", reason: "Social networks allow unverified information to spread rapidly among large audiences." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, which authority conducts the competitive exams for the post of Computer Operator?", options: ["Federal Public Service Commission", "Sudurpashchim Pradesh Public Service Commission", "DoIT", "Ministry of IT"], answer: "Sudurpashchim Pradesh Public Service Commission", category: "SDP", reason: "Provincial recruitment is handled by the respective Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Hacking' into a 'Protected System' as per ETA 2063?", options: ["Same as regular hacking", "Higher punishment including up to 9 years imprisonment", "No punishment", "Only Rs. 500 fine"], answer: "Higher punishment including up to 9 years imprisonment", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 43 allows the government to declare systems as 'Protected', and crimes against them carry heavier penalties." },
  { question: "Which application is a 'Community Messaging' app widely used in Nepal for official groups (8.6)?", options: ["YouTube", "Viber", "Netflix", "BIOS"], answer: "Viber", category: "SDP", reason: "Viber is extremely popular in Nepal for both personal and organizational group chats." },
  { question: "Under ICT Policy 2072, what is the goal for broadband speed for households (8.3)?", options: ["128 kbps", "Minimum 512 kbps / 2 Mbps", "10 Gbps", "No specific goal"], answer: "Minimum 512 kbps / 2 Mbps", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy set baseline targets for internet speed to ensure meaningful digital access." },
  { question: "Which term describes the 'socially acceptable' behavior on social media platforms?", options: ["Protocol", "Netiquette", "Firewall", "Encryption"], answer: "Netiquette", category: "SDP", reason: "Netiquette (Network Etiquette) refers to the unofficial rules of polite and correct conduct online." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, what is the mandatory domain extension for all government offices?", options: [".gov.np", ".org.np", ".com.np", ".net.np"], answer: ".gov.np", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive strictly mandates the use of the .gov.np TLD to verify official status." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, 'Performance Evaluation' is carried out for what main purpose?", options: ["To check if the person is alive", "For promotion and career development", "To calculate overtime pay", "To change the job description"], answer: "For promotion and career development", category: "SDP", reason: "Performance scores are a critical weightage factor in the promotion system of civil servants." },
  { question: "Which video tool allows for 'Screen Recording' and is built into Windows 10/11 (8.6 context)?", options: ["Zoom", "Google Meet", "Xbox Game Bar", "Viber"], answer: "Xbox Game Bar", category: "SDP", reason: "Windows includes a native recording tool (Win+G) which is relevant for digital documentation." },
  { question: "What is the result of applying 'Salt' to a password in cyber security (Syllabus 9 intersection, applied here)?", options: ["It deletes the password", "It adds random data to a password before hashing to prevent rainbow table attacks", "It makes the password taste better", "It is only for Excel"], answer: "It adds random data to a password before hashing to prevent rainbow table attacks", category: "SDP", reason: "Salting is a security best practice for storing user credentials securely in databases." },
  { question: "Which section of the ETA 2063 provides for the 'IT Tribunal'?", options: ["Section 10", "Section 30", "Section 60", "Section 80"], answer: "Section 60", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 60 mandates the formation of a specialized court to hear cyber offences." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Messaging' app owned by Meta (8.6)?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Viber", "Twitter", "Zoom"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "Meta (formerly Facebook) owns Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy 2072 targets to generate what percentage of national electricity from 'Green ICT'?", options: ["10%", "50%", "No specific percentage (focus is on energy efficiency)", "100%"], answer: "No specific percentage (focus is on energy efficiency)", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy promotes environmental sustainability rather than setting power generation targets." },
  { question: "Under the Local Government Operation Act 2074, a 'Palika' can formulate which type of laws?", options: ["National Security Laws", "Acts, Regulations, and Directives within its 22 constitutional powers", "International Treaties", "Criminal Codes"], answer: "Acts, Regulations, and Directives within its 22 constitutional powers", category: "SDP", reason: "Local levels have legislative power within the schedule 8 of the constitution." },
  { question: "Which social networking site is best for 'Real-time Citizen Engagement' during an emergency?", options: ["LinkedIn", "Twitter (X)", "Pinterest", "Flickr"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter's speed and feed structure make it the premier tool for crisis communication." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, who owns the 'Content' of a government website?", options: ["The Private Developer", "The hosting company", "The respective Government Body (Organization)", "Google"], answer: "The respective Government Body (Organization)", category: "SDP", reason: "Data sovereignty dictates that the state entity is the legal owner of its digital data." },
  { question: "What happens if a civil servant in Sudurpashchim Pradesh is caught 'Leaking confidential IT data'?", options: ["They get a bonus", "They face disciplinary action under the Civil Service Act and criminal charges under ETA 2063", "Nothing", "They are moved to a different room"], answer: "They face disciplinary action under the Civil Service Act and criminal charges under ETA 2063", category: "SDP", reason: "Leaking data violates both professional code of conduct and criminal cyber laws." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool allows 'Live Streaming' directly to YouTube (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "WhatsApp", "Viber", "Standard Phone Call"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Paid versions of Zoom provide a direct bridge to stream meetings to YouTube and Facebook Live." },
  { question: "What is the full form of 'GIDC' in Nepal's institutional framework?", options: ["General Information Data Center", "Government Integrated Data Center", "Global Integrated Data Command", "Government Internet Distribution Center"], answer: "Government Integrated Data Center", category: "SDP", reason: "GIDC is the central server hub for all government digital operations." },
  { question: "Which 'Advantage' of social networking relates to 'Education' (8.7)?", options: ["Cyberstalking", "Peer-to-peer learning and information sharing", "Privacy loss", "Ad spending"], answer: "Peer-to-peer learning and information sharing", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media facilitates groups and forums where educational materials are shared." },
  { question: "In the ETA Regulation 2064, which 'Officer' handles the application for a Digital Signature license?", options: ["The Police", "The Controller", "The Webmaster", "The Minister"], answer: "The Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The Controller of Certification Authority (CCA) is the legal licensing authority." },
  { question: "Which 'Social Media' platform is owned by Google (8.6)?", options: ["Facebook", "Twitter", "YouTube", "Instagram"], answer: "YouTube", category: "SDP", reason: "Google acquired YouTube in 2006." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, can a civil servant participate in 'Politics'?", options: ["Yes, they can", "No, it is strictly prohibited for permanent civil servants", "Only if they are computer operators", "Only during holidays"], answer: "No, it is strictly prohibited for permanent civil servants", category: "SDP", reason: "Political neutrality is a core pillar of civil service ethics in Nepal." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Digital Signature Theft' under ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 1,000 fine", "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", "Warning only", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Misusing or stealing someone's digital identity is a criminal offense under Section 51." },
  { question: "Which institution handles the 'monitoring' of all .gov.np websites for uptime (8.5 context)?", options: ["DoIT", "NITC", "Ministry of Home Affairs", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "NITC", category: "SDP", reason: "As the primary host (GIDC), NITC is responsible for the technical availability of government sites." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act 2074, which of the following is a function of the Rural Municipality (Gaunpalika) regarding technology?", options: ["Launching national satellites", "Management of local level statistics and data", "Issuing international roaming licenses", "Regulating nationwide television"], answer: "Management of local level statistics and data", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 11 of the Act empowers local levels to manage their own local statistics, including digitization of vital registration." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, what is the mandatory retirement age for a civil servant?", options: ["58 years", "60 years", "62 years", "65 years"], answer: "60 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The 2079 Act for Sudurpashchim Pradesh followed the standard of increasing the retirement age to 60 years." },
  { question: "What is the primary objective of the ICT Policy 2072?", options: ["To ban all analog devices", "To build an inclusive information society for socio-economic development", "To make the internet only available in cities", "To increase the cost of data"], answer: "To build an inclusive information society for socio-economic development", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy focuses on using ICT as a tool for poverty reduction and achieving national development goals." },
  { question: "Which section of the Electronic Transaction Act (ETA) 2063 deals with the 'Offences Relating to Computer'?", options: ["Chapter 2", "Chapter 5", "Chapter 9", "Chapter 12"], answer: "Chapter 9", category: "SDP", reason: "Chapter 9 of the ETA 2063 contains the legal provisions and penalties for hacking, data tampering, and other cybercrimes." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Development and Management Directive 2078, which of the following is mandatory for a government website?", options: ["Commercial advertisements", "Official logo of the organization", "Link to private news portals", "Personal social media of staff"], answer: "Official logo of the organization", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive requires uniformity in branding, including the mandatory display of the national flag and the specific organization's logo." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a popular 'Micro-blogging' social media platform (8.6)?", options: ["YouTube", "Facebook", "Twitter (X)", "Viber"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter is defined by its character limit and real-time short-form updates, known as micro-blogging." },
  { question: "What is a major 'Disadvantage' of Social Networking as per syllabus section 8.7?", options: ["Easy connectivity", "Risk of data theft and identity fraud", "Low cost communication", "Real-time feedback"], answer: "Risk of data theft and identity fraud", category: "SDP", reason: "While beneficial for communication, social networks expose users to cybersecurity risks and privacy breaches." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, which 'Service' group does a Computer Operator belong to?", options: ["Engineering Service", "Administration Service", "Miscellaneous (Bibidh) Service", "Education Service"], answer: "Miscellaneous (Bibidh) Service", category: "SDP", reason: "Computer Operators are categorized under the Miscellaneous (Bibidh) service group in both federal and provincial acts." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is owned and developed by Google (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Microsoft Teams", "Google Meet", "Viber"], answer: "Google Meet", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Meet is the proprietary enterprise-grade video meeting solution from Google." },
  { question: "Under the Electronic Transaction Regulation 2064, who is the 'Controller'?", options: ["A police inspector", "The individual appointed by the government to regulate Certification Authorities", "The IT manager of a bank", "The webmaster of a ministry"], answer: "The individual appointed by the government to regulate Certification Authorities", category: "SDP", reason: "The OCCA (Controller) is the regulatory body for digital signatures and CAs in Nepal." },
  { question: "As per the Website Directive 2078, every government website must contain a link to ______.", options: ["The Citizen Charter (Nagarik Bada Patra)", "Facebook of the Minister", "Local shops", "Foreign news"], answer: "The Citizen Charter (Nagarik Bada Patra)", category: "SDP", reason: "To ensure transparency and public service accountability, the digital Citizen Charter is a mandatory inclusion." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Vulnerability' of using social media for government offices (8.7)?", options: ["Transparency", "Spread of rumors and misinformation", "Reduced paper usage", "Public engagement"], answer: "Spread of rumors and misinformation", category: "SDP", reason: "False information can spread quickly on social platforms, creating challenges for official government messaging." },
  { question: "What is the 'probation period' for a male employee appointed to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service?", options: ["6 months", "1 year", "2 years", "None"], answer: "1 year", category: "SDP", reason: "Standard civil service laws in Nepal provide a 1-year probation for males and 6 months for females." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, which of the following is a 'Target' for the year 2020?", options: ["To reach 90% broadband population coverage", "To ban all 2G phones", "To make Nepal a fully automated island", "To shut down all cyber cafes"], answer: "To reach 90% broadband population coverage", category: "SDP", reason: "The 2072 policy set ambitious infrastructure goals for nationwide broadband expansion." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is famous for its 'Breakout Rooms' feature to split participants into small groups (8.6)?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Viber", "Zoom", "Facebook"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Zoom popularized the 'Breakout Rooms' feature for workshops and educational sessions." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, if a person gains 'unauthorized access' to a system, they are liable for:", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine only", "Up to Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Lifetime ban from internet", "Rs. 1,000 fine"], answer: "Up to Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 45 of the Act provides strict penalties for hacking and unauthorized entry into computer systems." },
  { question: "The Government Website Directive 2078 mandates that all official websites must be hosted at:", options: ["Amazon Cloud", "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", "Any private data center", "Local hard drive"], answer: "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", category: "SDP", reason: "Centralized hosting at GIDC ensures national data security and standardized management." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Social Networking' site used primarily for professional career building (8.6)?", options: ["TikTok", "Flickr", "LinkedIn", "Viber"], answer: "LinkedIn", category: "SDP", reason: "LinkedIn is the world's largest professional network for careers and organizational networking." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act 2074, vital registration (Birth, Death, etc.) must be integrated with ______.", options: ["A physical book only", "The National ID / IT infrastructure", "A private server", "The Post Office"], answer: "The National ID / IT infrastructure", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act encourages the digitization of civil registration to integrate with national-level data systems." },
  { question: "Which messaging application is widely used in Nepal for creating 'Communities' and official notification groups (8.6)?", options: ["YouTube", "Viber", "Netflix", "BIOS"], answer: "Viber", category: "SDP", reason: "Viber is particularly popular in Nepal for both personal and organizational group communication." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service, what is the 'Study Leave' limit for the entire service period?", options: ["1 year", "3 years", "5 years", "Unlimited"], answer: "3 years", category: "SDP", reason: "Civil servants are generally entitled to a maximum of 3 years of study leave throughout their tenure." },
  { question: "What does 'S' in 'HTTPS' stand for in a browser's URL (8.6 context)?", options: ["System", "Standard", "Secure", "Selection"], answer: "Secure", category: "SDP", reason: "HTTPS indicates that the communication is encrypted using SSL/TLS protocols." },
  { question: "Under the ETA Regulation 2064, how many members are in the Information Technology Tribunal?", options: ["1 member", "2 members", "3 members", "5 members"], answer: "3 members", category: "SDP", reason: "The Tribunal consists of a Law Member, IT Member, and Commerce Member." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government sites must follow which 'Web Accessibility' standard?", options: ["ISO 9001", "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", "IEEE 802.11", "HTML 1.0"], answer: "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", category: "SDP", reason: "This ensures that government information is accessible to persons with disabilities." },
  { question: "Which video tool is 'unlimited' for one-on-one calls in its basic version (8.6)?", options: ["Google Meet", "Zoom", "WhatsApp", "Microsoft Teams"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "WhatsApp provides free, unlimited calling for users, unlike enterprise tools that may have time limits for groups." },
  { question: "What is 'Phishing' in the context of social networking (8.7)?", options: ["Fishing in a lake", "Deceptive messages designed to steal login or financial information", "Watching videos", "Updating the status"], answer: "Deceptive messages designed to steal login or financial information", category: "SDP", reason: "Phishing is a major security disadvantage where attackers pose as legitimate entities to trick users." },
  { question: "The 'E-Governance Master Plan' (EGMP) in Nepal was a precursor to which policy?", options: ["ETA 2063", "ICT Policy 2072", "Local Govt Act", "Civil Service Act"], answer: "ICT Policy 2072", category: "SDP", reason: "The ICT Policy 2072 incorporated the vision and strategies laid out in earlier e-governance plans." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, which body conducts the recruitment exams?", options: ["Federal Public Service Commission", "Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog (Pradesh Public Service Commission)", "Ministry of IT", "DoIT"], answer: "Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog (Pradesh Public Service Commission)", category: "SDP", reason: "Provincial recruitment is the constitutional and legal mandate of the respective Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog." },
  { question: "Which of the following describes 'Two-Factor Authentication' (2FA) for social media security (8.7)?", options: ["Having two accounts", "Using both a password and a second code from a phone to log in", "Sharing a password with a friend", "Using two different browsers"], answer: "Using both a password and a second code from a phone to log in", category: "SDP", reason: "2FA significantly increases account security by requiring two different verification factors." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government websites must be available in which two languages?", options: ["Nepali and Hindi", "Nepali and English", "English and Chinese", "Nepali and Sanskrit"], answer: "Nepali and English", category: "SDP", reason: "To ensure local and international transparency, dual language support is required." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Digital Signature Theft' under ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 1,000 fine", "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", "Warning only", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Misusing or stealing someone's digital identity is a criminal offense under Section 51." },
  { question: "Which social networking site is owned by 'Meta'?", options: ["Twitter", "Viber", "Facebook", "Google"], answer: "Facebook", category: "SDP", reason: "Meta Platforms, Inc. is the parent company of Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp." },
  { question: "Under the Local Government Operation Act 2074, a 'Palika' is responsible for providing which 'Digital' service?", options: ["Free international calling", "Digital vital registration (Birth, Death, Marriage)", "Global positioning system", "None of these"], answer: "Digital vital registration (Birth, Death, Marriage)", category: "SDP", reason: "Managing civil registration is a core constitutional power and function of local levels." },
  { question: "What is 'Netiquette' on social networks (8.7)?", options: ["A type of network cable", "The code of conduct for polite and appropriate online behavior", "A computer virus", "A type of internet speed"], answer: "The code of conduct for polite and appropriate online behavior", category: "SDP", reason: "Netiquette helps maintain professional and respectful interactions on social platforms." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is 'Digital Nepal'?", options: ["A new computer brand", "A strategic framework for national digital transformation", "A type of internet browser", "A mobile game"], answer: "A strategic framework for national digital transformation", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital Nepal is the flagship initiative to digitize economy, health, agriculture, and more." },
  { question: "Which video tool allows for up to 100 participants for free but with a time limit (8.6)?", options: ["Viber", "WhatsApp", "Zoom", "Standard SMS"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Zoom's basic free plan has a 100-participant capacity with a 40-minute duration limit." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, a Computer Operator's primary responsibility in maintenance is (8.2 context):", options: ["Fixing power lines", "Ensuring data security and smooth operation of office IT systems", "Cleaning the floor", "Selling office equipment"], answer: "Ensuring data security and smooth operation of office IT systems", category: "SDP", reason: "Computer Operators manage the digital environment and hardware health of their respective offices." },
  { question: "What is 'Spamming' in social networking (8.7)?", options: ["Deleting old posts", "Sending unsolicited and repeated commercial or annoying messages", "Formatting a disk", "Changing a profile picture"], answer: "Sending unsolicited and repeated commercial or annoying messages", category: "SDP", reason: "Spamming is a significant disadvantage as it clutters communication and can hide malicious links." },
  { question: "The Electronic Transaction Act 2063 classifies 'Cybercrime' as a ______ offence.", options: ["Civil", "Criminal", "Administrative", "None"], answer: "Criminal", category: "SDP", reason: "Acts defined under ETA 2063 are subject to police investigation and trial in an IT Tribunal." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Pro' of using social media for a government agency (8.7)?", options: ["Public rumors", "Direct, two-way interaction with citizens", "Privacy risks", "High costs"], answer: "Direct, two-way interaction with citizens", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media bridges the gap between officials and the public, improving feedback loops." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, who owns the 'Content' of the website?", options: ["The private designer", "The hosting company", "The respective Government Organization", "The Internet"], answer: "The respective Government Organization", category: "SDP", reason: "Data sovereignty ensures that the state entity is the legal owner of its information and data." },
  { question: "In 'Zoom', what is the 'Mute All' feature used for (8.6)?", options: ["To end the meeting", "To silence all participants' microphones at once to avoid background noise", "To delete the participants", "To hide the screen"], answer: "To silence all participants' microphones at once to avoid background noise", category: "SDP", reason: "This is an essential administrative tool for maintaining order during large virtual meetings." },
  { question: "Under the ETA Regulation 2064, if a Certification Authority violates its license, the Controller can:", options: ["Promote them", "Suspend or Revoke their license", "Double their salary", "Nothing"], answer: "Suspend or Revoke their license", category: "SDP", reason: "Regulatory bodies have the legal power to enforce compliance and security standards." },
  { question: "Which social networking site is best known for 'Professional Networking'?", options: ["Pinterest", "LinkedIn", "TikTok", "Flickr"], answer: "LinkedIn", category: "SDP", reason: "LinkedIn is tailored for professional branding, networking, and recruitment." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, a permanent civil servant is entitled to 'Casual Leave' (Pariwarik/Parva Vida) of how many days per year?", options: ["6 days", "12 days", "15 days", "30 days"], answer: "12 days", category: "SDP", reason: "Civil service rules in Nepal typically allocate 12 days of casual and festival leave annually." },
  { question: "What does '.gov.np' domain represent (8.5)?", options: ["Government of Nepal", "Global Organization of Nepal", "General Office of Nepal", "Government of Netherlands"], answer: "Government of Nepal", category: "SDP", reason: ".np is the country code for Nepal, and .gov is the restricted second-level domain for government." },
  { question: "Which tool would you use to 'Share your screen' in Microsoft Teams (8.6)?", options: ["Mute", "Share Content", "Raise Hand", "End Call"], answer: "Share Content", category: "SDP", reason: "'Share Content' is the UI command to display your desktop to other participants in Teams." },
  { question: "What is 'Cyberbullying' as a disadvantage of social media (8.7)?", options: ["Helping people online", "Using electronic communication to harass or intimidate a person", "Updating software", "Building a network"], answer: "Using electronic communication to harass or intimidate a person", category: "SDP", reason: "Social platforms can unfortunately be misused to bully or shame individuals." },
  { question: "In the ICT Policy 2072, 'G-Cloud' refers to:", options: ["Gaming Cloud", "Government Cloud for centralized infrastructure", "Green Cloud", "Global Cloud"], answer: "Government Cloud for centralized infrastructure", category: "SDP", reason: "G-Cloud is designed to share storage and computing power among various government departments." },
  { question: "Which section of the ETA 2063 provides legal validity to 'Electronic Records'?", options: ["Section 3", "Section 10", "Section 15", "Section 20"], answer: "Section 3", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 3 explicitly states that electronic records have the same legal standing as paper ones." },
  { question: "According to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 (8.2), what is the mandatory age of retirement for a civil servant?", options: ["58 years", "60 years", "62 years", "65 years"], answer: "60 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The provincial act established 60 years as the retirement age, aligning with recent changes in the civil service structure." },
  { question: "In HTML (7.2.3.5), which attribute is used to make a table cell span across multiple columns?", options: ["rowspan", "colspan", "width", "span"], answer: "colspan", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'colspan' attribute defines how many columns a single <td> or <th> cell should occupy horizontally." },
  { question: "Which database object (5.3.6) is specifically designed to provide a professional, printable summary of data?", options: ["Table", "Form", "Query", "Report"], answer: "Report", category: "SDP", reason: "Reports summarize and format table/query data specifically for printing or digital presentation." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut key to start a 'Slide Show' in PowerPoint from the current selected slide (6.4)?", options: ["F5", "Shift + F5", "Ctrl + F5", "Alt + F5"], answer: "Shift + F5", category: "SDP", reason: "F5 starts from the beginning; Shift + F5 is the standard shortcut to launch the show from the active slide." },
  { question: "Under the Electronic Transaction Act 2063 (8.4), a 'Subscriber' is legally defined as a person who:", options: ["Hacks a system", "Is issued a Digital Signature Certificate", "Repairs computers", "Works at the Ministry"], answer: "Is issued a Digital Signature Certificate", category: "SDP", reason: "The ETA defines a subscriber as the legitimate holder of the digital keys listed in a certificate." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.2) is an 'Empty Tag' that does not require a separate closing tag?", options: ["<p>", "<b>", "<img>", "<html>"], answer: "<img>", category: "SDP", reason: "Tags like <img>, <br>, and <hr> are empty elements that do not contain text content inside them." },
  { question: "Which data type in MS Access (5.3.1) should be used for a field that will only contain 'True' or 'False' values?", options: ["Number", "Short Text", "Yes/No", "OLE Object"], answer: "Yes/No", category: "SDP", reason: "The Yes/No (Boolean) data type is optimized for dual-state logical data." },
  { question: "What is the function of the 'Slide Sorter' view in PowerPoint (6.4)?", options: ["To edit individual text", "To view all slides as thumbnails for easy reordering", "To add animations", "To check spelling"], answer: "To view all slides as thumbnails for easy reordering", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Sorter provides a grid overview of the entire deck, making logical organization easy." },
  { question: "The Local Government Operation Act 2074 (8.1) empowers municipalities to manage which 'digital' records?", options: ["Vital Registration (Birth, Death, etc.)", "International Passports", "National Citizenship IDs", "Stock market trading"], answer: "Vital Registration (Birth, Death, etc.)", category: "SDP", reason: "Managing and digitizing vital registration and local statistics is a core function of local governments under the 2074 Act." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.4) is used to create a single-line input field for a user's name?", options: ["<text>", "<textarea>", "<input type='text'>", "<textfield>"], answer: "<input type='text'>", category: "SDP", reason: "This is the standard form tag for basic text entry strings." },
  { question: "In a database, what is 'Referential Integrity' (5.2)?", options: ["The speed of the database", "Ensuring consistency between related tables so orphaned records are not created", "Hiding data from users", "Formatting a table"], answer: "Ensuring consistency between related tables so orphaned records are not created", category: "SDP", reason: "Referential integrity ensures that a foreign key must always point to a valid primary key." },
  { question: "Which PowerPoint feature (6.3) allows you to set a universal layout, font, and logo for every slide in the presentation?", options: ["Design Theme", "Slide Master", "Animation Pane", "Transition"], answer: "Slide Master", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Master is the top-level template that dictates the global design of all slides in the deck." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for unauthorized access to a computer system (Hacking) under ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Warning only", "No penalty"], answer: "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 45 of the ETA 2063 defines these specific punishments for hacking and data tampering." },
  { question: "Which specific HTML tag (7.2.3.6) allows one webpage to be displayed inside another webpage?", options: ["<link>", "<embed>", "<iframe>", "<meta>"], answer: "<iframe>", category: "SDP", reason: "An <iframe> (Inline Frame) acts as a window to display another HTML document within the current one." },
  { question: "Which database object (5.3.6) is primarily used to provide an interface for data entry and navigation for end-users?", options: ["Table", "Form", "Query", "Report"], answer: "Form", category: "SDP", reason: "Forms provide a structured screen layout to make viewing and entering table data more intuitive." },
  { question: "Which specific Animation (6.5) category is used to make an object 'disappear' from the slide during a show?", options: ["Entrance", "Emphasis", "Exit", "Motion Path"], answer: "Exit", category: "SDP", reason: "Exit animations control the departure of objects from the viewable slide area." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Directive 2078 (8.5), official domains must exclusively use which suffix?", options: [".com.np", ".org.np", ".gov.np", ".net.np"], answer: ".gov.np", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive mandates .gov.np to ensure citizens can identify official government portals easily." },
  { question: "Which attribute in the <a> tag (7.2.3.2) specifies where the linked document should open (e.g., in a new tab)?", options: ["href", "src", "target", "path"], answer: "target", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'target' attribute (e.g., target='_blank') defines the browsing context for the link." },
  { question: "What is an 'Attribute' in a database table (5.2)?", options: ["A row", "A column / field", "A password", "A software name"], answer: "A column / field", category: "SDP", reason: "Attributes are the categories of information stored for every record in a table." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool (8.6) is a native Microsoft product integrated into the Office suite?", options: ["Zoom", "Google Meet", "Viber", "Microsoft Teams"], answer: "Microsoft Teams", category: "SDP", reason: "Teams is Microsoft's specialized communication platform for meetings and collaboration." },
  { question: "What is 'CMS' in web designing (7.1)?", options: ["Central Management Software", "Content Management System", "Cloud Main System", "Computer Media Service"], answer: "Content Management System", category: "SDP", reason: "A CMS is software used to create and manage website content without manual HTML coding." },
  { question: "In a database, which view is used to view, add, and delete actual records in a grid format (5.3.5)?", options: ["Design View", "Datasheet View", "Layout View", "Pivot View"], answer: "Datasheet View", category: "SDP", reason: "Datasheet View presents the table in a spreadsheet-like grid for data manipulation." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut is used to 'stop' a running Slide Show in PowerPoint (6.4)?", options: ["Enter", "Esc", "Shift", "End"], answer: "Esc", category: "SDP", reason: "The Escape key returns the user to the editing view from full-screen presentation mode." },
  { question: "What is the primary mission of the ICT Policy 2072 (8.3)?", options: ["To sell more phones", "To transform Nepal into an information and knowledge-based society", "To make internet free for all", "To ban paper documents"], answer: "To transform Nepal into an information and knowledge-based society", category: "SDP", reason: "The overarching goal of the 2072 policy is socio-economic transformation through digital inclusion." },
  { question: "Which tag (7.2.3.5) is used for 'Table Header' cells, making them bold and centered by default?", options: ["<td>", "<th>", "<tr>", "<thead>"], answer: "<th>", category: "SDP", reason: "<th> defines the heading cells of a table." },
  { question: "Which 'Key' (5.2) in a table connects it to a primary key in another table to form a relationship?", options: ["Master Key", "Foreign Key", "Composite Key", "Shared Key"], answer: "Foreign Key", category: "SDP", reason: "Foreign keys are the mechanism used to link tables logically in a relational database." },
  { question: "To add a 'Transition' effect to the whole slide (6.4), you use which tab?", options: ["Home", "Animations", "Transitions", "Design"], answer: "Transitions", category: "SDP", reason: "The Transitions tab manages the visual handover between slides." },
  { question: "Under the ETA Regulation 2064, how many members constitute the IT Tribunal?", options: ["1 member", "2 members", "3 members", "5 members"], answer: "3 members", category: "SDP", reason: "The specialized IT Tribunal is a three-member judicial body consisting of Law, IT, and Commerce members." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.4) is used to create a numbered (ordered) list?", options: ["<ul>", "<ol>", "<li>", "<nl>"], answer: "<ol>", category: "SDP", reason: "<ol> stands for 'Ordered List'." },
  { question: "In MS Access (5.3.4), which property provides a custom error message to users if they enter invalid data?", options: ["Validation Rule", "Validation Text", "Input Mask", "Required"], answer: "Validation Text", category: "SDP", reason: "Validation Text is the message displayed when the logical condition in a Validation Rule is violated." },
  { question: "Which tool (6.6) allows you to insert logical diagrams like 'Cycles' or 'Flowcharts' in PowerPoint?", options: ["WordArt", "SmartArt", "Table", "Chart"], answer: "SmartArt", category: "SDP", reason: "SmartArt provides logic-based graphic templates for complex information visualization." },
  { question: "The 'Verified' checkmark on official social media accounts is important for (8.7 context):", options: ["Making the account pretty", "Confirming the authenticity and official status of the government handle", "Increasing internet speed", "Deleting old posts"], answer: "Confirming the authenticity and official status of the government handle", category: "SDP", reason: "Verification badges prevent misinformation by identifying the authorized source of truth." },
  { question: "What is the 'alt' attribute used for in the <img> tag (7.2.3.3)?", options: ["To link the image", "To provide a text description for screen readers and as a fallback", "To change the resolution", "To rotate the image"], answer: "To provide a text description for screen readers and as a fallback", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt text is critical for web accessibility for visually impaired users." },
  { question: "Which query type (5.3.6) allows you to 'Summarize' data in a grid similar to an Excel Pivot Table?", options: ["Select Query", "Update Query", "Crosstab Query", "Delete Query"], answer: "Crosstab Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Crosstab queries restructure data to show aggregate values across two different dimensions." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint (6.1), the boxed areas with dotted borders that hold content are called:", options: ["TextBoxes", "Frames", "Placeholders", "Cells"], answer: "Placeholders", category: "SDP", reason: "Placeholders are part of a slide layout, defining where titles, text, or media can be inserted." },
  { question: "Which social media platform (8.6) is famous for 'micro-blogging' and character limits?", options: ["YouTube", "Facebook", "Twitter (X)", "Viber"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter/X is defined by short, concise, real-time updates." },
  { question: "To add a horizontal rule (thematic separator line) in HTML (7.2.3.1), use:", options: ["<br>", "<line>", "<hr>", "<border>"], answer: "<hr>", category: "SDP", reason: "<hr> stands for Horizontal Rule." },
  { question: "What is 'Data Redundancy' in a database (5.1)?", options: ["Data safety", "The storage of the same data in multiple places unnecessarily", "Compressed data", "Private data"], answer: "The storage of the same data in multiple places unnecessarily", category: "SDP", reason: "Redundancy wastes space and leads to inconsistency; DBMS aims to minimize it." },
  { question: "Which view (6.2) in PowerPoint shows the 'text only' content of the slides?", options: ["Slide Sorter", "Normal View", "Outline View", "Reading View"], answer: "Outline View", category: "SDP", reason: "Outline View strips graphics to focus on the content hierarchy of titles and bullets." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government sites must follow which 'Accessibility' standard?", options: ["ISO 9001", "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", "IEEE 802", "HTML 1.0"], answer: "W3C Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)", category: "SDP", reason: "Ensuring all citizens, including those with disabilities, can access information is a legal requirement." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.1) is used for the most important heading on a page?", options: ["<head>", "<h1>", "<heading>", "<h6>"], answer: "<h1>", category: "SDP", reason: "h1 is the primary title level in the HTML heading hierarchy." },
  { question: "What happens if a user tries to enter duplicate values in a field set as a 'Primary Key' (5.2)?", options: ["The system accepts it", "The system displays an error and prevents the record from being saved", "The old record is deleted", "The computer restarts"], answer: "The system displays an error and prevents the record from being saved", category: "SDP", reason: "Uniqueness is the defining rule of a Primary Key." },
  { question: "What is the maximum 'Zoom' level supported in MS PowerPoint (6.2 context)?", options: ["100%", "200%", "400%", "500%"], answer: "400%", category: "SDP", reason: "PowerPoint allows zooming from 10% to 400%." },
  { question: "Which messaging app is most popular in Nepal for official notification 'communities' (8.6)?", options: ["YouTube", "Twitter", "Viber", "Zoom"], answer: "Viber", category: "SDP", reason: "Viber's 'Community' feature is widely used for organizational announcements in Nepal." },
  { question: "To add a 'Tooltip' that appears when hovering over an HTML element (7.2.3.1), use which attribute?", options: ["alt", "title", "name", "src"], answer: "title", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'title' attribute provides extra info shown as a popup on hover." },
  { question: "Which database object (5.3.6) is used to perform bulk changes, like updating all salaries by 10%?", options: ["Select Query", "Update Query", "Form", "Report"], answer: "Update Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Update queries are action queries used to modify existing data in the tables." },
  { question: "To change the 'Aspect Ratio' (e.g. 4:3 to 16:9) in PowerPoint, you go to which tab?", options: ["Home", "Design", "Transitions", "Review"], answer: "Design", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Size and background settings are located in the Design tab." },
  { question: "A 'Digital Nepal Framework' (8.3 context) focuses on how many 'Sectors'?", options: ["5", "8", "10", "12"], answer: "8", category: "SDP", reason: "The framework identifies 8 key sectors like Health, Agriculture, and Finance for digital transformation." },
  { question: "In HTML (7.2.3.5), what does <tr> stand for?", options: ["Table Record", "Table Row", "Text Row", "Title Row"], answer: "Table Row", category: "SDP", reason: "Tables are built row-by-row using the <tr> element." },
  { question: "What is a 'Composite Key' in a database (5.2)?", options: ["A key that uses only text", "A primary key made of two or more fields combined", "A key that is hidden", "A type of password"], answer: "A primary key made of two or more fields combined", category: "SDP", reason: "Composite keys are used when no single field is unique enough to identify a row." },
  { question: "According to the Electronic Transaction Act (ETA), 2063, which authority is responsible for licensing the Certification Authorities (CA)?", options: ["Prime Minister", "Minister of Communication", "Controller", "Director General of DoIT"], answer: "Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 13 of the ETA 2063 empowers the 'Controller' (Office of the Controller of Certification Authority) to issue licenses to CAs." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act, 2079, what is the mandatory retirement age for civil servants?", options: ["58 years", "60 years", "62 years", "65 years"], answer: "60 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The 2079 Act for Sudurpashchim Pradesh aligns with recent changes, setting the retirement age at 60 years." },
  { question: "Which section of the Electronic Transaction Act, 2063 deals with 'Punishment for cybercrime' related to the publication of illegal materials in electronic form?", options: ["Section 44", "Section 45", "Section 47", "Section 50"], answer: "Section 47", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 47 is the most prominent clause for penalizing the publication of prohibited or obscene content online." },
  { question: "What is the maximum fine for a first-time offense under Section 47 of the Electronic Transaction Act, 2063?", options: ["Rs. 50,000", "Rs. 100,000", "Rs. 200,000", "Rs. 500,000"], answer: "Rs. 100,000", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act prescribes a fine not exceeding one hundred thousand rupees or imprisonment up to five years, or both." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act, 2074, which body is responsible for managing local level statistics and data?", options: ["District Coordination Committee", "Pradesh Government", "Rural Municipality/Municipality", "Federal Government"], answer: "Rural Municipality/Municipality", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 11 of the Act lists the collection and management of local statistics as a power and function of the Palika." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is owned and developed by Google?", options: ["Zoom", "Microsoft Teams", "Google Meet", "Viber"], answer: "Google Meet", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Meet is the native enterprise-grade video communication service in the Google Workspace suite." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Development and Management Directive, 2078, where must all government websites be hosted?", options: ["Any private cloud", "Google Cloud", "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", "On the local office computer"], answer: "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive mandates centralized hosting at the GIDC for security, standardization, and data sovereignty." },
  { question: "Which social media platform is primarily known for 'micro-blogging' and real-time news updates?", options: ["Facebook", "Instagram", "Twitter (X)", "YouTube"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter is defined as a micro-blogging service due to its character limits and high-frequency updates." },
  { question: "What is a major 'Disadvantage' of Social Networking for a government organization?", options: ["Direct citizen engagement", "Spread of misinformation and rumors", "Cost-effective dissemination of info", "Transparency"], answer: "Spread of misinformation and rumors", category: "SDP", reason: "The speed and viral nature of social media can lead to the rapid spread of fake news if not managed carefully." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act, 2079, what is the 'Probation Period' for a newly appointed male Computer Operator?", options: ["6 months", "1 year", "18 months", "2 years"], answer: "1 year", category: "SDP", reason: "Similar to the Federal Civil Service Act, males generally serve a 1-year probation, while females serve 6 months." },
  { question: "Under the Electronic Transaction Regulation, 2064, how many members are in the Information Technology Tribunal?", options: ["1 member", "3 members", "5 members", "7 members"], answer: "3 members", category: "SDP", reason: "The IT Tribunal is a three-member body consisting of Law, IT, and Commerce members." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy, 2072 envisions transforming Nepal into a ______ society.", options: ["High-income", "Paper-free", "Information and Knowledge-based", "Industrial"], answer: "Information and Knowledge-based", category: "SDP", reason: "The central vision of the 2072 policy is socio-economic transformation into a knowledge-based society." },
  { question: "Which of the following is an example of an 'Action Query' (Database knowledge applied to section 8.4 context)?", options: ["Select Query", "Update Query", "Find Query", "Simple Query"], answer: "Update Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Action queries (Delete, Update, Append) modify data, which is regulated under the data integrity clauses of the ETA." },
  { question: "According to Directive 2078, every government website must have a link to which of the following for transparency?", options: ["Facebook page of the head", "Suchana Adhikari (Information Officer) details", "A private news portal", "Gaming site"], answer: "Suchana Adhikari (Information Officer) details", category: "SDP", reason: "To comply with the Right to Information Act, official websites must clearly identify the Information Officer." },
  { question: "Which messaging app is owned by Meta Platforms, Inc.?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Viber", "Telegram", "Zoom"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "Meta (formerly Facebook) acquired WhatsApp in 2014." },
  { question: "What is the primary benefit of 'Two-Factor Authentication' (2FA) for social media security?", options: ["Increases internet speed", "Adds an extra layer of security beyond just a password", "Allows logging in without a password", "Deletes viruses"], answer: "Adds an extra layer of security beyond just a password", category: "SDP", reason: "2FA requires a second proof of identity, making it much harder for unauthorized users to gain access." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, a Computer Operator belongs to which 'Service'?", options: ["Engineering Service", "Administration Service", "Miscellaneous (Bibidh) Service", "Education Service"], answer: "Miscellaneous (Bibidh) Service", category: "SDP", reason: "Computer-related posts in the Nepalese civil service are traditionally grouped under the Miscellaneous service." },
  { question: "The 'Digital Nepal Framework' identifies how many key 'Sectors' for transformation as per the 2072 Policy context?", options: ["5", "8", "10", "12"], answer: "8", category: "SDP", reason: "The framework focuses on 8 sectors including Digital Foundation, Agriculture, Health, and Education." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is specifically designed for 'Communities' and is widely popular in Nepal for group messaging?", options: ["Microsoft Teams", "Google Meet", "Viber", "Zoom"], answer: "Viber", category: "SDP", reason: "While Teams/Meet are for meetings, Viber 'Communities' are a standard tool for group communication in Nepal." },
  { question: "What is 'Phishing'?", options: ["A way to catch fish", "Deceptive communication to trick people into revealing sensitive information", "A network protocol", "A type of hardware"], answer: "Deceptive communication to trick people into revealing sensitive information", category: "SDP", reason: "Phishing is a major disadvantage of social networking where attackers impersonate trusted entities." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, what is the mandatory domain extension for all government bodies?", options: [".com.np", ".org.np", ".gov.np", ".net.np"], answer: ".gov.np", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive ensures uniformity and authenticity by mandating the .gov.np TLD." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, a 'Digital Signature' provides which of the following properties to a document?", options: ["Confidentiality", "Integrity and Authenticity", "Fast speed", "Encryption"], answer: "Integrity and Authenticity", category: "SDP", reason: "Signatures ensure the document hasn't been changed (Integrity) and prove who sent it (Authenticity)." },
  { question: "Who serves as the member-secretary of the IT Council under the ICT Policy 2072?", options: ["Minister of IT", "Secretary of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", "Director of NITC", "Chief Secretary"], answer: "Secretary of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", category: "SDP", reason: "The ministerial secretary handles the administrative functions of the high-level IT Council." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Vulnerability' mentioned as a disadvantage of Social Networking?", options: ["Privacy Loss", "Cyberbullying", "Data theft", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "All listed items are documented risks associated with public social networks." },
  { question: "Which tool is best for 'Live Streaming' government press conferences to the general public?", options: ["Microsoft Teams", "Facebook Live / YouTube Live", "WhatsApp Call", "Viber"], answer: "Facebook Live / YouTube Live", category: "SDP", reason: "These platforms are optimized for broadcasting video to large, anonymous public audiences." },
  { question: "According to the Local Government Operation Act 2074, vital registration (Birth, Death, etc.) must be integrated with ______.", options: ["A physical book only", "The National ID / IT system", "A private server", "None of these"], answer: "The National ID / IT system", category: "SDP", reason: "The law promotes a digital workflow that feeds local data into national databases." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, 'Performance Evaluation' is used for:", options: ["Only salary increase", "Promotion and career advancement", "Checking computer speed", "Setting the BIOS"], answer: "Promotion and career advancement", category: "SDP", reason: "Performance scores are a key requirement for being eligible for promotion in the civil service." },
  { question: "What does a 'Verified Account' (Blue checkmark) signify on platforms like Twitter or Facebook?", options: ["The user is rich", "The account is authentic and confirmed by the platform", "The account has no ads", "The account is private"], answer: "The account is authentic and confirmed by the platform", category: "SDP", reason: "Verification badges help citizens distinguish official government accounts from fake ones." },
  { question: "Which 'Advantage' of Social Networking relates to citizen-state relations?", options: ["Cyberstalking", "Direct, two-way communication and feedback", "Privacy settings", "Spreading ads"], answer: "Direct, two-way communication and feedback", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media bridges the gap by allowing citizens to provide feedback directly to officials." },
  { question: "Under ETA 2063, what is the penalty for 'Hacking' into a computer system with the intent to damage it?", options: ["Fine of Rs. 10,000", "Fine of Rs. 200,000 or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Warning letter", "Lifetime prison"], answer: "Fine of Rs. 200,000 or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 45 specifically defines the penalties for unauthorized damage to computer systems." },
  { question: "The Government Website Directive 2078 states that a website should be ______.", options: ["Static only", "Responsive and user-friendly", "Accessible only in English", "Updated once a year"], answer: "Responsive and user-friendly", category: "SDP", reason: "Responsive design ensures the site works well on mobile phones and tablets used by citizens." },
  { question: "Which platform is primarily used for 'video hosting and sharing'?", options: ["LinkedIn", "YouTube", "WhatsApp", "Zoom"], answer: "YouTube", category: "SDP", reason: "YouTube is a dedicated video repository where organizations upload informational content." },
  { question: "The 'ICT Policy 2072' emphasizes 'Green ICT'. What does this mean?", options: ["Using green colored computers", "Eco-friendly disposal of e-waste and energy-efficient computing", "Planting trees near computers", "Using paper instead of digital"], answer: "Eco-friendly disposal of e-waste and energy-efficient computing", category: "SDP", reason: "Green ICT focuses on environmental sustainability within the technology sector." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, a civil servant is 'suspended' if:", options: ["They are late for 1 day", "They are taken into judicial custody for a criminal charge", "They take a sick leave", "They use a mouse"], answer: "They are taken into judicial custody for a criminal charge", category: "SDP", reason: "Legal detention triggers an automatic suspension from civil service duties." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool allows for 'Waiting Rooms' to screen participants before a meeting?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Zoom", "Viber", "SMS"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Zoom's Waiting Room is a standard security feature to prevent 'Zoombombing'." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, what is the required frequency for 'Security Audits'?", options: ["Every 10 years", "Once a year", "Never", "Every day"], answer: "Once a year", category: "SDP", reason: "Periodic audits are necessary to ensure government data remains secure against new threats." },
  { question: "What is 'Netiquette'?", options: ["A new network protocol", "The code of conduct for appropriate behavior on the internet", "A type of firewall", "A search engine"], answer: "The code of conduct for appropriate behavior on the internet", category: "SDP", reason: "Proper behavior on official social channels is essential for professional government communication." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a function of a 'Certification Authority' (CA)?", options: ["Repairing computers", "Issuing Digital Signature Certificates (DSC)", "Selling internet bandwidth", "Designing web graphics"], answer: "Issuing Digital Signature Certificates (DSC)", category: "SDP", reason: "CAs are the authorized bodies that verify identities and issue cryptographic certificates." },
  { question: "Under ICT Policy 2072, what is 'Digital Divide'?", options: ["A division in the CPU", "The gap between those with access to ICT and those without", "Dividing a file into pieces", "A type of password"], answer: "The gap between those with access to ICT and those without", category: "SDP", reason: "Bridging this gap is a major social goal of the national ICT policy." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is integrated by default with 'Google Calendar'?", options: ["Microsoft Teams", "Zoom", "Google Meet", "WhatsApp"], answer: "Google Meet", category: "SDP", reason: "Being part of Google Workspace, Meet is fully synchronized with Google's calendar and mail." },
  { question: "The Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 specifies that 'Politics' participation for employees is:", options: ["Allowed", "Strictly prohibited", "Allowed for Computer Operators only", "Allowed on weekends"], answer: "Strictly prohibited", category: "SDP", reason: "Civil servants must maintain political neutrality to serve the public impartially." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Unauthorized Publication' of data intended for another person under ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Simple warning", "No penalty"], answer: "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 48 penalizes the breach of confidentiality and unauthorized disclosure of digital data." },
  { question: "Which social networking site is specifically designed for 'Image and Video' sharing in square formats?", options: ["LinkedIn", "Twitter", "Instagram", "RSS"], answer: "Instagram", category: "SDP", reason: "Instagram is a visual-centric social network." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, websites must be compatible with which browser(s)?", options: ["Only Google Chrome", "Only Internet Explorer", "All major, commonly used modern browsers", "None"], answer: "All major, commonly used modern browsers", category: "SDP", reason: "Cross-browser compatibility ensures all citizens can access government services regardless of their preferred software." },
  { question: "What is the result of using 'Breakout Rooms' in a video conference?", options: ["The meeting ends", "The group is divided into small, separate discussion sessions", "Everyone is muted", "The screen becomes black"], answer: "The group is divided into small, separate discussion sessions", category: "SDP", reason: "Breakout rooms facilitate small group work within a larger meeting context." },
  { question: "Under the ETA Regulation 2064, what must a person possess to verify a digital signature?", options: ["The Private Key of the sender", "The Public Key of the sender", "A physical key", "No key is needed"], answer: "The Public Key of the sender", category: "SDP", reason: "Asymmetric cryptography uses the public key for verification and the private key for signing." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Pro' of using Social Networking for public education (8.7)?", options: ["Cyberstalking", "Peer-to-peer information sharing and rapid reach", "Identity theft", "Addiction"], answer: "Peer-to-peer information sharing and rapid reach", category: "SDP", reason: "The ability to share knowledge across a massive network instantly is a major advantage." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, which authority is the 'Highest Administrative Officer'?", options: ["The Governor", "The Chief Secretary (Pradesh Mukhya Sachib)", "The Minister", "The Computer Operator"], answer: "The Chief Secretary (Pradesh Mukhya Sachib)", category: "SDP", reason: "The Chief Secretary leads the administrative hierarchy of the province." },
  { question: "What happens if a civil servant in Sudurpashchim Pradesh is caught doing 'Sexual Harassment' (8.2 context)?", options: ["They are promoted", "They face disciplinary action which could lead to dismissal from service", "They pay Rs. 100", "Nothing"], answer: "They face disciplinary action which could lead to dismissal from service", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act includes strict code of conduct rules regarding workplace harassment." },
  { question: "The 'E-Governance Master Plan' (EGMP) targets which of the following?", options: ["Banning the internet", "Effective and efficient citizen-centric service delivery through ICT", "Selling hardware", "Only city dwellers"], answer: "Effective and efficient citizen-centric service delivery through ICT", category: "SDP", reason: "The primary goal of EGMP is the modernization of public service through technology." },
  { question: "According to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, a Computer Operator belongs to which service group?", options: ["Administration", "Engineering", "Miscellaneous (Bibidh)", "Forestry"], answer: "Miscellaneous (Bibidh)", category: "SDP", reason: "In the Nepalese civil service structure, technical ICT roles like Computer Operator are placed under the Miscellaneous (Bibidh) service." },
  { question: "What is the primary purpose of the 'Local Government Operation Act, 2074' (8.1)?", options: ["To manage international relations", "To define the powers and functions of Rural Municipalities and Municipalities", "To regulate national banks", "To control the military"], answer: "To define the powers and functions of Rural Municipalities and Municipalities", category: "SDP", reason: "This act provides the legal framework for the operation of local levels (Palikas) in federal Nepal." },
  { question: "Which specific section of the Electronic Transaction Act (ETA) 2063 provides for the 'IT Tribunal'?", options: ["Section 47", "Section 50", "Section 60", "Section 72"], answer: "Section 60", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 60 of the ETA 2063 mandates the formation of the Information Technology Tribunal to adjudicate cyber offenses." },
  { question: "In a Zoom meeting (8.6), what is the function of the 'Co-host'?", options: ["They can end the meeting for everyone", "They have most administrative controls like the host to manage participants", "They can only watch the video", "They are responsible for paying for the call"], answer: "They have most administrative controls like the host to manage participants", category: "SDP", reason: "Co-hosts assist the host in managing participants (muting, admitting from waiting room) but cannot end the meeting." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy 2072 (8.3) aims to make government services available online. What is the specific target percentage mentioned in the document for the end of its period?", options: ["50%", "75%", "90%", "100%"], answer: "75%", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy set a target to provide 75% of government services through digital channels." },
  { question: "What is a major 'Disadvantage' of social networking as mentioned in syllabus section 8.7?", options: ["Real-time feedback", "Low cost", "Cyberbullying and privacy concerns", "Global reach"], answer: "Cyberbullying and privacy concerns", category: "SDP", reason: "Exposure to online harassment and the risk of personal data theft are significant downsides of social media." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Development and Management Directive 2078 (8.5), all government websites must use which domain?", options: [".com.np", ".org.np", ".gov.np", ".net.np"], answer: ".gov.np", category: "SDP", reason: "Official government portals must use the restricted .gov.np extension to ensure authenticity." },
  { question: "Which social media platform allows for a maximum of 280 characters in a standard post (8.6)?", options: ["Facebook", "Twitter (X)", "Instagram", "WhatsApp"], answer: "Twitter (X)", category: "SDP", reason: "Twitter (now X) is a micro-blogging site defined by its brevity, currently allowing 280 characters for standard users." },
  { question: "Under the ETA Regulation 2064 (8.4), a 'Digital Signature Certificate' is typically valid for how many years before renewal?", options: ["1 year", "2 years", "5 years", "10 years"], answer: "2 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The regulations specify a standard 2-year validity period for issued digital certificates." },
  { question: "Which feature of 'Microsoft Teams' allows users to see a visual history of messages and shared files in one place (8.6)?", options: ["Mute All", "Channels", "Waiting Room", "Filters"], answer: "Channels", category: "SDP", reason: "Channels in Teams act as dedicated sections for specific topics, storing chat history and collaborative files." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, what is the 'probation period' for a newly appointed male employee?", options: ["6 months", "1 year", "18 months", "2 years"], answer: "1 year", category: "SDP", reason: "Standard civil service law in Nepal provides 1 year for males and 6 months for females." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, who is the head of the high-level 'Information Technology Council'?", options: ["Minister of Communication", "Prime Minister", "President", "Chief Secretary"], answer: "Prime Minister", category: "SDP", reason: "The Prime Minister chairs the IT Council to provide top-level strategic direction for the nation." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for publishing 'Obscene Material' in electronic form under Section 47 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Fine of Rs. 10,000", "Imprisonment up to 5 years or fine up to Rs. 100,000 or both", "Simple warning", "No penalty"], answer: "Imprisonment up to 5 years or fine up to Rs. 100,000 or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 47 is the primary clause for content-related cybercrimes in Nepal." },
  { question: "Which of the following is an 'Advantage' of social networking (8.7)?", options: ["Identity theft", "Information spread at zero or low cost", "Addiction", "Fake news"], answer: "Information spread at zero or low cost", category: "SDP", reason: "Social media is a highly efficient and cost-effective tool for disseminating news and information." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is owned by Google and integrated into Gmail (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Microsoft Teams", "Google Meet", "Viber"], answer: "Google Meet", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Meet is the native video communication service for the Google ecosystem." },
  { question: "Under the Local Government Operation Act 2074, which level is responsible for 'Digitizing' local statistics?", options: ["Federal Govt", "Pradesh Govt", "The Municipality/Rural Municipality", "Police Department"], answer: "The Municipality/Rural Municipality", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act places the responsibility of local data management directly on the local government bodies (Palikas)." },
  { question: "What is 'End-to-End Encryption' in the context of WhatsApp (8.6)?", options: ["Messages are public", "Only the sender and recipient can read the message; even WhatsApp cannot access it", "The message is deleted after reading", "The message travels faster"], answer: "Only the sender and recipient can read the message; even WhatsApp cannot access it", category: "SDP", reason: "Encryption ensures privacy by making the data unreadable to any third party during transit." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, which authority handles the 'Transfer' of a Computer Operator within the province?", options: ["Federal Ministry", "Pradesh Ministry of Internal Affairs and Law / Chief Minister's Office", "Public Service Commission", "District Court"], answer: "Pradesh Ministry of Internal Affairs and Law / Chief Minister's Office", category: "SDP", reason: "Provincial ministries handle the administrative transfers of employees within their jurisdiction under the provincial act." },
  { question: "What does a 'Verified' checkmark (Badge) signify on Facebook or Twitter (8.6)?", options: ["The user is famous", "The platform has confirmed the authenticity of the public figure or brand", "The account is free of viruses", "The account is private"], answer: "The platform has confirmed the authenticity of the public figure or brand", category: "SDP", reason: "Verification badges help users distinguish real official accounts from impersonators." },
  { question: "As per the ETA Regulation 2064, who has the power to 'Suspend' a license of a Certification Authority?", options: ["The Police", "The Prime Minister", "The Controller", "The Chief Justice"], answer: "The Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The Controller (OCCA) is the designated regulator with the authority to enforce compliance." },
  { question: "Which feature in 'Zoom' prevents uninvited people from joining a meeting (8.6)?", options: ["Mute", "Waiting Room / Passcode", "Screen Share", "Whiteboard"], answer: "Waiting Room / Passcode", category: "SDP", reason: "Security features like passcodes and waiting rooms ensure that only authorized participants enter the meeting." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy 2072 emphasizes the reduction of 'Digital Divide'. What is it?", options: ["The physical division of a computer", "The gap between people with access to ICT and those without", "Dividing files into folders", "A type of internet speed"], answer: "The gap between people with access to ICT and those without", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital Divide refers to the inequality in access to information and communication technology." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government sites must be updated ______.", options: ["Once a year", "Every month", "Regularly and as soon as new information is available", "Never"], answer: "Regularly and as soon as new information is available", category: "SDP", reason: "Providing current information is a core requirement for governmental transparency." },
  { question: "Which social networking site is specifically designed for 'Professional Networking' (8.6)?", options: ["TikTok", "Instagram", "LinkedIn", "Flickr"], answer: "LinkedIn", category: "SDP", reason: "LinkedIn focuses on career development, professional connections, and industry news." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for hacking into a 'Protected System' under the Electronic Transaction Act 2063?", options: ["Rs. 50,000 fine only", "Fine up to Rs. 500,000 or imprisonment up to 9 years or both", "Warning only", "Rs. 1,000 fine"], answer: "Fine up to Rs. 500,000 or imprisonment up to 9 years or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Attacking critical infrastructure defined as 'Protected Systems' carries significantly higher penalties." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is famous for its 'Together Mode' showing participants in a virtual shared space (8.6)?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Viber", "Microsoft Teams", "Standard Telephone"], answer: "Microsoft Teams", category: "SDP", reason: "Microsoft Teams introduced 'Together Mode' to simulate a shared meeting environment." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, a Computer Operator belongs to the 'Miscellaneous' (Bibidh) service. What is the level for this post?", options: ["4th Level", "5th Level", "6th Level", "Officer Level"], answer: "5th Level", category: "SDP", reason: "The post of Computer Operator is generally categorized as a non-gazetted first-class or 5th level provincial position." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Electronic Record' includes data generated through:", options: ["Only hard disks", "Only magnetic tapes", "Optical, magnetic, or similar means", "Only paper printouts"], answer: "Optical, magnetic, or similar means", category: "SDP", reason: "The definition of electronic record is broad to encompass all digital storage technologies." },
  { question: "What is 'Phishing' in the context of social networking risks (8.7)?", options: ["Catching fish", "Sending fake messages to steal login or credit card data", "Posting high quality photos", "Searching for friends"], answer: "Sending fake messages to steal login or credit card data", category: "SDP", reason: "Phishing is a deceptive social engineering practice used to compromise accounts." },
  { question: "Which directive (8.5) mandates that government websites must be 'Search Engine Friendly'?", options: ["ETA 2063", "Website Management Directive 2078", "ICT Policy 2072", "Civil Service Act"], answer: "Website Management Directive 2078", category: "SDP", reason: "The 2078 directive sets technical standards for SEO so citizens can easily find government services." },
  { question: "Which social media platform is primarily used for 'video sharing' (8.6)?", options: ["Twitter", "Viber", "YouTube", "LinkedIn"], answer: "YouTube", category: "SDP", reason: "YouTube is a dedicated video repository and social platform owned by Google." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is the goal for 'Digital Literacy' by 2020?", options: ["25%", "50%", "75%", "100%"], answer: "75%", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy aimed to bring digital literacy to 75% of the population." },
  { question: "In MS Access (related to 8.4 context of data integrity), what is a 'Tuple'?", options: ["A column", "A table", "A row / record", "A primary key"], answer: "A row / record", category: "SDP", reason: "In relational database theory, a single entry or record is called a tuple." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool allows for 'Screen Sharing' (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Google Meet", "Microsoft Teams", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "Screen sharing is a fundamental feature of all modern video conferencing platforms." },
  { question: "The Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 provides 'Casual Leave' (Pariwarik/Parva Vida) of how many days per year?", options: ["6 days", "12 days", "15 days", "30 days"], answer: "12 days", category: "SDP", reason: "Standard civil service rules in Nepal allocate 12 days of casual/festival leave annually." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Non-repudiation' means:", options: ["You can delete a file", "The sender cannot deny sending the signed document", "The file is encrypted", "Access is blocked"], answer: "The sender cannot deny sending the signed document", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital signatures provide legal and cryptographic proof of authorship." },
  { question: "Which disadvantage of social networking involves 'over-usage' (8.7)?", options: ["Data theft", "Addiction and loss of productivity", "Phishing", "Spam"], answer: "Addiction and loss of productivity", category: "SDP", reason: "Excessive use of social media can lead to behavioral addiction and decreased focus on work." },
  { question: "The Website Directive 2078 requires all government websites to include which contact person?", options: ["The Web Designer", "The Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", "The Prime Minister", "The Police"], answer: "The Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a requirement of the Right to Information Act integrated into the web directive." },
  { question: "Which social media tool is owned by 'Meta'?", options: ["Twitter", "Viber", "Facebook", "Google Meet"], answer: "Facebook", category: "SDP", reason: "Meta Platforms, Inc. is the parent company of Facebook, Instagram, and WhatsApp." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is 'G-Cloud'?", options: ["Gaming Cloud", "Government Cloud for centralized IT infrastructure", "Green Cloud", "Global Cloud"], answer: "Government Cloud for centralized IT infrastructure", category: "SDP", reason: "G-Cloud is a shared computing resource for various government agencies." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for damaging computer source code under ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Rs. 1,000 fine", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 44 of the Act specifically protects computer source code." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool has a '40-minute limit' for free group meetings (8.6)?", options: ["Google Meet", "WhatsApp", "Zoom", "Viber"], answer: "Zoom", category: "SDP", reason: "Zoom's free tier imposes a 40-minute cap on meetings with 3 or more people." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, a permanent employee is entitled to how many days of 'Sick Leave' per year?", options: ["6 days", "12 days", "15 days", "30 days"], answer: "12 days", category: "SDP", reason: "Civil servants earn one day of sick leave per month worked, totaling 12 per year." },
  { question: "The 'Citizen Charter' must be prominently displayed as per (8.5):", options: ["On every website page", "In the 'About' section only", "On the homepage and in a searchable format", "It is not required"], answer: "On the homepage and in a searchable format", category: "SDP", reason: "Standardizing access to citizen charters on websites is a key mandate of the 2078 directive." },
  { question: "Which messaging app is commonly used for 'End-to-End' encrypted private messages (8.6)?", options: ["WhatsApp", "Twitter", "YouTube", "Flickr"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "WhatsApp uses the Signal protocol to ensure only the parties in the chat can read messages." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Asymmetric Cryptosystem' uses how many keys?", options: ["1", "2 (Public and Private)", "3", "Unlimited"], answer: "2 (Public and Private)", category: "SDP", reason: "Asymmetric encryption relies on a pair of related keys for security." },
  { question: "Which of these is an 'Advantage' of social networking (8.7)?", options: ["Privacy Loss", "Real-time dissemination of alerts and news", "Spreading rumors", "Cyber stalking"], answer: "Real-time dissemination of alerts and news", category: "SDP", reason: "The speed of social media makes it ideal for immediate public safety announcements." },
  { question: "In Sudurpashchim Pradesh, what is the 'Age Limit' for a female candidate to apply for a permanent government post?", options: ["35 years", "40 years", "45 years", "50 years"], answer: "40 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The age limit is 35 for males and 40 for females/candidates with disabilities." },
  { question: "What happens if 'Referential Integrity' is enforced and you try to delete a record used as a primary key by another table?", options: ["The record is deleted", "The database gives an error and blocks the deletion", "The computer restarts", "The text turns red"], answer: "The database gives an error and blocks the deletion", category: "SDP", reason: "Integrity rules prevent 'orphaned' data by ensuring child records must have a parent." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool is owned by 'Microsoft' (8.6)?", options: ["Zoom", "Meet", "Teams", "Viber"], answer: "Teams", category: "SDP", reason: "Microsoft Teams is the corporate communication tool for the Microsoft 365 suite." },
  { question: "Which section of the Electronic Transaction Act (ETA) 2063 provides for the 'Extraterritorial Jurisdiction' of the law?", options: ["Section 2", "Section 15", "Section 47", "Section 72"], answer: "Section 2", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 2 of the ETA 2063 states that the Act applies to any person who commits an offense outside Nepal if the computer system is located within Nepal." },
  { question: "According to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, a 'Computer Operator' is appointed to a permanent post through which method?", options: ["Internal Promotion only", "Open Competitive Examination", "Contract service", "Nomination by the Minister"], answer: "Open Competitive Examination", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act mandates that permanent civil service positions must be filled through open and fair competitive exams conducted by the Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog." },
  { question: "Under the Local Government Operation Act 2074, which 'Digital Service' is a mandatory power of the Ward Committee?", options: ["Hosting international websites", "Management of local level data and vital registration (Birth/Death)", "Issuing national citizenship", "Regulating satellite TV"], answer: "Management of local level data and vital registration (Birth/Death)", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act empowers local levels to digitize and manage local records, particularly civil registrations." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for a person who knowingly 'hacks' a computer system to destroy or alter data under Section 45 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Fine of Rs. 10,000", "Imprisonment up to 3 years or fine up to Rs. 200,000 or both", "Lifetime ban from using computers", "Rs. 1,000 fine per day"], answer: "Imprisonment up to 3 years or fine up to Rs. 200,000 or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 45 specifically defines the punishment for unauthorized damage to data and systems." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is the target for the ICT sector's contribution to the national GDP by 2020?", options: ["2.5%", "5%", "7.5%", "10%"], answer: "7.5%", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy document set an economic target for the ICT sector to reach a 7.5% share of the GDP." },
  { question: "The 'Government Website Development and Management Directive 2078' mandates that websites must be updated in which languages?", options: ["Nepali only", "English only", "Both Nepali and English", "Any local language only"], answer: "Both Nepali and English", category: "SDP", reason: "Official government portals must provide information in both the national and an international language for broad accessibility." },
  { question: "Who is the 'Authority' for issuing licenses to Certification Authorities (CA) under the ETA 2063?", options: ["Director of Nepal Police", "The Controller", "The Prime Minister", "The Chief Justice"], answer: "The Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The OCCA (Office of the Controller of Certification Authority) is the legal licensing and regulatory body." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, what is the probation period for a 'Female' employee?", options: ["3 months", "6 months", "1 year", "2 years"], answer: "6 months", category: "SDP", reason: "Provincial and Federal laws in Nepal provide a 6-month probation for females and 1 year for males." },
  { question: "As per the Electronic Transaction Regulation 2064, how many members are in the 'Appellate Tribunal'?", options: ["1 member", "2 members", "3 members", "5 members"], answer: "3 members", category: "SDP", reason: "The Appellate Tribunal, like the IT Tribunal, is a three-member judicial body." },
  { question: "Which institutional role involves the management of the 'Government Integrated Data Center' (GIDC)?", options: ["DoIT", "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", "Ministry of Finance", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC is the primary body under MoCIT responsible for the government's centralized hardware infrastructure." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy 2072 emphasizes 'Digital Literacy' to achieve which percentage by 2020?", options: ["50%", "75%", "90%", "100%"], answer: "75%", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy aimed to bring 75% of the population to a standard level of digital literacy." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Digital Signature Theft' or fraudulent use under Section 51 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", "Simple warning", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Misusing or stealing someone's digital identity for deceit is a criminal offense." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, who owns the 'Copyright' of the content on a government portal?", options: ["The Private Developer", "The Hosting Provider", "The respective Government Organization", "The Information Officer"], answer: "The respective Government Organization", category: "SDP", reason: "Official data and content generated by the state belong legally to that specific government entity." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, 'Suspension' of an employee occurs if they are:", options: ["Late for office for 5 days", "Taken into judicial custody for a criminal offense", "On sick leave", "Traveling abroad"], answer: "Taken into judicial custody for a criminal offense", category: "SDP", reason: "Legal detention leads to an automatic suspension of service duties until the case outcome." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Electronic Record' refers to data generated by:", options: ["Only desktop PCs", "Any electronic, magnetic, optical, or similar means", "Only printers", "Only paper files"], answer: "Any electronic, magnetic, optical, or similar means", category: "SDP", reason: "The Act uses a broad, technologically neutral definition to cover all forms of digital storage." },
  { question: "The 'Citizen Charter' (Nagarik Bada Patra) must be digitally available on websites as per:", options: ["ETA 2063", "Government Website Directive 2078", "Civil Service Act", "Local Government Act"], answer: "Government Website Directive 2078", category: "SDP", reason: "Standardizing access to public service procedures is a key mandate of the 2078 directive." },
  { question: "Who serves as the member-secretary of the 'IT council' chaired by the Prime Minister (8.3)?", options: ["Minister of IT", "Secretary of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", "Director of NITC", "Chief Justice"], answer: "Secretary of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", category: "SDP", reason: "The Secretary handles the administrative leadership of the national high-level Council." },
  { question: "What is the result of applying a 'Cascade Delete' in a relationship (Technical law context 8.4)?", options: ["It deletes the database", "It automatically deletes related child records when a parent record is deleted", "It creates a backup", "It increases speed"], answer: "It automatically deletes related child records when a parent record is deleted", category: "SDP", reason: "Referential integrity maintenance (Cascade Delete) is a core requirement for valid relational databases under electronic standards." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, which body conducts recruitment for provincial posts?", options: ["Federal Public Service Commission", "Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog", "DoIT", "Ministry of IT"], answer: "Pradesh Lok Sewa Aayog", category: "SDP", reason: "Provincial recruitment is the constitutional and legal mandate of the Provincial Public Service Commission." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'damaging computer source code' under Section 44 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Warning only", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Source code protection is critical for software integrity and is legally enforced under Section 44." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government sites must be hosted on which infrastructure?", options: ["Private Cloud", "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", "Local hard drive", "Foreign server"], answer: "Government Integrated Data Center (GIDC)", category: "SDP", reason: "Centralized hosting at GIDC ensures national data security and standardized management." },
  { question: "The 'Digital Nepal Framework' identifies how many priority sectors for digital transformation?", options: ["5", "8", "10", "12"], answer: "8", category: "SDP", reason: "The framework focuses on 8 sectors including Health, Agriculture, Energy, and Education." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, 'Performance Evaluation' is primarily used for:", options: ["Salary increase only", "Promotion and career advancement", "Checking internet usage", "Setting the BIOS"], answer: "Promotion and career advancement", category: "SDP", reason: "Performance scores are a mandatory weightage factor in the promotion system of civil servants." },
  { question: "Under ETA 2063, 'Non-repudiation' in Digital Signatures ensures that:", options: ["The document is secret", "The signer cannot deny having signed and sent the document", "The file is compressed", "The internet is fast"], answer: "The signer cannot deny having signed and sent the document", category: "SDP", reason: "Cryptographic proof using a unique private key makes the signer legally accountable." },
  { question: "The 'IT Tribunal' members are appointed by whom?", options: ["Chief Justice", "Public Service Commission", "Government of Nepal", "Minister of IT"], answer: "Government of Nepal", category: "SDP", reason: "The executive government appoints the judicial, technical, and commercial members of the Tribunal." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is 'E-Health'?", options: ["Selling gadgets online", "Telemedicine and digital health records to improve medical reach", "Replacing doctors with computers", "Printing medical books"], answer: "Telemedicine and digital health records to improve medical reach", category: "SDP", reason: "E-health uses ICT to improve healthcare delivery, especially in remote regions." },
  { question: "As per the Website Directive 2078, every government website must clearly identify which contact person?", options: ["The Web Developer", "The Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", "The Prime Minister", "The Security Guard"], answer: "The Information Officer (Suchana Adhikari)", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a mandatory requirement to facilitate the Right to Information for citizens." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Asymmetric Cryptosystem' refers to using:", options: ["One secret key", "A pair of related keys (Public and Private)", "A simple password", "A physical lock"], answer: "A pair of related keys (Public and Private)", category: "SDP", reason: "Asymmetric encryption is the foundational technology for modern digital signatures." },
  { question: "Which institutional role involves the 'Standardization' of Devanagari Unicode in Nepal (8.5 context)?", options: ["NITC", "Department of Information Technology (DoIT)", "Nepal Academy", "Ministry of Home Affairs"], answer: "Department of Information Technology (DoIT)", category: "SDP", reason: "DoIT leads the implementation of technical IT standards and localized language support." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Digital Identity Theft' under Section 51 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 1,000 fine", "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", "Warning only", "No punishment"], answer: "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Fraudulently creating or using another person's digital signature is a criminal offense." },
  { question: "The ICT Policy 2072 aims to reach 'Broadband' coverage to what percentage of the population by 2020?", options: ["50%", "75%", "90%", "100%"], answer: "90%", category: "SDP", reason: "Infrastructure growth targets are a core part of the policy's roadmap." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government sites must be compatible with:", options: ["Only Google Chrome", "Only Windows 7", "All major, commonly used modern browsers", "None"], answer: "All major, commonly used modern browsers", category: "SDP", reason: "Cross-browser compatibility ensures all citizens can access government services." },
  { question: "Under the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, can a civil servant participate in 'Political Party' activities?", options: ["Yes, it's a right", "No, it is strictly prohibited for permanent employees", "Only after office hours", "Only on holidays"], answer: "No, it is strictly prohibited for permanent employees", category: "SDP", reason: "Political neutrality is a fundamental code of conduct for civil servants in Nepal." },
  { question: "What happens if you violate 'Referential Integrity' while attempting to delete a primary key record?", options: ["The record is deleted anyway", "The DBMS blocks the deletion with an error", "The computer restarts", "The data turns red"], answer: "The DBMS blocks the deletion with an error", category: "SDP", reason: "Referential integrity protects the logic of the database by preventing orphaned child records." },
  { question: "Which institutional role involves the 'Web Audit' of government portals to check for security flaws?", options: ["Ministry of Finance", "Department of Information Technology (DoIT)", "National Library", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "Department of Information Technology (DoIT)", category: "SDP", reason: "DoIT provides security testing to protect state digital assets from hacking." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, the term 'Digital Divide' refers to:", options: ["Dividing a computer physically", "The gap between those who have access to technology and those who do not", "Dividing files into folders", "A type of firewall"], answer: "The gap between those who have access to technology and those who do not", category: "SDP", reason: "Reducing this inequality is a major socio-economic goal of the policy." },
  { question: "The 'Government Cloud' (G-Cloud) infrastructure is operated by which institution?", options: ["Google", "NITC", "Ministry of Communication", "Microsoft"], answer: "NITC", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC manages the shared cloud resources for government departments in Nepal." },
  { question: "As per the ETA 2063, if a cybercrime is committed against a system in Nepal from 'Another Country', the law:", options: ["Does not apply", "Applies as if the offense was committed in Nepal", "Applies only to citizens", "Requires a UN warrant"], answer: "Applies as if the offense was committed in Nepal", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 2 provides extraterritorial jurisdiction to protect national digital interests." },
  { question: "The Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 provides how many days of 'Casual Leave' per year?", options: ["6 days", "12 days", "15 days", "30 days"], answer: "12 days", category: "SDP", reason: "Standard civil service rules in Nepal allocate 12 days for personal and festival leave." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for 'Breach of Confidentiality' under Section 48 of ETA 2063?", options: ["Rs. 500 fine", "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", "Suspension from work", "Simple warning"], answer: "Rs. 100,000 fine or 2 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Penalties exist for those who disclose secret electronic data obtained while performing official duties." },
  { question: "Which institution handles 'Domain Registration' for .gov.np sites for free (8.5 context)?", options: ["Mercantile", "NITC", "DoIT", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "NITC", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC is the official and free registrar for all Nepalese government domain names." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063, 'Digital Signature' is achieved using which combination?", options: ["Password + SMS", "Asymmetric Cryptosystem + Hash function", "Image scan + Password", "Voice + Fingerprint"], answer: "Asymmetric Cryptosystem + Hash function", category: "SDP", reason: "This is the technical definition of a secure digital signature under the law." },
  { question: "According to the Website Directive 2078, government homepages must be updated within what time frame for new notices?", options: ["24 hours", "7 days", "30 days", "Never"], answer: "24 hours", category: "SDP", reason: "Timely dissemination of official information is a core requirement of the directive." },
  { question: "In the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, the 'Miscellaneous' (Bibidh) service group is where ______ belong.", options: ["Doctors", "Engineers", "Computer Operators", "Drivers"], answer: "Computer Operators", category: "SDP", reason: "IT-related technical posts are categorized under the Miscellaneous service group." },
  { question: "What is the 'Retirement Age' in Sudurpashchim Pradesh as per the 2079 Act?", options: ["58 years", "60 years", "62 years", "65 years"], answer: "60 years", category: "SDP", reason: "The provincial act established 60 years as the mandatory retirement age." },
  { question: "Who acts as the 'Secretariat' for the national Information Technology Council?", options: ["NITC", "DoIT", "Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", "Nepal Police"], answer: "Ministry of Communication and Information Technology", category: "SDP", reason: "The Ministry handles the administrative and coordinating functions for the IT Council." },
  { question: "Under ETA 2063, a 'Certification Authority' (CA) must have a license issued by:", options: ["The Prime Minister", "The Controller", "The Nepal Rastra Bank", "The Police"], answer: "The Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The Office of the Controller regulates the entities that issue digital certificates." },
  { question: "According to ICT Policy 2072, 'Green ICT' focuses on:", options: ["Green monitor screens", "Eco-friendly disposal of e-waste and energy efficiency", "Using computers in forests", "Banning paper entirely"], answer: "Eco-friendly disposal of e-waste and energy efficiency", category: "SDP", reason: "Sustainability and environmental responsibility are core components of modern ICT policies." },
  { question: "The 'Hetauda Disaster Recovery Center (DRC)' serves as a backup for:", options: ["Google servers", "The GIDC in Kathmandu", "The Nepal Police", "Private Banks"], answer: "The GIDC in Kathmandu", category: "SDP", reason: "The Hetauda center provides geographical redundancy for critical state data." },
  { question: "What is the 'Primary Goal' of the Electronic Transaction Act 2063?", options: ["To ban computers", "To provide legal recognition to electronic data and secure digital signatures", "To increase tax on software", "To hire more operators"], answer: "To provide legal recognition to electronic data and secure digital signatures", category: "SDP", reason: "The ETA was enacted to bridge the legal gap between physical and digital transactions in Nepal." },
  { question: "In the Hexadecimal number system, what is the decimal value of the digit 'E'?", options: ["12", "13", "14", "15"], answer: "14", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal uses 0-9, then A=10, B=11, C=12, D=13, E=14, and F=15." },
  { question: "Which specific hardware component is responsible for providing 'Grounding' or 'Earthing' to protect a PC from electrical surges (10.1)?", options: ["SMPS", "The metal chassis connected to the power cord's third pin", "The CMOS battery", "The CPU fan"], answer: "The metal chassis connected to the power cord's third pin", category: "SDP", reason: "The third pin on a power plug connects the computer's metal case to the building's earth ground to safely divert stray electricity." },
  { question: "What is the binary equivalent of the decimal number '20'?", options: ["10100", "10011", "11000", "10110"], answer: "10100", category: "SDP", reason: "20 in binary is 16 + 4, which corresponds to the bits at positions 2^4 and 2^2 (10100)." },
  { question: "According to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079, which 'Service' category does the post of Computer Operator fall under?", options: ["Administration", "Miscellaneous (Bibidh)", "Engineering", "Education"], answer: "Miscellaneous (Bibidh)", category: "SDP", reason: "Technical IT-related positions like Computer Operator are grouped under the 'Miscellaneous' (Bibidh) service in the civil service framework." },
  { question: "In the Windows Command Prompt (2.4), which command is used to remove the 'System' and 'Hidden' attributes from a file named 'secret.sys'?", options: ["ATTRIB -S -H secret.sys", "ATTRIB +S +H secret.sys", "DEL S H secret.sys", "REN S H secret.sys"], answer: "ATTRIB -S -H secret.sys", category: "SDP", reason: "The minus (-) sign is used in the ATTRIB command to clear or remove specific attributes." },
  { question: "Which function in MS Excel (4.4.18) allows you to find the 'input' value required to achieve a specific target 'output'?", options: ["Pivot Table", "Scenario Manager", "Goal Seek", "Solver"], answer: "Goal Seek", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a 'What-If' analysis tool that iterates to find the value of a single variable needed for a desired result." },
  { question: "What is the primary technical difference between 'Preeti' and 'Nepali Unicode' fonts (3.3.5)?", options: ["Preeti is faster to type", "Unicode is a universal encoding standard that is logically understood by the OS for sorting and searching", "Preeti uses less RAM", "Unicode only works on the internet"], answer: "Unicode is a universal encoding standard that is logically understood by the OS for sorting and searching", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode maps characters to unique digital codes, whereas legacy fonts like Preeti are simply visual overlays on English ASCII keys." },
  { question: "Which database object (5.3.6) provides the most user-friendly interface for entering new data into a table?", options: ["Query", "Report", "Form", "Relationship window"], answer: "Form", category: "SDP", reason: "Forms provide a structured screen layout designed to facilitate data entry and navigation for end-users." },
  { question: "In HTML (7.2.3.5), which tag is used to define an individual data cell within a table row?", options: ["<tr>", "<th>", "<td>", "<thead>"], answer: "<td>", category: "SDP", reason: "<td> stands for Table Data, representing the standard cells in an HTML table." },
  { question: "What does a 'Continuous short beep' during the BIOS POST process typically signify (10.4)?", options: ["Hardware is working perfectly", "Power Supply failure or overheating issue", "Keyboard is missing", "RAM is not detected"], answer: "Power Supply failure or overheating issue", category: "SDP", reason: "A non-stop alarm beep is a critical warning indicating power instability or a thermal emergency." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072 (8.3), which institution is responsible for hosting the 'GIDC'?", options: ["Ministry of Home Affairs", "Department of IT", "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "National Information Technology Center (NITC)", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC manages the Government Integrated Data Center, which acts as the central hub for state digital data." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut key is used to insert a 'New Slide' in PowerPoint?", options: ["Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + M", "Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + D"], answer: "Ctrl + M", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + N creates a new file; Ctrl + M inserts a new slide into the current presentation." },
  { question: "Which IPv4 address is reserved for 'Loopback' testing of the local computer?", options: ["192.168.1.1", "127.0.0.1", "10.0.0.1", "255.255.255.255"], answer: "127.0.0.1", category: "SDP", reason: "127.0.0.1 is the standard address used to verify that the local TCP/IP stack is functioning." },
  { question: "In a database (5.2), 'Referential Integrity' prevents which of the following?", options: ["Data duplication in a single table", "Orphaned records in a related table", "Slow query performance", "Formatting errors"], answer: "Orphaned records in a related table", category: "SDP", reason: "Referential integrity ensures that every foreign key value in a child table matches a valid primary key in the parent table." },
  { question: "Which 'View' in MS Word is best suited for viewing the hierarchical structure of headings (3.3.18)?", options: ["Print Layout", "Outline View", "Draft View", "Read Mode"], answer: "Outline View", category: "SDP", reason: "Outline View allows users to expand or collapse sections based on their assigned Heading styles." },
  { question: "Which 'System Tool' (2.5.2.9) would you use to return your system files to an earlier state after a virus attack?", options: ["Disk Defragmenter", "Disk Scanning", "System Restore", "Format"], answer: "System Restore", category: "SDP", reason: "System Restore rolls back the registry and system files to a previously saved 'Restore Point'." },
  { question: "What is the result of using the 'DIR /W' command in the Command Prompt?", options: ["List files with full details", "List files across the screen in multiple columns (Wide format)", "List only system files", "List files in descending order"], answer: "List files across the screen in multiple columns (Wide format)", category: "SDP", reason: "The /W switch displays filenames in a compact grid to save screen space." },
  { question: "In MS Excel, what happens if you apply 'Absolute' referencing ($A$1) to a formula and copy it across a row?", options: ["The reference changes to B1, C1...", "The reference remains fixed to $A$1", "The formula results in #REF!", "The formula is deleted"], answer: "The reference remains fixed to $A$1", category: "SDP", reason: "Dollar signs lock the coordinates so they never change during a move or copy operation." },
  { question: "Which 'Section Break' (3.3.11) allows you to change the orientation from Portrait to Landscape for a single page inside a document?", options: ["Continuous", "Next Page", "Even Page", "Column"], answer: "Next Page", category: "SDP", reason: "Next Page section breaks allow for unique page setup and orientation settings for the pages within that section." },
  { question: "What is the penalty for unauthorized 'Publication' of electronic information under Section 48 of the ETA 2063?", options: ["Fine up to Rs. 10,000", "Fine up to Rs. 200,000 or imprisonment up to 3 years or both", "Simple warning", "Rs. 1,000 fine per day"], answer: "Fine up to Rs. 200,000 or imprisonment up to 3 years or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 48 penalizes the breach of confidentiality and unauthorized disclosure of private data." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Tab' in Word 2013 contains the 'Page Borders' and 'Watermark' tools (3.3.19)?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Design", "Layout"], answer: "Design", category: "SDP", reason: "Starting from Word 2013, Microsoft moved page-styling background tools to a new dedicated 'Design' tab." },
  { question: "In the legacy 'Preeti' font layout, which key produces the Nepali character 'च'?", options: ["c", "v", "j", "d"], answer: "c", category: "SDP", reason: "In Preeti font mapping, the lowercase 'c' key is mapped to 'Cha' (च)." },
  { question: "Which network topology (1.7.6) uses a central backbone cable with terminators at both ends?", options: ["Star", "Ring", "Bus", "Mesh"], answer: "Bus", category: "SDP", reason: "In a Bus topology, all nodes are connected to a single linear cable." },
  { question: "What does a '######' display in an Excel cell indicate (4.4.2)?", options: ["Invalid formula", "The column is too narrow to display the numeric value", "Reference is missing", "The value is zero"], answer: "The column is too narrow to display the numeric value", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel uses hash marks as a visual cue that there isn't enough horizontal space to show a number or date." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Directive 2078 (8.5), how often should a security audit be performed?", options: ["Every 10 years", "Once every month", "At least once a year", "Never"], answer: "At least once a year", category: "SDP", reason: "The directive mandates annual audits to ensure the resilience of government portals against cyber threats." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Markup Tag' is used to define the title of an HTML document seen in the browser tab?", options: ["<head>", "<meta>", "<title>", "<h1>"], answer: "<title>", category: "SDP", reason: "The <title> tag must be nested inside the <head> element." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of a 'Digital Signature' for a government official?", options: ["To make emails faster", "To ensure authenticity, integrity, and non-repudiation of electronic documents", "To hide the sender's name", "To compress the file"], answer: "To ensure authenticity, integrity, and non-repudiation of electronic documents", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital signatures provide cryptographic proof of identity and that the content hasn't been tampered with." },
  { question: "Which 'Backup Method' (10.8) saves only the data that has changed since the last backup of any type?", options: ["Full Backup", "Incremental Backup", "Differential Backup", "Mirror Backup"], answer: "Incremental Backup", category: "SDP", reason: "Incremental backups are the fastest as they only store the absolute newest changes since the previous log." },
  { question: "In MS Excel, the function '=MOD(10, 3)' will return which value?", options: ["3.33", "1", "3", "0"], answer: "1", category: "SDP", reason: "MOD returns the remainder of a division. 10 / 3 = 3 with a remainder of 1." },
  { question: "To start a program directly from the Windows 'Run' dialog box (Win+R), you should type its ______ name.", options: ["Formal", "Executable", "Icon", "Shortcut"], answer: "Executable", category: "SDP", reason: "Typing the .exe filename (like notepad or calc) starts the application process directly." },
  { question: "Which component of the CPU (1.2.2.3) manages the flow of data between the ALU and memory?", options: ["Control Unit", "Cache", "Register", "Bus"], answer: "Control Unit", category: "SDP", reason: "The Control Unit (CU) coordinates and directs the movement of instructions and data inside the processor." },
  { question: "A '.ppsx' file extension in PowerPoint (6.2) represents a:", options: ["Template", "Standard Editable Presentation", "PowerPoint Show (Opens directly to presentation mode)", "Macro-enabled file"], answer: "PowerPoint Show (Opens directly to presentation mode)", category: "SDP", reason: "A Show file bypasses the editing interface for immediate delivery." },
  { question: "Which video conferencing tool mentioned in syllabus 8.6 is owned by Meta?", options: ["Zoom", "WhatsApp", "Teams", "Google Meet"], answer: "WhatsApp", category: "SDP", reason: "WhatsApp, along with Instagram and Facebook, is owned by Meta Platforms, Inc." },
  { question: "What is the base of the 'Octal' number system?", options: ["2", "8", "10", "16"], answer: "8", category: "SDP", reason: "Octal is base-8, using digits 0 through 7." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.4) is used to create a list with 'bullets'?", options: ["<ol>", "<ul>", "<li>", "<nl>"], answer: "<ul>", category: "SDP", reason: "<ul> stands for 'Unordered List'." },
  { question: "The 'Hanging Indent' (3.3.9) is commonly used for which part of a document?", options: ["Letter head", "Title page", "Bibliographies / References", "Footnotes"], answer: "Bibliographies / References", category: "SDP", reason: "Hanging indents allow author names to stand out on the left margin." },
  { question: "What is the primary objective of an Operating System as defined in 2.1?", options: ["To make hardware more expensive", "To provide a convenient and efficient interface between user and hardware", "To delete old files automatically", "To stop all network access"], answer: "To provide a convenient and efficient interface between user and hardware", category: "SDP", reason: "The goal of an OS is resource management and user convenience." },
  { question: "In 'Preeti' font, the key 'Shift + f' results in which character?", options: ["ि", "ी", "इ", "ई"], answer: "ी", category: "SDP", reason: "Lowercase 'f' is the short 'i' sign (ि); Shift + 'f' is the long 'i' sign (ी) in Preeti." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Key' (5.2) in a database table uniquely identifies each record?", options: ["Foreign Key", "Master Key", "Primary Key", "Secondary Key"], answer: "Primary Key", category: "SDP", reason: "Primary keys must be unique and cannot contain null values." },
  { question: "What is the result of binary addition '1 + 1'?", options: ["1", "2", "10", "11"], answer: "10", category: "SDP", reason: "1+1 equals 2 decimal, which is written as '10' in binary." },
  { question: "Which browser (1.7.4) is developed by the Mozilla Foundation?", options: ["Chrome", "Edge", "Safari", "Firefox"], answer: "Firefox", category: "SDP", reason: "Mozilla Firefox is a popular open-source web browser." },
  { question: "Which system tool (2.5.2.9) is used to 'prepare' a new storage drive by creating a file system?", options: ["Scanning", "Defragmenter", "Format", "Restore"], answer: "Format", category: "SDP", reason: "Formatting initializes the storage structure on a partition." },
  { question: "What happens if a user 'Accidentally' deletes a file from a 'Network Drive' in Windows Explorer?", options: ["It goes to the local Recycle Bin", "It is permanently deleted immediately", "It moves to the server's desktop", "The computer crashes"], answer: "It is permanently deleted immediately", category: "SDP", reason: "Network drives do not use the local computer's Recycle Bin for holding deleted items." },
  { question: "To start a 'New Document' in any Windows application, the universal shortcut is:", options: ["Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + O", "Ctrl + P"], answer: "Ctrl + N", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + N is the standard command to create a new instance/file." },
  { question: "The 'Formula Bar' in Excel displays which of the following?", options: ["Only the resulting value", "The underlying calculation or formula of the active cell", "The name of the author", "The computer name"], answer: "The underlying calculation or formula of the active cell", category: "SDP", reason: "The formula bar allows you to see the logic behind the visible result in a cell." },
  { question: "Which 'Number System' is Base-16?", options: ["Binary", "Octal", "Decimal", "Hexadecimal"], answer: "Hexadecimal", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal uses sixteen symbols (0-F)." },
  { question: "In the IP address '192.168.1.1', which part represents the first 'Octet'?", options: ["192", "168", "1", "The whole address"], answer: "192", category: "SDP", reason: "An octet is one of the four 8-bit blocks in an IPv4 address." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Remedy' prevents a 'Virus' from infecting the system when a thumb drive is plugged in?", options: ["Firewall", "Antivirus (Real-time protection / USB scan)", "Formatting the monitor", "Changing the keyboard"], answer: "Antivirus (Real-time protection / USB scan)", category: "SDP", reason: "Antivirus software proactively scans removable media to block malware execution." },
  { question: "What is the binary representation of decimal '1'?", options: ["0", "1", "10", "11"], answer: "1", category: "SDP", reason: "Decimal 1 remains 1 in binary form." },
  { question: "Which institutional unit in Nepal (11.5.4) provides 'Security Monitoring' for government digital assets?", options: ["SOC", "DoIT", "MoCIT", "NITC"], answer: "SOC", category: "SDP", reason: "Security Operation Centers perform constant monitoring to detect cyber attacks." },
  { question: "What is the decimal equivalent of the Octal number '27'?", options: ["21", "23", "27", "31"], answer: "23", category: "SDP", reason: "(2 × 8¹) + (7 × 8⁰) = 16 + 7 = 23." },
  { question: "In MS Excel, which feature (4.4.18) is used to find the best possible value for a formula by changing multiple variables while staying within constraints?", options: ["Goal Seek", "Solver", "Scenario Manager", "Data Validation"], answer: "Solver", category: "SDP", reason: "While Goal Seek handles one variable, Solver is an advanced add-in that handles multiple variables and constraints." },
  { question: "According to the Electronic Transaction Act 2063, which authority handles the licensing of Certification Authorities?", options: ["Minister of IT", "The Controller", "Director of NITC", "Governor of NRB"], answer: "The Controller", category: "SDP", reason: "The Office of the Controller of Certification Authority (OCCA) is the regulator for digital signature licenses in Nepal." },
  { question: "Which specific register in the CPU (1.2.2.3) stores the current 'opcode' while it is being decoded by the Control Unit?", options: ["Program Counter", "Accumulator", "Instruction Register (IR)", "Memory Data Register"], answer: "Instruction Register (IR)", category: "SDP", reason: "The Instruction Register holds the bit-pattern of the command currently being executed by the processor." },
  { question: "In command-line operation (2.4), what does the command 'ATTRIB +H +R filename.txt' do?", options: ["Deletes the file", "Makes the file both Hidden and Read-only", "Renames the file to HR", "Moves the file to a hidden folder"], answer: "Makes the file both Hidden and Read-only", category: "SDP", reason: "The ATTRIB command allows multiple flags to be set simultaneously using the '+' operator." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.4) is used to create a multi-line input area for long comments or messages?", options: ["<input type='text'>", "<textarea>", "<textblock>", "<input type='area'>"], answer: "<textarea>", category: "SDP", reason: "<textarea> allows for resizable, multi-line user input in a web form." },
  { question: "In the legacy 'Preeti' font layout (3.12), which key produces the Nepali character 'प'?", options: ["p", "h", "k", "i"], answer: "h", category: "SDP", reason: "In the Preeti mapping used in Nepal, the 'h' key is assigned to the letter 'Pa' (प)." },
  { question: "What is the primary characteristic of 'Ransomware' (9.2)?", options: ["Showing popup ads", "Encrypting user files and demanding payment for the key", "Recording keystrokes", "Deleting the BIOS"], answer: "Encrypting user files and demanding payment for the key", category: "SDP", reason: "Ransomware targets data availability by locking files behind encryption until a ransom is paid." },
  { question: "Which hardware device (10.3) uses an 8-pin connector and is the standard for Ethernet networking?", options: ["RJ-11", "RJ-45", "BNC", "HDMI"], answer: "RJ-45", category: "SDP", reason: "RJ-45 is the standard modular connector used with Twisted Pair (UTP/STP) networking cables." },
  { question: "In MS Access (5.3.6), which object is best for displaying an interactive 'dialog-style' screen for data entry?", options: ["Table", "Report", "Query", "Form"], answer: "Form", category: "SDP", reason: "Forms provide the graphical user interface layer over raw database tables for better usability." },
  { question: "What is the binary representation of the decimal number '31'?", options: ["1111", "10000", "11111", "11011"], answer: "11111", category: "SDP", reason: "31 is 16+8+4+2+1, which corresponds to five consecutive '1' bits (11111)." },
  { question: "To start a Slide Show in PowerPoint from the 'Beginning', which function key is used?", options: ["F2", "F5", "Shift + F5", "F12"], answer: "F5", category: "SDP", reason: "F5 launches the presentation from the first slide; Shift + F5 starts from the active slide." },
  { question: "Which network utility (8.6) provides the local IP address and MAC address of a Windows computer?", options: ["ping", "ipconfig /all", "nslookup", "tracert"], answer: "ipconfig /all", category: "SDP", reason: "The /all switch provides comprehensive details including the 'Physical Address' (MAC)." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072 (8.3), what is the goal for broadband speed for residential areas?", options: ["128 kbps", "512 kbps / 2 Mbps", "1 Gbps", "10 Gbps"], answer: "512 kbps / 2 Mbps", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy defined minimum broadband speed targets to encourage digital growth in households." },
  { question: "Which document security feature (9.4) allows a recipient to verify that a document came from a specific sender (Authenticity)?", options: ["Encryption", "Digital Signature", "Password", "Folder Lock"], answer: "Digital Signature", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital signatures use asymmetric keys to provide proof of origin that cannot be forged." },
  { question: "In MS Word, which keyboard shortcut creates a 'Non-Breaking Space' to keep two words together on one line?", options: ["Ctrl + Space", "Shift + Space", "Ctrl + Shift + Space", "Alt + Space"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + Space", category: "SDP", reason: "Non-breaking spaces prevent the browser/processor from splitting specific words across a line break." },
  { question: "Which Excel error (4.4.2) occurs if you try to divide a number by zero or an empty cell?", options: ["#VALUE!", "#REF!", "#DIV/0!", "#NAME?"], answer: "#DIV/0!", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a mathematical error code identifying division by zero." },
  { question: "In a relational database (5.2), 'Cardinality' refers to:", options: ["The number of columns", "The number of rows (records)", "The storage size", "The number of users"], answer: "The number of rows (records)", category: "SDP", reason: "Cardinality is the count of tuples (rows) in a relation; Degree is the count of attributes (columns)." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Remedy' (1.4/9.3.4) identifies and deletes malware by matching its 'code signature'?", options: ["Firewall", "IDS", "Antivirus software", "Disk Defragmenter"], answer: "Antivirus software", category: "SDP", reason: "Signature-based detection is the primary method antivirus uses to find known malware." },
  { question: "To change the 'Orientation' of a page from Portrait to Landscape in MS Excel, you go to the ______ tab.", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Page Layout", "View"], answer: "Page Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "All physical page setup options are managed within the Page Layout tab." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Default Gateway' in network settings (8.5)?", options: ["To boost speed", "To act as the exit point for traffic going to external networks", "To assign IPs", "To translate domain names"], answer: "To act as the exit point for traffic going to external networks", category: "SDP", reason: "The gateway is the IP of the router interface that bridges the local LAN to the internet." },
  { question: "Which institutional role (11.5.3) involves maintaining the 'Disaster Recovery Center' (DRC) in Hetauda?", options: ["DoIT", "NITC", "MoCIT", "Nepal Telecom"], answer: "NITC", category: "SDP", reason: "NITC operates both the primary data center (Kathmandu) and the recovery site (Hetauda)." },
  { question: "What is the result of binary multiplication '10 × 11'?", options: ["101", "110", "111", "1010"], answer: "110", category: "SDP", reason: "Decimal 2 (10) × Decimal 3 (11) = Decimal 6. 6 in binary is 110." },
  { question: "In HTML (7.2.3.5), which tag is used for the header cells of a table?", options: ["<td>", "<th>", "<tr>", "<thead>"], answer: "<th>", category: "SDP", reason: "<th> stands for Table Header and usually renders as bold/centered text." },
  { question: "Which Windows tool (10.7) shows a yellow icon when a hardware component has no compatible driver?", options: ["Task Manager", "Disk Management", "Device Manager", "Resource Monitor"], answer: "Device Manager", category: "SDP", reason: "Device Manager manages all hardware communication through drivers and flags problematic hardware." },
  { question: "Which security principle is violated when an attacker 'intercepts' a private email (9.2)?", options: ["Confidentiality", "Integrity", "Availability", "Authorization"], answer: "Confidentiality", category: "SDP", reason: "Confidentiality is about ensuring only authorized recipients can read the data." },
  { question: "What is the base of the 'Hexadecimal' number system?", options: ["2", "8", "10", "16"], answer: "16", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal uses sixteen symbols: 0-9 and A-F." },
  { question: "Which MS Excel function (4.7) returns the 'current date' only, as a static or dynamic value?", options: ["=NOW()", "=DATE()", "=TODAY()", "=TIME()"], answer: "=TODAY()", category: "SDP", reason: "=TODAY() returns just the system date; =NOW() includes the time." },
  { question: "To start a new 'Row' in a table while at the last cell using the keyboard, press:", options: ["Enter", "Tab", "Spacebar", "Shift"], answer: "Tab", category: "SDP", reason: "In MS Word and Excel, pressing Tab in the final cell of a row/table automatically adds a new entry space." },
  { question: "Which type of network is most suitable for connecting personal devices like a mouse, headset, and phone (1.7.2)?", options: ["LAN", "PAN", "WAN", "MAN"], answer: "PAN", category: "SDP", reason: "PAN (Personal Area Network) covers the immediate range (meters) around an individual." },
  { question: "What happens if a computer case is 'shaking' or vibrating loudly (10.4)?", options: ["Reinstall the OS", "Check for loose screws on fans or the mechanical hard drive", "Change the monitor", "Upgrade the RAM"], answer: "Check for loose screws on fans or the mechanical hard drive", category: "SDP", reason: "Mechanical moving parts cause resonance; tightening mountings is the primary maintenance fix." },
  { question: "According to the Government Website Directive 2078 (8.5), websites must be accessible via:", options: ["Only Firefox", "Only Chrome", "All major modern web browsers", "None"], answer: "All major modern web browsers", category: "SDP", reason: "Universal accessibility requires cross-browser compatibility for all citizens." },
  { question: "Which 'View' in PowerPoint allows you to manage the universal 'footer' and 'page number' on printed notes (6.3)?", options: ["Slide Master", "Notes Master", "Handout Master", "Outline View"], answer: "Notes Master", category: "SDP", reason: "The Notes Master template controls the layout and metadata of physical speaker notes printouts." },
  { question: "What is 'Liveware' (1.2.4)?", options: ["Hardware that is on", "The people who use and maintain the computer system", "A type of virus", "Network cables"], answer: "The people who use and maintain the computer system", category: "SDP", reason: "Liveware refers to the human component (operators, admins) in an information system." },
  { question: "What is the decimal equivalent of the binary number '1100'?", options: ["8", "10", "12", "14"], answer: "12", category: "SDP", reason: "8 + 4 = 12." },
  { question: "Which component of the OS (2.1) acts as a bridge between user applications and the physical hardware?", options: ["The Shell", "The Kernel", "The BIOS", "The GUI"], answer: "The Kernel", category: "SDP", reason: "The kernel is the essential core that manages hardware resources for software apps." },
  { question: "In 'Preeti' font, the key 'Shift + f' results in which character?", options: ["ि", "ी", "इ", "ई"], answer: "ी", category: "SDP", reason: "Lowercase 'f' is the short 'i' sign; Shift + 'f' is the long 'i' sign (ी) in legacy Preeti." },
  { question: "Which 'Key' in a database table (5.2) links to a primary key in another table?", options: ["Master Key", "Foreign Key", "Shared Key", "Composite Key"], answer: "Foreign Key", category: "SDP", reason: "Foreign keys establish relationships by referencing unique identifiers in other tables." },
  { question: "Convert the decimal number '9' into octal.", options: ["9", "10", "11", "12"], answer: "11", category: "SDP", reason: "9 divided by 8 is 1 with a remainder of 1. Reading upwards gives '11'." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Wildcard' (1.6.3) is used to find a file where one character is unknown?", options: ["*", "?", "#", "@"], answer: "?", category: "SDP", reason: "The question mark (?) represents exactly one unknown character." },
  { question: "What is the primary role of the 'SOC' (11.5.4) in the Nepalese government?", options: ["Selling computers", "Providing 24/7 security monitoring for state systems", "Repairing laptops", "Editing videos"], answer: "Providing 24/7 security monitoring for state systems", category: "SDP", reason: "Security Operation Centers are dedicated to real-time defense of critical digital assets." },
  { question: "Which type of maintenance (10.8 context) creates a copy of data to protect against hardware failure?", options: ["Preventive", "Reactive", "Backup", "Format"], answer: "Backup", category: "SDP", reason: "Backup creates redundant data sets for recovery purposes." },
  { question: "In 'Microsoft Network' (1.7.7), what does a 'Homegroup' allow?", options: ["Internet access for free", "Easy sharing of files and printers among home PCs", "Encryption of emails", "Blocking hackers"], answer: "Easy sharing of files and printers among home PCs", category: "SDP", reason: "Homegroups were designed to simplify local peer-to-peer sharing in Windows." },
  { question: "Which 'Number System' is Base-2?", options: ["Decimal", "Octal", "Hexadecimal", "Binary"], answer: "Binary", category: "SDP", reason: "The binary system uses only two symbols (0 and 1)." },
  { question: "What happens if a technician touches a 'Motherboard' without being grounded (10.1)?", options: ["It gets cleaned", "Electrostatic Discharge (ESD) can destroy sensitive circuits", "The CPU gets faster", "No change"], answer: "Electrostatic Discharge (ESD) can destroy sensitive circuits", category: "SDP", reason: "Human bodies carry static electricity that can 'fry' microscopic semiconductor pathways." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Section Break' (3.8) starts a new section on the very next page?", options: ["Continuous", "Next Page", "Even Page", "Odd Page"], answer: "Next Page", category: "SDP", reason: "Next Page breaks are the standard way to divide a document into parts with unique formatting." },
  { question: "What is the binary representation of decimal '5'?", options: ["101", "110", "111", "011"], answer: "101", category: "SDP", reason: "4 + 1 = 5, which is 1 0 1 in the 2^n positions." },
  { question: "Which 'Institutional Body' (11.5.2) in Nepal issues 'Computer Operator' vacancies through competitive exams?", options: ["DoIT", "NITC", "MoCIT", "Public Service Commission (Lok Sewa Aayog)"], answer: "Public Service Commission (Lok Sewa Aayog)", category: "SDP", reason: "Recursive question: the Lok Sewa Aayog is the constitutional body for civil service recruitment." },
  { question: "To repeat a logo on 'Every Page' of a printout in Excel (4.10), you should insert it in the:", options: ["First Row", "Header", "Floating textbox", "Status bar"], answer: "Header", category: "SDP", reason: "Headers and footers repeat visual elements on every physical sheet produced by the printer." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'ALU' (1.2.2.3)?", options: ["Coordinate instruction flow", "Perform mathematical and logical calculations", "Store permanent data", "Connect to the web"], answer: "Perform mathematical and logical calculations", category: "SDP", reason: "The Arithmetic Logic Unit is the 'calculator' engine of the CPU." },
  { question: "What is the binary equivalent of the decimal number '45'?", options: ["101101", "110101", "101011", "101111"], answer: "101101", category: "SDP", reason: "45 = 32 + 8 + 4 + 1. In binary positions (32 16 8 4 2 1), this translates to 1 0 1 1 0 1." },
  { question: "Which command-line operation in Windows (2.4) is used to set the 'Archive' attribute on a file named 'data.log'?", options: ["ATTRIB +A data.log", "ATTRIB -A data.log", "SET A data.log", "MOVE A data.log"], answer: "ATTRIB +A data.log", category: "SDP", reason: "The '+A' flag sets the Archive attribute, which indicates to backup software that the file has been modified." },
  { question: "In MS Word, what is the keyboard shortcut for 'Hanging Indent' (3.3.9)?", options: ["Ctrl + M", "Ctrl + T", "Ctrl + K", "Ctrl + H"], answer: "Ctrl + T", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + T creates a hanging indent; Ctrl + Shift + T removes it." },
  { question: "Which Excel function (4.7) counts the number of non-empty cells in a range, including both text and numbers?", options: ["=COUNT()", "=COUNTA()", "=COUNTIF()", "=COUNTBLANK()"], answer: "=COUNTA()", category: "SDP", reason: "COUNTA stands for 'Count All' (non-blank cells); COUNT only tallies numeric data." },
  { question: "In a database (5.2), a key that is a 'Primary Key' in one table and used to link to another table is called a:", options: ["Candidate Key", "Foreign Key", "Composite Key", "Super Key"], answer: "Foreign Key", category: "SDP", reason: "Foreign keys are the mechanism used to establish and enforce links between the data in two tables." },
  { question: "Which PowerPoint view (6.4) is the best for seeing all slides as thumbnails to easily reorganize the presentation flow?", options: ["Outline View", "Slide Sorter View", "Reading View", "Notes Page View"], answer: "Slide Sorter View", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Sorter provides a grid-based overview of the entire deck, allowing for easy drag-and-drop sequencing." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.2) is used to define the largest heading level?", options: ["<h6>", "<head>", "<h1>", "<heading>"], answer: "<h1>", category: "SDP", reason: "HTML provides six levels of headings, where <h1> is the most important and largest." },
  { question: "What is the standard 'subnet mask' for a Class C IPv4 address (8.5)?", options: ["255.0.0.0", "255.255.0.0", "255.255.255.0", "255.255.255.255"], answer: "255.255.255.0", category: "SDP", reason: "Class C networks use the first 24 bits for the network ID, represented by 255.255.255.0." },
  { question: "Which specific malware type (9.2) disguises itself as a legitimate program to trick the user into installing it?", options: ["Worm", "Virus", "Trojan Horse", "Spyware"], answer: "Trojan Horse", category: "SDP", reason: "Trojans appear helpful or legitimate but contain hidden malicious code that executes once the program is run." },
  { question: "What does a 'Continuous Beep' during the computer's POST process typically indicate (10.4)?", options: ["Success", "RAM Error", "Power Supply Unit failure or CPU Overheating", "No keyboard detected"], answer: "Power Supply Unit failure or CPU Overheating", category: "SDP", reason: "A non-stop alarm beep is a critical warning from the BIOS regarding power or thermal status." },
  { question: "According to the Sudurpashchim Pradesh Civil Service Act 2079 (8.2), what is the 'probation period' for a newly appointed male Computer Operator?", options: ["6 months", "1 year", "1.5 years", "2 years"], answer: "1 year", category: "SDP", reason: "The provincial act specifies a 1-year probation for males and 6 months for females." },
  { question: "In the Hexadecimal system, what is the decimal equivalent of 'A'?", options: ["9", "10", "11", "12"], answer: "10", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal uses 0-9, then A=10, B=11, C=12, D=13, E=14, F=15." },
  { question: "Which Windows element (2.5.2.1) acts as a temporary holding area for deleted files until they are permanently removed?", options: ["My Computer", "Recycle Bin", "Taskbar", "Control Panel"], answer: "Recycle Bin", category: "SDP", reason: "The Recycle Bin allows for the restoration of files deleted from the local hard drive." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Double Underline' text in MS Word?", options: ["Ctrl + U", "Ctrl + Shift + U", "Ctrl + Shift + D", "Alt + D"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + D", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl+U is for single underline; Ctrl+Shift+D applies a double line formatting." },
  { question: "Which Excel feature (4.4.18) allows you to automatically calculate a target input value by working backward from a known result?", options: ["Sort", "Filter", "Goal Seek", "Data Validation"], answer: "Goal Seek", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a 'What-If Analysis' tool that solves for a missing variable to reach a specific goal." },
  { question: "In a database, what is the 'Primary Key' constraint?", options: ["Must be a number", "Must be unique and not null", "Must be the first field", "Must contain text"], answer: "Must be unique and not null", category: "SDP", reason: "Primary keys must uniquely identify every row and cannot have empty (Null) values." },
  { question: "Which specific Animation category (6.5) causes an object to 'appear' on a PowerPoint slide during the show?", options: ["Entrance", "Emphasis", "Exit", "Motion Path"], answer: "Entrance", category: "SDP", reason: "Entrance effects control the arrival of an element on the screen." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.5) is used to define a row in a table?", options: ["<td>", "<th>", "<tr>", "<thead>"], answer: "<tr>", category: "SDP", reason: "<tr> stands for Table Row; it acts as a container for data and header cells." },
  { question: "What does 'DNS' stand for in computer networking (8.5)?", options: ["Digital Network System", "Domain Name System", "Data Network Service", "Direct Name Server"], answer: "Domain Name System", category: "SDP", reason: "DNS is the service that translates human-readable domain names into numeric IP addresses." },
  { question: "Which security principle ensures that data has not been altered or tampered with during transmission?", options: ["Confidentiality", "Integrity", "Availability", "Authentication"], answer: "Integrity", category: "SDP", reason: "Integrity is the assurance that the information is accurate and consistent." },
  { question: "Which hardware component (10.1) provides battery backup and surge protection to a computer system?", options: ["SMPS", "UPS", "CMOS", "Motherboard"], answer: "UPS", category: "SDP", reason: "Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) provides emergency power when the input power source fails." },
  { question: "According to the Electronic Transaction Act 2063 (8.4), who is responsible for the 'Security' of the private key of a digital signature?", options: ["The Government", "The Controller", "The Subscriber", "The Police"], answer: "The Subscriber", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 31 of the ETA 2063 states the subscriber must take reasonable care to retain control of the private key." },
  { question: "What is the decimal equivalent of the Octal number '12'?", options: ["8", "10", "12", "14"], answer: "10", category: "SDP", reason: "(1 × 8¹) + (2 × 8⁰) = 8 + 2 = 10." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Windows System Tool' (2.5.2.9) is used to consolidate fragmented files on a mechanical hard drive?", options: ["Disk Scanning", "Disk Defragmenter", "Backup", "System Restore"], answer: "Disk Defragmenter", category: "SDP", reason: "Defragmentation improves disk read speeds by making files occupy contiguous storage sectors." },
  { question: "In MS Word, the legacy Devanagari font 'Preeti' (3.3.5) maps the character 'ह' to which English key?", options: ["h", "u", "i", "s"], answer: "i", category: "SDP", reason: "In the Preeti keyboard layout, pressing 'i' results in the Nepali letter 'Ha'." },
  { question: "Which mathematical operator represents 'Multiplication' in an Excel formula?", options: ["x", "X", "*", "."], answer: "*", category: "SDP", reason: "The asterisk (*) is the standard arithmetic operator for multiplication in computing." },
  { question: "What is 'Referential Integrity' in MS Access (5.2)?", options: ["Ensuring data is encrypted", "Ensuring that a foreign key value always has a matching primary key in a related table", "Speeding up report generation", "Checking for spelling"], answer: "Ensuring that a foreign key value always has a matching primary key in a related table", category: "SDP", reason: "Referential integrity maintains consistent relationships and prevents orphaned data." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to start a Slide Show from the 'Beginning' in PowerPoint?", options: ["F2", "F5", "Shift + F5", "F12"], answer: "F5", category: "SDP", reason: "F5 launches the presentation from the first slide." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.2) is used to create a hyperlink?", options: ["<link>", "<href>", "<a>", "<url>"], answer: "<a>", category: "SDP", reason: "The anchor tag (<a>) creates clickable links using the 'href' attribute." },
  { question: "Which network topology (8.1) is most robust because every node is connected to every other node?", options: ["Star", "Bus", "Ring", "Mesh"], answer: "Mesh", category: "SDP", reason: "Mesh topology provides high redundancy and alternative paths for data if a link fails." },
  { question: "Which type of malware (9.2) records every key pressed by the user to steal passwords?", options: ["Virus", "Worm", "Keylogger", "Adware"], answer: "Keylogger", category: "SDP", reason: "Keyloggers are a form of spyware that captures input strings to compromise accounts." },
  { question: "If a computer's 'Date and Time' keeps resetting after every reboot, which component needs replacing?", options: ["PSU", "RAM", "CMOS Battery", "CPU"], answer: "CMOS Battery", category: "SDP", reason: "The CMOS battery maintains power to the Real-Time Clock (RTC) chip when the system is off." },
  { question: "According to the ICT Policy 2072, what is a 'Digital Divide'?", options: ["Dividing a computer into two parts", "The gap between those with access to modern ICT and those without", "A mathematical division problem", "A type of internet firewall"], answer: "The gap between those with access to modern ICT and those without", category: "SDP", reason: "The policy aims to reduce inequality in technology access across the nation." },
  { question: "What is the result of binary addition '10 + 01'?", options: ["10", "11", "101", "01"], answer: "11", category: "SDP", reason: "Decimal 2 (10) + Decimal 1 (01) = Decimal 3 (11)." },
  { question: "Which command in Windows CMD (2.4) clears the current screen of all text?", options: ["DIR", "VER", "CLS", "EXIT"], answer: "CLS", category: "SDP", reason: "'CLS' stands for Clear Screen." },
  { question: "Which feature in MS Word (3.14) is used to create a set of labels for 100 different recipients from one template?", options: ["Mail Merge", "Track Changes", "Format Painter", "Thesaurus"], answer: "Mail Merge", category: "SDP", reason: "Mail Merge automates mass personalized output by combining a document with a data source." },
  { question: "In MS Excel, what does the reference 'Sheet1!$B$10' represent?", options: ["Relative reference", "Absolute reference to cell B10 on Sheet 1", "Mixed reference", "An error"], answer: "Absolute reference to cell B10 on Sheet 1", category: "SDP", reason: "The dollar signs lock both column and row, and the exclamation mark denotes a sheet reference." },
  { question: "What is 'Normalization' in a database (5.1)?", options: ["Increasing data duplication", "Organizing data into multiple tables to minimize redundancy", "Formatting text", "Scanning for viruses"], answer: "Organizing data into multiple tables to minimize redundancy", category: "SDP", reason: "Normalization improves data integrity and reduces wasted storage space." },
  { question: "Which PowerPoint 'View' (6.4) allows the presenter to see notes and upcoming slides while the audience sees only the current slide?", options: ["Outline View", "Reading View", "Presenter View", "Notes Page"], answer: "Presenter View", category: "SDP", reason: "Presenter View uses dual monitors to provide extra tools and info to the speaker." },
  { question: "Which HTML tag (7.2.3.3) specifies 'alternative text' if an image cannot be displayed?", options: ["src", "link", "alt", "href"], answer: "alt", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'alt' attribute is essential for accessibility and as a fallback if the image source is broken." },
  { question: "Which network device (8.3) connects different networks and directs traffic based on IP addresses?", options: ["Hub", "Switch", "Router", "Repeater"], answer: "Router", category: "SDP", reason: "Routers operate at the Network layer to determine the best path for data packets across subnets." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of a 'Firewall' in Cyber Security (9.3.2)?", options: ["Speed up downloads", "Filter incoming and outgoing network traffic based on security rules", "Clean the computer hardware", "Update Windows"], answer: "Filter incoming and outgoing network traffic based on security rules", category: "SDP", reason: "A firewall acts as a protective barrier between trusted internal networks and the untrusted internet." },
  { question: "If a technician uses 'Isopropyl Alcohol' (99%) for maintenance (10.1), what is the most likely use?", options: ["Cleaning a printer ink", "Removing old thermal paste and cleaning delicate circuit contacts", "Washing the plastic case", "Cooling the CPU"], answer: "Removing old thermal paste and cleaning delicate circuit contacts", category: "SDP", reason: "High-purity alcohol evaporates quickly without leaving conductive residue, making it safe for electronics." },
  { question: "Under the ETA 2063 (11.2), what is the penalty for unauthorized 'Hacking' (Section 45)?", options: ["Rs. 5,000 fine", "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", "Lifetime ban from internet", "Warning letter"], answer: "Rs. 200,000 fine or 3 years imprisonment or both", category: "SDP", reason: "Section 45 specifically defines the punishment for damaging systems or unauthorized data access." },
  { question: "What is the Hexadecimal equivalent of decimal '16'?", options: ["10", "16", "F", "G"], answer: "10", category: "SDP", reason: "16 / 16 = 1 (remainder 0). The value is 10 in base-16." },
  { question: "Which Windows element (2.5.2.1) displays the Start button and active application icons?", options: ["Title Bar", "Scroll Bar", "Taskbar", "Status Bar"], answer: "Taskbar", category: "SDP", reason: "The Taskbar is the primary navigation bar located at the bottom of the Windows desktop." },
  { question: "Which key produces the ' Akar' (ा) vowel sign in the legacy Preeti font?", options: ["a", "f", "s", "d"], answer: "f", category: "SDP", reason: "In the legacy Preeti layout, 'f' is used to type the Aa-vowel (ा)." },
  { question: "Which specific MS Excel view (4.4.19) allows you to see the exact blue boundary lines for printing?", options: ["Normal View", "Page Layout View", "Page Break Preview", "Outline View"], answer: "Page Break Preview", category: "SDP", reason: "Page Break Preview allows users to manually adjust exactly where data is split across physical pages." },
  { question: "Which database object (5.3.6) summarizes data for a final, professional presentation on paper?", options: ["Form", "Query", "Table", "Report"], answer: "Report", category: "SDP", reason: "Reports are formatted objects intended for output, grouping, and totaling data." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'ALU' in the CPU (1.2.2.3)?", options: ["Manage timing", "Perform arithmetic and logical operations", "Store permanent files", "Connect to Wi-Fi"], answer: "Perform arithmetic and logical operations", category: "SDP", reason: "The Arithmetic Logic Unit is the mathematical processing engine of the central processor." },
  { question: "Which type of computer is primarily designed to process data from a physical process such as heartbeats or seismic activity?", options: ["Digital Computer", "Analog Computer", "Hybrid Computer", "Supercomputer"], answer: "Analog Computer", category: "SDP", reason: "Analog computers deal with continuous variables and physical quantities rather than discrete numbers." },
  { question: "A smartphone or a tablet is categorized under which type of computer?", options: ["Mainframe", "Minicomputer", "Microcomputer", "Supercomputer"], answer: "Microcomputer", category: "SDP", reason: "Microcomputers use microprocessors and are designed for individual use, including desktops, laptops, and mobile devices." },
  { question: "Which type of computer is used in large organizations for high-volume transaction processing like airline reservations?", options: ["Workstation", "Mainframe", "Supercomputer", "Mini Computer"], answer: "Mainframe", category: "SDP", reason: "Mainframes are optimized for high-volume input/output and large-scale data management." },
  { question: "Which application of computer technology refers to using computers to help design products like machinery or buildings?", options: ["CAM", "CAD", "CBT", "CAL"], answer: "CAD", category: "SDP", reason: "CAD (Computer-Aided Design) is used by engineers and architects to create precise technical drawings and 3D models." },
  { question: "A computer that combines the features of both analog and digital computers is known as a:", options: ["Mainframe", "Supercomputer", "Hybrid Computer", "Workstation"], answer: "Hybrid Computer", category: "SDP", reason: "Hybrid computers use analog components for speed/physical data and digital components for logical accuracy." },
  { question: "What is the primary difference between a computer virus and a computer worm?", options: ["A virus is helpful, a worm is not", "A virus needs a host file to attach to, while a worm is standalone", "Worms only infect monitors", "Viruses are made of hardware"], answer: "A virus needs a host file to attach to, while a worm is standalone", category: "SDP", reason: "Viruses are parasitic and need human action to spread; worms are self-replicating and travel via network vulnerabilities." },
  { question: "Which cybersecurity threat involves a malicious program disguised as a legitimate software to trick users into installing it?", options: ["Worm", "Spyware", "Trojan Horse", "Phishing"], answer: "Trojan Horse", category: "SDP", reason: "Trojans rely on deception (social engineering) to bypass security rather than self-replication." },
  { question: "Deceptive emails that look like they come from a trusted bank to steal passwords are a form of:", options: ["Spamming", "Phishing", "Hacking", "Formatting"], answer: "Phishing", category: "SDP", reason: "Phishing targets human psychology to steal credentials through fake communications." },
  { question: "Which type of malware quietly records every key pressed by the user to capture sensitive data?", options: ["Ransomware", "Adware", "Keylogger", "Logic Bomb"], answer: "Keylogger", category: "SDP", reason: "Keyloggers are a type of spyware used specifically to steal login IDs and passwords." },
  { question: "What is the best 'Remedy' for protecting a computer from external cyber threats?", options: ["Increasing the RAM", "Installing and updating Antivirus and Firewall software", "Cleaning the keyboard", "Turning off the monitor"], answer: "Installing and updating Antivirus and Firewall software", category: "SDP", reason: "Antivirus and Firewalls provide the essential software barriers needed to detect and block malicious traffic." },
  { question: "Which malware type encrypts a user's files and demands payment to unlock them?", options: ["Spyware", "Trojan", "Ransomware", "Worm"], answer: "Ransomware", category: "SDP", reason: "Ransomware holds data hostage for financial gain." },
  { question: "Which of the following is NOT one of the five basic elements of multimedia?", options: ["Text", "Graphics", "Hardware", "Animation"], answer: "Hardware", category: "SDP", reason: "Multimedia elements are content types (Text, Graphics, Audio, Video, Animation); hardware is the medium used to play them." },
  { question: "In multimedia, what is the term for a series of static images played in rapid sequence to show motion?", options: ["Video", "Transition", "Animation", "Filtering"], answer: "Animation", category: "SDP", reason: "Animation creates the illusion of movement using drawings or computer models." },
  { question: "Which hardware component is essential for a computer to process and output audio in a multimedia system?", options: ["Graphic Card", "Sound Card", "Network Card", "Modem"], answer: "Sound Card", category: "SDP", reason: "The sound card converts digital audio data into analog signals for speakers." },
  { question: "Multimedia applications used for both education and entertainment are often called:", options: ["Infotainment", "Edutainment", "Broadcasting", "Simulations"], answer: "Edutainment", category: "SDP", reason: "Edutainment combines educational content with game-like elements to keep learners engaged." },
  { question: "Which of the following describes a 'Folder' in a computer system?", options: ["A piece of hardware", "A logical container used to organize and group files", "A single line of text", "A type of internet connection"], answer: "A logical container used to organize and group files", category: "SDP", reason: "Folders (directories) help users manage the storage hierarchy on a disk." },
  { question: "What does a 'File Extension' identify?", options: ["The size of the file", "The type or format of the file and the app that opens it", "The location of the file", "The author's name"], answer: "The type or format of the file and the app that opens it", category: "SDP", reason: "Extensions like .docx or .pdf tell the OS how to handle the data." },
  { question: "Which file extension is used for a standard image file with high compression?", options: [".txt", ".exe", ".jpg", ".mp3"], answer: ".jpg", category: "SDP", reason: "JPEG (.jpg) is a lossy compressed format optimized for digital photography." },
  { question: "Which file attribute makes a file invisible to standard directory listings?", options: ["Read-only", "Archive", "Hidden", "System"], answer: "Hidden", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Hidden' attribute (+H) keeps sensitive or system files out of the user's normal view." },
  { question: "When setting up a Microsoft Network, a 'Workgroup' is characterized as:", options: ["A centralized server-controlled network", "A peer-to-peer network for small groups without a central server", "A public internet connection", "A type of firewall"], answer: "A peer-to-peer network for small groups without a central server", category: "SDP", reason: "Workgroups are logical groupings of PCs for easy sharing within a local home or small office." },
  { question: "To share a 'Printer' in a Windows network, you must enable which setting?", options: ["IPCONFIG", "File and Printer Sharing", "DNS Client", "Disk Scanning"], answer: "File and Printer Sharing", category: "SDP", reason: "This Windows feature allows local resources to be accessible by other nodes on the LAN." },
  { question: "Which command-line utility in Windows allows you to view the computer's 'Full Pathname' and name?", options: ["VER", "HOSTNAME", "CLS", "VOL"], answer: "HOSTNAME", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'hostname' command returns the logical name assigned to the machine in the network." },
  { question: "How many 'octets' (8-bit blocks) make up an IPv4 address?", options: ["2", "4", "6", "8"], answer: "4", category: "SDP", reason: "IPv4 is a 32-bit address divided into four 8-bit decimal numbers separated by dots (e.g., 192.168.1.1)." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of a 'Subnet Mask'?", options: ["To hide the IP address", "To define the boundary between the network portion and host portion of an IP address", "To provide faster internet", "To encrypt data"], answer: "To define the boundary between the network portion and host portion of an IP address", category: "SDP", reason: "The mask identifies which part of the IP address belongs to the specific subnet." },
  { question: "The 'Default Gateway' is usually the IP address of which device?", options: ["The Printer", "The Local PC", "The Router interface connecting to the outside network", "The DNS server"], answer: "The Router interface connecting to the outside network", category: "SDP", reason: "The gateway is the 'exit' used by a local node to send data outside its own subnet." },
  { question: "Which technology allows a remote user to access a private internal network securely via an encrypted 'tunnel' over the internet?", options: ["WWW", "VPN", "Intranet", "Extranet"], answer: "VPN", category: "SDP", reason: "VPN (Virtual Private Network) provides confidentiality and security across public networks." },
  { question: "Which network topology connects every node to a single central cable called a backbone?", options: ["Star", "Ring", "Bus", "Mesh"], answer: "Bus", category: "SDP", reason: "Bus topology uses a shared linear cable with terminators at each end." },
  { question: "In which topology does every node act as a 'repeater' to pass signals to the next neighbor in a circle?", options: ["Bus", "Star", "Mesh", "Ring"], answer: "Ring", category: "SDP", reason: "Ring topology uses a closed-loop system where data travels in one direction through each node." },
  { question: "Which set of rules governs how data is packaged and transmitted over the internet?", options: ["Topology", "Protocol (e.g., TCP/IP)", "Medium", "Gateway"], answer: "Protocol (e.g., TCP/IP)", category: "SDP", reason: "Protocols are standardized rules that allow diverse systems to communicate." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Dynamic' address assignment method in a Microsoft Network?", options: ["Static IP", "DHCP", "Manual Entry", "MAC Mapping"], answer: "DHCP", category: "SDP", reason: "DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol) automatically assigns IP addresses to clients." },
  { question: "Which computer application involves 'Telemedicine' as a primary use case?", options: ["Banking", "Health / Medicine", "Entertainment", "E-Commerce"], answer: "Health / Medicine", category: "SDP", reason: "Computers in healthcare allow for remote diagnosis and treatment (Telemedicine)." },
  { question: "A 'Logic Bomb' is a type of computer threat that executes when:", options: ["The computer starts", "A specific event or date occurs", "The user types 'Bomb'", "The internet disconnects"], answer: "A specific event or date occurs", category: "SDP", reason: "Logic bombs are malicious code snippets that stay dormant until a trigger condition is met." },
  { question: "Which multimedia element is measured in 'Frames Per Second' (FPS)?", options: ["Text", "Graphics", "Video", "Audio"], answer: "Video", category: "SDP", reason: "Video quality and smoothness depend on the frequency of photographic frames displayed." },
  { question: "Which 'Wildcard' character is used to represent zero or more unknown characters in a file search?", options: ["?", "#", "*", "&"], answer: "*", category: "SDP", reason: "The asterisk (*) is a universal wildcard; '?' represents exactly one character." },
  { question: "To join a computer to a 'Domain' in a Microsoft Network, you generally need:", options: ["A printer", "A user account with administrative permissions in the domain", "A CD-ROM", "A faster monitor"], answer: "A user account with administrative permissions in the domain", category: "SDP", reason: "Domains are centralized server-managed networks that require authorized credentials to join." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of hosts in a standard Class C IPv4 network (excluding network and broadcast)?", options: ["2", "254", "65534", "16 million"], answer: "254", category: "SDP", reason: "A Class C block has 256 addresses; 1 is for network ID, 1 for broadcast, leaving 254 for hosts." },
  { question: "Which topology is considered the 'most robust' because every node is connected to multiple other nodes?", options: ["Star", "Bus", "Mesh", "Tree"], answer: "Mesh", category: "SDP", reason: "Mesh topology provides high redundancy; if one link fails, data takes an alternate path." },
  { question: "Which protocol is used for sending 'E-mail' between mail servers?", options: ["POP3", "IMAP", "SMTP", "HTTP"], answer: "SMTP", category: "SDP", reason: "Simple Mail Transfer Protocol (SMTP) is the standard for outgoing email transmission." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of an 'Antivirus' software?", options: ["To speed up the internet", "To detect, prevent, and remove malicious software", "To format the hard drive", "To build websites"], answer: "To detect, prevent, and remove malicious software", category: "SDP", reason: "Antivirus software monitors system files and activity to protect against malware." },
  { question: "In the IP address '192.168.1.1', which part is the 'First Octet'?", options: ["1", "168", "192", "The dot"], answer: "192", category: "SDP", reason: "IP addresses are read from left to right; the first block is the first octet." },
  { question: "What is 'Adware'?", options: ["Software that adds hardware", "Malware that displays unwanted advertisements on the user's screen", "Helpful software for designers", "A type of network cable"], answer: "Malware that displays unwanted advertisements on the user's screen", category: "SDP", reason: "Adware generates revenue for attackers by forcing pop-ups and ads on victims." },
  { question: "Which multimedia format is commonly used for uncompressed, high-quality audio?", options: [".mp3", ".wav", ".jpg", ".gif"], answer: ".wav", category: "SDP", reason: "WAV is a standard lossless/uncompressed audio format primarily for Windows." },
  { question: "What is the 'Pathname' of a file located in the 'Documents' folder on the C: drive?", options: ["C/Documents/file", "C:\\Documents\\file", "Documents:C\\file", "root/docs/file"], answer: "C:\\Documents\\file", category: "SDP", reason: "Windows pathnames use drive letters, colons, and backslashes as separators." },
  { question: "Which network utility allows you to see every router 'hop' taken by a packet to reach its destination?", options: ["PING", "IPCONFIG", "TRACERT", "NSLOOKUP"], answer: "TRACERT", category: "SDP", reason: "TRACERT (Trace Route) maps the network path step-by-step." },
  { question: "A 'Private' network using internet technology accessible only to employees is called a/an:", options: ["Internet", "Extranet", "Intranet", "Globalnet"], answer: "Intranet", category: "SDP", reason: "Intranets provide internal information sharing and collaboration for organizations." },
  { question: "What is a 'Subnet' technically?", options: ["A faster version of the internet", "A logical subdivision of an IP network", "A type of hardware switch", "A hidden webpage"], answer: "A logical subdivision of an IP network", category: "SDP", reason: "Subnetting improves network efficiency and management by grouping addresses." },
  { question: "Which network topology connects multiple 'Star' networks to a single 'Bus' backbone?", options: ["Mesh", "Ring", "Tree", "Hybrid"], answer: "Tree", category: "SDP", reason: "Tree topology is hierarchical, using a backbone to link different branch networks." },
  { question: "Which 'Protocol' is used to securely browse websites with encryption?", options: ["HTTP", "FTP", "HTTPS", "DNS"], answer: "HTTPS", category: "SDP", reason: "HTTPS (Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure) uses SSL/TLS to protect user data." },
  { question: "What is 'Spyware'?", options: ["Malware that deletes files", "Software that secretly records user activity and sends it to a third party", "Software for spying on competitors", "A type of firewall"], answer: "Software that secretly records user activity and sends it to a third party", category: "SDP", reason: "Spyware captures sensitive info like passwords or browsing history covertly." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'High-level' language mentioned in syllabus 1.2.3.2?", options: ["Binary", "Assembly", "Python", "Machine Language"], answer: "Python", category: "SDP", reason: "High-level languages are closer to human language; Machine and Assembly are low-level." },
  { question: "What is the result of binary addition '10 + 10'?", options: ["20", "100", "110", "01"], answer: "100", category: "SDP", reason: "In binary, 2+2=4. 4 is represented as 100." },
  { question: "Which 'Search Engine' is owned by Microsoft and often default in Edge browsers (1.7.4 context)?", options: ["Google", "Bing", "Yahoo", "Baidu"], answer: "Bing", category: "SDP", reason: "Bing is Microsoft's proprietary search engine." },
  { question: "What is a 'Trojan'?", options: ["A network cable", "Malware that hides inside a legitimate-looking program", "A type of computer screen", "A fast computer"], answer: "Malware that hides inside a legitimate-looking program", category: "SDP", reason: "Trojans mislead users of its true intent by appearing useful." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Remedy' is best for avoiding 'Phishing' scams?", options: ["Updating the monitor", "Checking the sender's actual email address and not clicking suspicious links", "Formatting the hard drive", "Buying a new CPU"], answer: "Checking the sender's actual email address and not clicking suspicious links", category: "SDP", reason: "User awareness is the primary defense against social engineering like phishing." },
  { question: "In 'Microsoft Network' (1.7.7), which button do you click to see other computers on the LAN?", options: ["Control Panel", "Network / Network Neighborhood", "MS Word", "Recycle Bin"], answer: "Network / Network Neighborhood", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'Network' icon in File Explorer displays reachable nodes on the same network." },
  { question: "What is the standard 'DPI' related to in multimedia graphics?", options: ["Data Per Inch", "Dots Per Inch", "Digital Picture Index", "Direct Pixel Input"], answer: "Dots Per Inch", category: "SDP", reason: "DPI measures the resolution and quality of printed or displayed images." },
  { question: "Which 'Number System' uses digits from 0 to 7 only?", options: ["Binary", "Octal", "Decimal", "Hexadecimal"], answer: "Octal", category: "SDP", reason: "Octal is base-8 counting." },
  { question: "Which network utility is used to query 'DNS' to find an IP address for a name?", options: ["IPCONFIG", "PING", "NSLOOKUP", "TRACERT"], answer: "NSLOOKUP", category: "SDP", reason: "NSLOOKUP is specifically for Domain Name System troubleshooting." },
  { question: "What is 'Digital Signature' primarily used for in network security (9.4)?", options: ["Drawing a name", "To ensure document authenticity and integrity", "To speed up the internet", "To hide the sender's identity"], answer: "To ensure document authenticity and integrity", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital signatures prove the identity of the signer and that the data hasn't been tampered with." },
  { question: "A 'Workstation' is best described as:", options: ["A very cheap computer", "A high-performance microcomputer designed for technical applications", "A computer with no CPU", "A server for 1 million users"], answer: "A high-performance microcomputer designed for technical applications", category: "SDP", reason: "Workstations are powerful PCs used for architecture, engineering, and data analysis." },
  { question: "Which 'Cloud service' allows users to sync their mobile data with a remote server (e.g. iCloud)?", options: ["LAN", "BIOS", "Cloud-based services", "RAM"], answer: "Cloud-based services", category: "SDP", reason: "Syllabus 8.9 specifically mentions iCloud as a cloud service provider." },
  { question: "What is the binary representation of decimal '3'?", options: ["10", "11", "101", "111"], answer: "11", category: "SDP", reason: "11 is (1x2) + (1x1) = 3." },
  { question: "In 'Microsoft Network' (1.7.7), what does 'Mapping a Network Drive' do?", options: ["Deletes a drive", "Assigns a drive letter (like Z:) to a shared folder on another PC", "Changes the computer name", "Formats the server"], answer: "Assigns a drive letter (like Z:) to a shared folder on another PC", category: "SDP", reason: "Mapping creates a shortcut to remote storage as if it were a local disk." },
  { question: "Which of the following is an 'Input Unit' for images?", options: ["Printer", "Plotter", "Scanner", "Monitor"], answer: "Scanner", category: "SDP", reason: "A scanner captures a physical image and converts it into digital data." },
  { question: "What is 'Bandwidth' measured in?", options: ["Hertz", "Bits per second (bps)", "Pixels", "Ohms"], answer: "Bits per second (bps)", category: "SDP", reason: "Bandwidth is the capacity rate of a network connection." },
  { question: "Which 'Topology' is easiest to expand but fails entirely if the main cable breaks?", options: ["Mesh", "Star", "Bus", "Ring"], answer: "Bus", category: "SDP", reason: "The backbone is a single point of failure in Bus topology." },
  { question: "What is 'Metadata' in the context of files?", options: ["Deleted data", "Information about a file (like size, type, and creation date)", "A type of virus", "The name of the monitor"], answer: "Information about a file (like size, type, and creation date)", category: "SDP", reason: "Metadata provides descriptive info about the actual data contents." },
  { question: "Which 'Number System' uses symbols from 0 to 9 and A to F?", options: ["Binary", "Octal", "Decimal", "Hexadecimal"], answer: "Hexadecimal", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal is base-16." },
  { question: "To change your 'IP Address' in Windows (1.7.5), you visit which setting area?", options: ["Recycle Bin", "MS Paint", "Network and Sharing Center -> Adapter Settings", "Character Map"], answer: "Network and Sharing Center -> Adapter Settings", category: "SDP", reason: "Logical network parameters are managed in the network adapter properties." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Threat' (1.4) locks your computer and demands money?", options: ["Spyware", "Adware", "Ransomware", "Worm"], answer: "Ransomware", category: "SDP", reason: "Ransomware targets availability and extorts victims for a key." },
  { question: "What does a '.pdf' file extension stand for?", options: ["Print Data File", "Portable Document Format", "Personal Digital Folder", "Portable Data File"], answer: "Portable Document Format", category: "SDP", reason: "PDF is a fixed-layout format for document sharing." },
  { question: "In 'Setting Up Microsoft Network' (1.7.7), what is a 'Password Protected Sharing' setting used for?", options: ["To speed up the network", "To ensure only authorized users can access shared resources", "To check the time", "To delete viruses"], answer: "To ensure only authorized users can access shared resources", category: "SDP", reason: "It acts as an access control layer for network folders." },
  { question: "What is the decimal equivalent of binary '101'?", options: ["3", "4", "5", "6"], answer: "5", category: "SDP", reason: "4 + 0 + 1 = 5." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Media' type for networking (1.7.6)?", options: ["SATA", "Twisted Pair (UTP)", "BIOS", "RAM"], answer: "Twisted Pair (UTP)", category: "SDP", reason: "UTP is the physical wire used for Ethernet LANs." },
  { question: "What does 'WWW' stand for?", options: ["World Wide Web", "Wide World Web", "Whole World Web", "Web World Wide"], answer: "World Wide Web", category: "SDP", reason: "WWW is the hypertext information system on the internet." },
  { question: "In 'Number Systems' (1.8.1), what is 'Base-10' called?", options: ["Binary", "Octal", "Decimal", "Hexadecimal"], answer: "Decimal", category: "SDP", reason: "Decimal is the standard human counting system." },
  { question: "Which of these is a component of 'Multimedia' (1.5)?", options: ["Text", "Audio", "Video", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "Multimedia integrates multiple content forms." },
  { question: "Which network utility shows the version of the computer's OS?", options: ["IPCONFIG", "VER", "DIR", "PING"], answer: "VER", category: "SDP", reason: "VER displays the Windows version string." },
  { question: "What is the 'Default Gateway' for most home networks?", options: ["The PC itself", "The Printer", "The Router", "Google.com"], answer: "The Router", category: "SDP", reason: "The router bridges the home LAN to the ISP." },
  { question: "A '.pptx' file extension indicates what type of file?", options: ["Word Document", "Excel Sheet", "PowerPoint Presentation", "Database"], answer: "PowerPoint Presentation", category: "SDP", reason: ".pptx is the standard XML format for PowerPoint." },
  { question: "What is the binary sum of '10 + 1'?", options: ["10", "11", "101", "1"], answer: "11", category: "SDP", reason: "2 + 1 = 3 (which is 11 in binary)." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Threat' (1.4) attaches to other files to spread?", options: ["Worm", "Trojan", "Virus", "Phishing"], answer: "Virus", category: "SDP", reason: "Viruses are parasitic and need a host file." },
  { question: "In 'Computer Room Setting' (1.3), why is 'Air Conditioning' important?", options: ["To keep the users cool", "To prevent hardware from overheating", "To make the computers run faster", "To save electricity"], answer: "To prevent hardware from overheating", category: "SDP", reason: "High temperatures lead to component failure." },
  { question: "Which network topology is used when all nodes are connected in a circle?", options: ["Star", "Mesh", "Bus", "Ring"], answer: "Ring", category: "SDP", reason: "Data travels from node to node in a closed loop in Ring topology." },
  { question: "What is a 'Bit'?", options: ["A hardware chip", "A software program", "The smallest unit of digital data (0 or 1)", "A type of network"], answer: "The smallest unit of digital data (0 or 1)", category: "SDP", reason: "Bits are the atoms of information in computing." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Cloud-based' backup service mentioned in 8.9?", options: ["RAM", "Dropbox", "Hard Drive", "BIOS"], answer: "Dropbox", category: "SDP", reason: "Dropbox allows files to be stored and accessed via the cloud." },
  { question: "To start a 'New Line' inside an Excel cell (4.5), you press:", options: ["Enter", "Alt + Enter", "Shift + Enter", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Alt + Enter", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt + Enter creates a manual line break within one cell." },
  { question: "Which 'Number System' is Base-16?", options: ["Binary", "Octal", "Decimal", "Hexadecimal"], answer: "Hexadecimal", category: "SDP", reason: "Hexadecimal uses 16 digits." },
  { question: "What does 'SRAM' stand for in memory (1.2.5)?", options: ["Simple RAM", "Static RAM", "Solid RAM", "System RAM"], answer: "Static RAM", category: "SDP", reason: "Static RAM is used for high-speed cache memory." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Threat' (1.4) records your browsing habits?", options: ["Ransomware", "Worm", "Spyware", "Trojan"], answer: "Spyware", category: "SDP", reason: "Spyware spies on user activity without their knowledge." },
  { question: "In 'Microsoft Network' (1.7.7), what does 'DHCP' do?", options: ["Deletes files", "Automatically assigns IP addresses to devices on the network", "Checks the time", "Speeds up the internet"], answer: "Automatically assigns IP addresses to devices on the network", category: "SDP", reason: "DHCP automates the network addressing process." },
  { question: "Convert the decimal '8' to binary.", options: ["100", "101", "111", "1000"], answer: "1000", category: "SDP", reason: "1 x 2³ = 8." },
  { question: "Which of these is 'Auxiliary Memory' (1.2.2.5)?", options: ["RAM", "Hard Disk", "Cache", "Register"], answer: "Hard Disk", category: "SDP", reason: "Auxiliary memory is permanent secondary storage." },
  { question: "What does '.zip' indicate?", options: ["A virus", "A compressed file archive", "A high-level language", "System firmware"], answer: "A compressed file archive", category: "SDP", reason: "ZIP files reduce storage size by bundling data." },
  { question: "What is the function of the 'Control Unit' in the CPU?", options: ["Perform addition", "Manage the instruction cycle and coordinate hardware", "Store large files", "Connect to a printer"], answer: "Manage the instruction cycle and coordinate hardware", category: "SDP", reason: "The CU manages the flow of data inside the processor." },
  { question: "Which network utility would you use to check the latency of 'www.google.com'?", options: ["IPCONFIG", "PING", "VER", "DIR"], answer: "PING", category: "SDP", reason: "PING reports round-trip time in milliseconds." },
  { question: "Which character standard (1.9) can represent characters from Ancient Greek and emojis?", options: ["ASCII", "Extended ASCII", "Unicode", "EBCDIC"], answer: "Unicode", category: "SDP", reason: "Unicode is the universal global character standard." },
  { question: "What is a 'Subnet Mask'?", options: ["To hide the computer's name", "To determine which part of an IP address is the Network and which is the Host", "To block viruses", "To assign a dynamic IP"], answer: "To determine which part of an IP address is the Network and which is the Host", category: "SDP", reason: "The mask defines the subnet boundaries." },
  { question: "Which topology requires a central switch or hub?", options: ["Bus", "Ring", "Star", "Mesh"], answer: "Star", category: "SDP", reason: "Star topology is the standard for modern LANs." },
  { question: "What is the binary representation of decimal '0'?", options: ["0", "1", "10", "11"], answer: "0", category: "SDP", reason: "Decimal 0 is 0 in all bases." },
  { question: "What is 'Liveware'?", options: ["Hardware that is on", "The humans involved in a computer system", "Software that works live", "Cables"], answer: "The humans involved in a computer system", category: "SDP", reason: "Liveware refers to the human component of IT." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Threat' (1.4) exploits human trust via fake websites?", options: ["Virus", "Worm", "Phishing", "Logic Bomb"], answer: "Phishing", category: "SDP", reason: "Phishing is a social engineering deception." },
  { question: "Which of the following is the primary goal of a presentation application like MS PowerPoint?", options: ["To manage accounting ledgers", "To create visual aids for effective communication and public speaking", "To design complex 3D games", "To host a web server"], answer: "To create visual aids for effective communication and public speaking", category: "SDP", reason: "PowerPoint is designed to provide visual support to a speaker through a sequence of slides." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint, what is a 'Slide'?", options: ["A document with 10 pages", "A single page of a presentation", "A spreadsheet grid", "A hardware component"], answer: "A single page of a presentation", category: "SDP", reason: "Slides are the individual workspaces where content is organized in a presentation." },
  { question: "Which PowerPoint feature is used to set a universal layout, font, and background for all slides in a deck?", options: ["Animation Pane", "Slide Master", "Transition Tab", "Handout Master"], answer: "Slide Master", category: "SDP", reason: "The Slide Master is the top-level template that stores information about the theme and layouts of a presentation." },
  { question: "To change the 'Background Style' of only the current slide, you use which feature?", options: ["Design Theme", "Format Background", "Slide Master", "Slide Layout"], answer: "Format Background", category: "SDP", reason: "The Format Background pane allows for granular control over fills, gradients, and images on a per-slide basis." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut is used to apply 'Bold' formatting to text on a slide?", options: ["Ctrl + B", "Ctrl + I", "Ctrl + U", "Ctrl + J"], answer: "Ctrl + B", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + B is the standard shortcut for bolding text across all Microsoft Office applications." },
  { question: "What does 'Formatting a Slide' involve?", options: ["Deleting the file", "Adjusting visual elements like background, alignment, fonts, and layouts", "Connecting to the internet", "Installing the OS"], answer: "Adjusting visual elements like background, alignment, fonts, and layouts", category: "SDP", reason: "Formatting refers to the customization of the appearance of the slide content." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Database Index' primary advantage?", options: ["It reduces the disk space used", "It speeds up data retrieval and searching", "It makes the database colorful", "It deletes duplicate records automatically"], answer: "It speeds up data retrieval and searching", category: "SDP", reason: "Indexing works like the index in a book, allowing the DBMS to find records without scanning the entire table." },
  { question: "What is the main drawback of adding an 'Index' to every single field in a table?", options: ["The computer will crash", "It slows down data entry and updates (Insert/Update operations)", "It makes the font smaller", "It hides the data"], answer: "It slows down data entry and updates (Insert/Update operations)", category: "SDP", reason: "The DBMS must update the index every time a record is modified, which adds overhead to data entry." },
  { question: "Which type of Index in a database ensures that no two records can have the same value in a specific field?", options: ["Clustered Index", "Unique Index", "Secondary Index", "Non-clustered Index"], answer: "Unique Index", category: "SDP", reason: "A Unique index prevents duplicate values in the indexed column, often used for Primary Keys." },
  { question: "Which database object is used to 'Modify' data in an existing table in bulk?", options: ["Select Query", "Update Query", "Form", "Report"], answer: "Update Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Update queries are 'Action' queries designed to change values in multiple records simultaneously." },
  { question: "To 'permanently remove' a table structure and its data from a database, which action is performed?", options: ["Hide Table", "Clear Table", "Delete Table", "Format Table"], answer: "Delete Table", category: "SDP", reason: "Deleting a table removes both the metadata (schema) and the actual records from the file." },
  { question: "Which database object provides a 'User Interface' for navigating and entering records one at a time?", options: ["Query", "Table", "Form", "Report"], answer: "Form", category: "SDP", reason: "Forms act as digital versions of paper forms, simplifying user interaction with raw table data." },
  { question: "A 'Report' in a database is primarily used for:", options: ["Entering data", "Managing relationships", "Formatting data for printing and summaries", "Creating new tables"], answer: "Formatting data for printing and summaries", category: "SDP", reason: "Reports are specialized for presentation and final output, supporting grouping and totaling." },
  { question: "Which component is used to 'Automate' repetitive tasks in MS Access, like opening a form when a button is clicked?", options: ["Query", "Macro", "Index", "Relationship"], answer: "Macro", category: "SDP", reason: "Macros are small programs used to automate a series of actions within the database application." },
  { question: "What is the first step in creating a database 'Query' in Design View?", options: ["Setting the font", "Adding the relevant tables to the query pane", "Printing the result", "Setting a password"], answer: "Adding the relevant tables to the query pane", category: "SDP", reason: "You must first specify which tables the query will pull information from." },
  { question: "Which of the following describes the concept of an 'Electronic Spreadsheet'?", options: ["A tool for editing videos", "A computer program used for organization, analysis, and storage of data in tabular form", "A system for managing network protocols", "A digital drawing board"], answer: "A computer program used for organization, analysis, and storage of data in tabular form", category: "SDP", reason: "Spreadsheets (like Excel) provide a dynamic grid for calculations and data management." },
  { question: "Which type of spreadsheet is 'open-source' and a popular alternative to MS Excel?", options: ["Google Sheets", "VisiCalc", "LibreOffice Calc", "Lotus 1-2-3"], answer: "LibreOffice Calc", category: "SDP", reason: "LibreOffice Calc is the most well-known free/open-source spreadsheet software." },
  { question: "What is an Excel 'Workbook'?", options: ["A single grid of cells", "A file containing one or more worksheets", "A printout of a chart", "A type of database primary key"], answer: "A file containing one or more worksheets", category: "SDP", reason: "The Workbook is the entire Excel file (.xlsx), while Worksheets are the individual tabs within it." },
  { question: "Which area of the Excel screen shows the 'address' of the active cell (e.g., C10)?", options: ["Formula Bar", "Status Bar", "Name Box", "Title Bar"], answer: "Name Box", category: "SDP", reason: "The Name Box, located to the left of the formula bar, identifies the coordinates of the selected cell." },
  { question: "The horizontal and vertical bars used to view data beyond the screen's boundary are called:", options: ["Title bars", "Scrollbars", "Toolbars", "Status bars"], answer: "Scrollbars", category: "SDP", reason: "Scrollbars allow navigation within large spreadsheets that do not fit in the current window." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut is used to 'Open' an existing workbook?", options: ["Ctrl + O", "Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + W"], answer: "Ctrl + O", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + O (Open) is the standard shortcut to access the file selection menu." },
  { question: "How do you 'Customize' the Quick Access Toolbar (QAT) in Excel?", options: ["By deleting the ribbon", "By clicking the small dropdown arrow on the toolbar", "By formatting a cell", "By clearing the RAM"], answer: "By clicking the small dropdown arrow on the toolbar", category: "SDP", reason: "The dropdown arrow allows users to add or remove their most frequently used commands." },
  { question: "Where can you change the 'Default number of sheets' for every new workbook you create?", options: ["Page Layout tab", "Excel Options -> General", "Review tab", "Formula bar"], answer: "Excel Options -> General", category: "SDP", reason: "Global application preferences are managed within the 'Excel Options' dialog." },
  { question: "Which 'View' in PowerPoint allows you to see small pictures of every slide to help reorganize the deck?", options: ["Outline View", "Slide Sorter View", "Normal View", "Reading View"], answer: "Slide Sorter View", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Sorter provides an overview of the presentation's structure as thumbnails." },
  { question: "To add an 'Entrance' animation to a text box, you must visit which tab?", options: ["Design", "Transitions", "Animations", "Layout"], answer: "Animations", category: "SDP", reason: "The Animations tab manages motion effects for objects 'inside' a slide." },
  { question: "Which database command is used to 'add a new record' to a table?", options: ["Update", "Append / Insert", "Format", "Delete"], answer: "Append / Insert", category: "SDP", reason: "Inserting a row adds new data to the existing table structure." },
  { question: "In an Excel worksheet, columns are identified by ______ and rows by ______.", options: ["Numbers, Letters", "Letters, Numbers", "Colors, Symbols", "Dots, Dashes"], answer: "Letters, Numbers", category: "SDP", reason: "Columns are alphabetical (A, B, C...) and rows are numeric (1, 2, 3...)." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Save' an Excel workbook?", options: ["Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + Shift + S", "Alt + S", "Ctrl + F12"], answer: "Ctrl + S", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + S is the universal command for saving file progress." },
  { question: "Which element of the Excel environment allows you to edit the underlying formula of a cell?", options: ["Status Bar", "Name Box", "Formula Bar", "Ribbon"], answer: "Formula Bar", category: "SDP", reason: "The Formula Bar shows exactly what was typed into the cell, whether a value or a calculation." },
  { question: "What does a 'Red wavy underline' on a word in PowerPoint indicate?", options: ["Formatting error", "Spelling error", "Animation error", "A link"], answer: "Spelling error", category: "SDP", reason: "PowerPoint uses the built-in dictionary to flag misspelled words with red underlines." },
  { question: "To center a selected image horizontally on a PowerPoint slide, you use the ______ tools.", options: ["Design", "Picture Format -> Align", "Transitions", "Slide Master"], answer: "Picture Format -> Align", category: "SDP", reason: "The Align menu provides precise positioning options for graphical objects." },
  { question: "Which type of 'Relationship' would exist between a 'State' and its 'Capital City'?", options: ["One-to-Many", "Many-to-Many", "One-to-One", "No relationship"], answer: "One-to-One", category: "SDP", reason: "In a logical database, one state has exactly one capital, and one capital belongs to exactly one state." },
  { question: "To add a 'Footer' to your Excel sheets that shows the date when printed, you visit:", options: ["Page Layout tab", "Insert -> Header & Footer", "Data -> Filter", "Review -> Protect"], answer: "Insert -> Header & Footer", category: "SDP", reason: "Headers and Footers are categorized as text-based insertion objects." },
  { question: "What is 'VisiCalc' famous for?", options: ["It was the first modern Operating System", "It was the first commercially successful spreadsheet program", "It was a type of hardware", "It was a virus"], answer: "It was the first commercially successful spreadsheet program", category: "SDP", reason: "VisiCalc is widely credited with making microcomputers useful for business." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Database Object' is primarily used to summarize and calculate totals from a table?", options: ["Form", "Report", "Query", "Relationship"], answer: "Report", category: "SDP", reason: "Reports are specifically designed to organize data into summaries and totals for output." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key 'Selects the entire Worksheet' in Excel?", options: ["Ctrl + A", "Ctrl + Shift + S", "Alt + A", "Ctrl + Space"], answer: "Ctrl + A", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + A is the universal Select All command." },
  { question: "To create a 'Cycle' diagram showing a continuous loop in PowerPoint, which tool is best?", options: ["WordArt", "Chart", "SmartArt", "Table"], answer: "SmartArt", category: "SDP", reason: "SmartArt contains logical graphic layouts like Cycles, Hierarchies, and Processes." },
  { question: "In a database, a 'Record' is another name for a ______.", options: ["Column", "Field", "Row / Tuple", "Header"], answer: "Row / Tuple", category: "SDP", reason: "Records are horizontal entries representing a single instance of an object in a table." },
  { question: "What happens if you delete a 'Macro' that a button was programmed to run?", options: ["The button is also deleted", "The button stays, but it will show an error or do nothing when clicked", "The computer restarts", "The table is deleted"], answer: "The button stays, but it will show an error or do nothing when clicked", category: "SDP", reason: "The link between the UI element and the automated instruction is broken if the macro is removed." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Cloud-based' spreadsheet?", options: ["MS Excel Desktop", "Google Sheets", "VisiCalc", "Lotus 1-2-3"], answer: "Google Sheets", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Sheets is a pure web-based application that saves data directly to the cloud." },
  { question: "In Excel, 'A1:D10' represents a ______.", options: ["Cell Address", "Worksheet Name", "Range", "Workbook"], answer: "Range", category: "SDP", reason: "A range is a collection of two or more cells defined by its top-left and bottom-right coordinates." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Rows' in an Excel 2010 worksheet?", options: ["65,536", "1,048,576", "16,384", "Unlimited"], answer: "1,048,576", category: "SDP", reason: "Modern Excel versions expanded row capacity to over a million." },
  { question: "Which function key is used to start the 'Slide Show' from the very first slide?", options: ["F2", "F5", "F7", "F11"], answer: "F5", category: "SDP", reason: "F5 is the standard global shortcut for launching a presentation." },
  { question: "Which specific attribute of a database field ensures no 'Null' or empty values are allowed?", options: ["Indexed", "Required", "Caption", "Input Mask"], answer: "Required", category: "SDP", reason: "The Required property enforces data entry into that specific field." },
  { question: "To see how a document will look before you print it in Excel, you use:", options: ["Draft view", "Print Preview", "Reading view", "Outline view"], answer: "Print Preview", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Preview allows users to check margins and alignment to save paper." },
  { question: "Which 'Alignment' setting in Excel allows you to orient text diagonally (e.g. 45 degrees)?", options: ["Wrap Text", "Shrink to Fit", "Orientation", "Merge"], answer: "Orientation", category: "SDP", reason: "Orientation controls allow for rotating text within a cell." },
  { question: "What does a 'Circular Reference' error in Excel mean?", options: ["The file is too round", "A formula refers back to its own cell", "The data is missing", "The chart is a pie"], answer: "A formula refers back to its own cell", category: "SDP", reason: "This creates an infinite loop where the calculation cannot be finalized." },
  { question: "Which view is the 'default' workspace for editing slides in PowerPoint?", options: ["Normal View", "Slide Sorter", "Outline View", "Slide Master"], answer: "Normal View", category: "SDP", reason: "Normal view provides the slide area, navigation pane, and notes pane together." },
  { question: "Which database object is most suitable for 'Searching' for a subset of records based on a specific criteria?", options: ["Table", "Form", "Query", "Report"], answer: "Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Queries act as logic-based filters for the entire database." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Redo' an action in MS Excel?", options: ["Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + Y", "Ctrl + R", "Ctrl + P"], answer: "Ctrl + Y", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Y reverses an Undo or repeats the last command." },
  { question: "Which type of 'Database relationship' requires a third table (Junction table) to work correctly?", options: ["One-to-One", "One-to-Many", "Many-to-Many", "None"], answer: "Many-to-Many", category: "SDP", reason: "Many-to-Many links are resolved by breaking them into two One-to-Many relationships via an intermediary table." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint, what is the file extension of a 'Slide Show' file that plays directly when clicked?", options: [".pptx", ".ppsx", ".potx", ".pptm"], answer: ".ppsx", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'PowerPoint Show' format bypassing the editor." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Spreadsheet Environment' part allows for quick navigation by typing a cell address directly?", options: ["Formula Bar", "Status Bar", "Name Box", "Quick Access Toolbar"], answer: "Name Box", category: "SDP", reason: "Typing 'Z100' in the Name Box and pressing Enter jumps the selection instantly to that cell." },
  { question: "To add a password to an MS Access database, you look in which tab?", options: ["Review", "External Data", "File -> Info -> Encrypt with Password", "Create"], answer: "File -> Info -> Encrypt with Password", category: "SDP", reason: "Security and encryption settings are part of the file-level 'Backstage View'." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of 'Word Wrap' in an Excel cell?", options: ["Deleting text", "Displaying long text on multiple lines within a single cell", "Calculating sums", "Adding a link"], answer: "Displaying long text on multiple lines within a single cell", category: "SDP", reason: "Wrap text increases row height to accommodate longer strings within a column's width." },
  { question: "Which function key triggers the 'Help' window in Excel?", options: ["F1", "F2", "F5", "F7"], answer: "F1", category: "SDP", reason: "F1 is the universal help shortcut for almost all Windows software." },
  { question: "In a database table, a single 'Column' is referred to as a ______.", options: ["Record", "Field", "Row", "Key"], answer: "Field", category: "SDP", reason: "Fields define the specific data categories for every record in the table." },
  { question: "To start a Slide Show from the 'Current Slide', the shortcut is:", options: ["F5", "Shift + F5", "Alt + F5", "Ctrl + F5"], answer: "Shift + F5", category: "SDP", reason: "Shift + F5 allows for previewing just the section being worked on." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' in Excel allows you to set the vertical or horizontal orientation?", options: ["Margins", "Size", "Orientation", "Scaling"], answer: "Orientation", category: "SDP", reason: "Orientation allows for Portrait or Landscape layouts." },
  { question: "What does 'SQL' stand for?", options: ["Structured Query Language", "Standard Query Link", "Simple Queue Logic", "System Question Language"], answer: "Structured Query Language", category: "SDP", reason: "SQL is the standard language for interacting with relational databases." },
  { question: "Which feature in MS Excel helps you find a target result by automatically adjusting an input value?", options: ["Filter", "Goal Seek", "Sort", "AutoFill"], answer: "Goal Seek", category: "SDP", reason: "Goal Seek is a specific 'What-If' tool for solving for a single variable." },
  { question: "In 'Customizing the Ribbon', what is a 'Group'?", options: ["A set of users", "A set of commands within a tab", "A collection of workbooks", "A type of chart"], answer: "A set of commands within a tab", category: "SDP", reason: "Tabs are made up of groups (like the Font or Alignment group)." },
  { question: "To make text appear 'Bold' in an HTML based web presentation (Topic 7 cross), you use:", options: ["<bold>", "<b>", "<strong>", "Both B and C"], answer: "Both B and C", category: "SDP", reason: "In HTML, both tags are used for bolding, though <strong> is semantically preferred." },
  { question: "Which database property provides a 'Mask' to guide users into entering data in a specific pattern (e.g. phone number)?", options: ["Validation Rule", "Input Mask", "Caption", "Indexed"], answer: "Input Mask", category: "SDP", reason: "Input Masks restrict data entry to a pre-defined template." },
  { question: "The 'Status Bar' in Excel displays the 'Average' and 'Sum' of a selected range automatically. This feature is called:", options: ["AutoSum", "AutoCalculate", "AutoFill", "AutoFormat"], answer: "AutoCalculate", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel provides live statistical summaries on the status bar for any numeric selection." },
  { question: "Which view is used to define 'Field Names' and 'Data Types' for a new table?", options: ["Datasheet view", "Design view", "Pivot view", "SQL view"], answer: "Design view", category: "SDP", reason: "Design view is the blueprint/structural mode of a database table." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key 'Duplicates' a selected shape on a PowerPoint slide?", options: ["Ctrl + C", "Ctrl + D", "Ctrl + X", "Alt + D"], answer: "Ctrl + D", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + D (Duplicate) is faster than copy and paste as it creates and places the copy in one step." },
  { question: "Which specific tool allows for 'Filtering' data using checkboxes at the top of columns?", options: ["Advanced Filter", "AutoFilter", "Validation", "Pivot"], answer: "AutoFilter", category: "SDP", reason: "AutoFilter adds dropdown buttons to headers for quick data sorting and filtering." },
  { question: "What is the maximum number of 'Undo' levels in MS Excel 2010 by default?", options: ["10", "50", "100", "Unlimited"], answer: "100", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel 2010 supports up to 100 levels of undo/redo actions." },
  { question: "To add a 'Watermark' to all slides in a presentation, you should modify the:", options: ["First Slide", "Slide Sorter", "Slide Master", "Animation Pane"], answer: "Slide Master", category: "SDP", reason: "Items placed on the master slide are inherited by the entire deck." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Proportional' chart in Excel?", options: ["Bar Chart", "Line Chart", "Pie Chart", "Scatter Plot"], answer: "Pie Chart", category: "SDP", reason: "Pie charts show how parts relate to a whole 100% total." },
  { question: "What does a 'Foreign Key' do in a database?", options: ["It unlocks a different database file", "It refers to the primary key of another table to link them", "It calculates averages", "It hides records"], answer: "It refers to the primary key of another table to link them", category: "SDP", reason: "Foreign keys are the mechanism for building relational links between tables." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Setting' allows row 1 to appear at the top of every physical printed page?", options: ["Freeze Panes", "Print Titles", "Header", "Margins"], answer: "Print Titles", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Titles (Page Setup) is the specific setting to repeat headers on paper output." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key increases font size to the 'Next' size in the dropdown list?", options: ["Ctrl + ]", "Ctrl + Shift + >", "Ctrl + Shift + +", "Alt + >"], answer: "Ctrl + Shift + >", category: "SDP", reason: "This is the standard shortcut to jump between the default size increments (e.g. 11 to 12)." },
  { question: "What happens if 'Referential Integrity' is enforced and you try to delete a record that is being used in another table?", options: ["The record is deleted", "The computer restarts", "The DBMS blocks the deletion with an error", "The table structure is deleted"], answer: "The DBMS blocks the deletion with an error", category: "SDP", reason: "It prevents the creation of 'orphaned' records that have no valid parent." },
  { question: "Which tool would you use to 'Predict' a future value in Excel using a set of historical data?", options: ["Forecast", "Sort", "Filter", "Validation"], answer: "Forecast", category: "SDP", reason: "Forecasting functions use existing trends to calculate future results." },
  { question: "To add 'Numbered or Bulleted Lists' in PowerPoint, you look in which group of the Home tab?", options: ["Font", "Paragraph", "Slides", "Editing"], answer: "Paragraph", category: "SDP", reason: "List formatting tools are located in the Paragraph section." },
  { question: "A 'Database Schema' refers to:", options: ["The actual data", "The logical description of the whole database structure", "The file size", "The number of users"], answer: "The logical description of the whole database structure", category: "SDP", reason: "The schema is the blueprint of how tables, fields, and keys are organized." },
  { question: "Which mathematical symbol represents 'Modulo' (remainder) in many programming contexts, though Excel uses a function?", options: ["/", "%", "^", "*"], answer: "%", category: "SDP", reason: "While Excel uses =MOD(), the '%' symbol is the modulo operator in languages like C/Java." },
  { question: "To hide a 'Column' in Excel, you right-click the header and select:", options: ["Delete", "Hide", "Format", "Clear"], answer: "Hide", category: "SDP", reason: "Hiding keeps the data in the file but makes it invisible on the screen." },
  { question: "Which of the following is NOT an MS Office application?", options: ["Access", "PowerPoint", "Notepad", "Excel"], answer: "Notepad", category: "SDP", reason: "Notepad is a basic Windows accessory, not part of the Office productivity suite." },
  { question: "In a database Query, 'Criteria' refers to:", options: ["The font used", "The conditions used to filter records", "The number of tables", "The size of the primary key"], answer: "The conditions used to filter records", category: "SDP", reason: "Criteria rows tell the query which data to look for (e.g. '>1000')." },
  { question: "What is the result of '=AVERAGE(10, \"Apple\", 20)'?", options: ["15", "#VALUE!", "30", "10"], answer: "15", category: "SDP", reason: "The AVERAGE function ignores text strings within its arguments list." },
  { question: "The 'Notes Pane' in PowerPoint is used for:", options: ["Designing graphics", "Writing text the presenter can see on their monitor but the audience cannot", "Adding transitions", "Scanning for viruses"], answer: "Writing text the presenter can see on their monitor but the audience cannot", category: "SDP", reason: "Notes are for speaker cues in 'Presenter View'." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Database Object' organizes data into a grid format like an Excel sheet?", options: ["Table (Datasheet view)", "Report", "Form", "Macro"], answer: "Table (Datasheet view)", category: "SDP", reason: "Datasheet view is the default spreadsheet-like interface for database tables." },
  { question: "To 'Import' a text file into Excel using a wizard, you use which tab?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Data", "Review"], answer: "Data", category: "SDP", reason: "Data tools like 'From Text/CSV' are in the Data tab." },
  { question: "Which shortcut 'Paints' the formatting of one object to another?", options: ["Ctrl + C", "Ctrl + Shift + C", "Format Painter", "Both B and C"], answer: "Both B and C", category: "SDP", reason: "Format Painter is the icon; Ctrl+Shift+C is the keyboard shortcut for copying formats." },
  { question: "What does a '#####' appearing in an Excel cell signify?", options: ["Formula error", "Negative date or number too wide for column", "Cell is deleted", "Internet error"], answer: "Negative date or number too wide for column", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a visual notification that the physical space is too small for the numeric data." },
  { question: "Which specific 'View' allows you to edit the text outline of a presentation?", options: ["Normal", "Slide Sorter", "Outline View", "Reading view"], answer: "Outline View", category: "SDP", reason: "Outline view focuses purely on titles and body text hierarchy." },
  { question: "Which database property specifies a 'Validation Message' if the entry is wrong?", options: ["Validation Rule", "Validation Text", "Caption", "Required"], answer: "Validation Text", category: "SDP", reason: "Validation Text is the custom error message shown to users." },
  { question: "To select all 'non-adjacent' cells in Excel, hold which key?", options: ["Shift", "Alt", "Ctrl", "Spacebar"], answer: "Ctrl", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl allows for the selection of disjointed ranges." },
  { question: "What is the maximum 'Rows' in a single Excel sheet (Modern versions)?", options: ["65,536", "1,048,576", "16,384", "Unlimited"], answer: "1,048,576", category: "SDP", reason: "Since .xlsx (Excel 2007+), the grid size is 1,048,576 rows." },
  { question: "Which 'Animation' category cause an object to 'leave' the slide?", options: ["Entrance", "Emphasis", "Exit", "Motion Path"], answer: "Exit", category: "SDP", reason: "Exit animations control how objects vanish from view." },
  { question: "Which database key uniquely identifies a record when there is no natural one available?", options: ["Primary Key", "Surrogate Key (AutoNumber)", "Foreign Key", "Secondary Key"], answer: "Surrogate Key (AutoNumber)", category: "SDP", reason: "Surrogate keys are system-generated IDs used purely for record identity." },
  { question: "To start a 'new line' in an Excel cell, press:", options: ["Enter", "Shift + Enter", "Alt + Enter", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Alt + Enter", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt + Enter is the manual carriage return for cells." },
  { question: "Which chart type is best for showing 'trends over time'?", options: ["Pie Chart", "Line Chart", "Bar Chart", "Scatter Plot"], answer: "Line Chart", category: "SDP", reason: "Line charts connect points to show progress or change over a period." },
  { question: "In a database table, an 'Attribute' refers to a:", options: ["Record", "Field / Column", "Row", "Key"], answer: "Field / Column", category: "SDP", reason: "Attribute is the technical relational term for a column." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to start a Slide Show from the 'Current Slide'?", options: ["F5", "Shift + F5", "Alt + F5", "Ctrl + F5"], answer: "Shift + F5", category: "SDP", reason: "Shift + F5 allows for previewing only the current part of the show." },
  { question: "Which Excel tab contains the 'Filter' command?", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Data", "Review"], answer: "Data", category: "SDP", reason: "While basic sorting is on Home, comprehensive Data management is in the Data tab." },
  { question: "What error message appears in Excel if a formula refers to a deleted cell?", options: ["#VALUE!", "#REF!", "#NAME?", "#DIV/0!"], answer: "#REF!", category: "SDP", reason: "#REF! indicates a broken cell reference." },
  { question: "Which 'Presentation View' shows the slide exactly as the audience will see it on the full screen?", options: ["Normal", "Slide Sorter", "Reading View", "Slide Show View"], answer: "Slide Show View", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Show is the final full-screen output mode." },
  { question: "Which database key links a 'Child' table to a 'Parent' table?", options: ["Primary Key", "Foreign Key", "Master Key", "Common Key"], answer: "Foreign Key", category: "SDP", reason: "The foreign key in the child refers to the primary key in the parent." },
  { question: "To 'Freeze' the top row of a spreadsheet, you use which tab?", options: ["Home", "Page Layout", "View", "Data"], answer: "View", category: "SDP", reason: "Freeze Panes is a window management tool found in the View tab." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint, 'Transitions' are applied to ______.", options: ["Objects", "The whole slide as it enters", "Audio files", "Passwords"], answer: "The whole slide as it enters", category: "SDP", reason: "Transitions are animations of the 'slides' themselves, not items on the slide." },
  { question: "Which of these is a 'Logical' Excel function?", options: ["=SUM()", "=IF()", "=MAX()", "=AVERAGE()"], answer: "=IF()", category: "SDP", reason: "IF tests a condition for a true/false result." },
  { question: "To add a 'Header' to a printed Excel report, go to:", options: ["Insert tab -> Header & Footer", "Data tab -> Header", "View tab -> Header", "Review tab -> Header"], answer: "Insert tab -> Header & Footer", category: "SDP", reason: "Headers and footers are part of the 'Text' group in the Insert tab." },
  { question: "What is the maximum 'Columns' in Excel (Modern versions)?", options: ["256", "1024", "16,384", "65,536"], answer: "16,384", category: "SDP", reason: "Column labels go from A to XFD (16,384)." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Database Object' organizes data for final presentation and printing?", options: ["Form", "Query", "Table", "Report"], answer: "Report", category: "SDP", reason: "Reports are formatted objects intended for printable summaries." },
  { question: "Which specific environment element in Excel shows the 'Current Zoom' percentage?", options: ["Formula bar", "Status bar", "Name box", "Title bar"], answer: "Status bar", category: "SDP", reason: "The Status bar (bottom right) contains the zoom slider and percentage." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint, what are 'Thumbnails'?", options: ["Small pictures", "Small versions of the slides in the navigation pane", "Type of animation", "Mouse clicks"], answer: "Small versions of the slides in the navigation pane", category: "SDP", reason: "Thumbnails allow you to see the sequence and content of slides at a glance." },
  { question: "Which database property restricts characters for a specific entry format (e.g. 000-000)?", options: ["Validation", "Input Mask", "Caption", "Required"], answer: "Input Mask", category: "SDP", reason: "Input masks provide a template to guide user input." },
  { question: "To select all 'Rows' in an Excel sheet, you click the intersection box at the top-left or press:", options: ["Ctrl + A", "Shift + Space", "Ctrl + Space", "Alt + A"], answer: "Ctrl + A", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + A selects the whole worksheet grid." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut key to check 'Spelling' in PowerPoint?", options: ["F5", "F7", "F12", "F2"], answer: "F7", category: "SDP", reason: "F7 is the universal Microsoft Office shortcut for spell-check." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Spreadsheet environment' part displays the coordinates of the current cell?", options: ["Formula bar", "Name box", "Status bar", "Title bar"], answer: "Name box", category: "SDP", reason: "The Name Box identifies the location of the selector." },
  { question: "To add an 'Emphasis' animation (pulsing) to an image already on the slide, you use:", options: ["Entrance", "Emphasis", "Exit", "Path"], answer: "Emphasis", category: "SDP", reason: "Emphasis effects draw attention to items already present on the slide." },
  { question: "Which database object provides an 'interface' for data entry?", options: ["Table", "Form", "Report", "Query"], answer: "Form", category: "SDP", reason: "Forms act as a screen layout for user-data interaction." },
  { question: "The 'Format Painter' icon looks like which object?", options: ["A pen", "A paintbrush", "A hammer", "A camera"], answer: "A paintbrush", category: "SDP", reason: "The paintbrush represents applying a visual 'coat' of formatting to new data." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'duplicate' a slide in the slides pane?", options: ["Ctrl + C", "Ctrl + D", "Ctrl + M", "Alt + D"], answer: "Ctrl + D", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + D is the duplicate command for objects and slides." },
  { question: "Which database key is uniquely identifying but not the Primary key?", options: ["Foreign Key", "Candidate Key", "Secondary Key", "Master Key"], answer: "Candidate Key", category: "SDP", reason: "A candidate key is a column that 'could' be a primary key because it is unique." },
  { question: "What is the result of '=SUM(10, 20, \"Cat\")'?", options: ["30", "#VALUE!", "0", "10"], answer: "30", category: "SDP", reason: "The SUM function ignores text strings within its arguments." },
  { question: "To 'Group' two shapes together in PowerPoint, press:", options: ["Ctrl + G", "Ctrl + K", "Ctrl + L", "Ctrl + M"], answer: "Ctrl + G", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + G combines selected items into a single unit." },
  { question: "Which view allows you to see 'Page Boundaries' in Excel while editing?", options: ["Normal", "Page Layout", "Page Break Preview", "Outline"], answer: "Page Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Page Layout view shows the physical paper sheets." },
  { question: "What is the 'Default' horizontal alignment for Text in Excel?", options: ["Left", "Right", "Center", "Justified"], answer: "Left", category: "SDP", reason: "Excel aligns characters to the left and numbers to the right by default." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Chart' is best for showing 'Scatter' correlations?", options: ["Pie", "Line", "Scatter (XY)", "Bar"], answer: "Scatter (XY)", category: "SDP", reason: "Scatter charts plot points based on coordinate values for two numerical axes." },
  { question: "What is 'Alt + Enter' used for in an Excel cell?", options: ["Saving", "Adding a new line within the same cell", "Calculating sum", "Printing"], answer: "Adding a new line within the same cell", category: "SDP", reason: "Alt + Enter creates a manual carriage return inside a cell." },
  { question: "Which database object asks a user for criteria (like a date) before running?", options: ["Table", "Select Query", "Parameter Query", "Form"], answer: "Parameter Query", category: "SDP", reason: "Parameter queries use prompt boxes to gather criteria at runtime." },
  { question: "To see 'Thumbnail' versions of all slides on one screen, use the ______ View.", options: ["Notes", "Master", "Slide Sorter", "Normal"], answer: "Slide Sorter", category: "SDP", reason: "Slide Sorter view provides a grid overview of the entire presentation." },
  { question: "Which function key triggers the 'Save As' menu in Excel?", options: ["F1", "F5", "F7", "F12"], answer: "F12", category: "SDP", reason: "F12 is the standard 'Save As' shortcut in MS Office." },
  { question: "In a database table, a 'Field Name' cannot be longer than how many characters in Access?", options: ["32", "64", "255", "Unlimited"], answer: "64", category: "SDP", reason: "Access limits field names to 64 characters." },
  { question: "Which alignment stretches text to fit the whole width of the cell (from margin to margin)?", options: ["Left", "Center", "Right", "Justify"], answer: "Justify", category: "SDP", reason: "Justification distributes space between words to create straight edges." },
  { question: "What does a 'Red triangle' in the corner of an Excel cell indicate?", options: ["Error", "Hidden formula", "Cell Comment / Note", "Protected cell"], answer: "Cell Comment / Note", category: "SDP", reason: "A small red indicator shows that a developer or user has added a popup note to that cell." },
  { question: "In PowerPoint, visual effects that play 'Between' slides are called ______.", options: ["Animations", "Transitions", "Styles", "Themes"], answer: "Transitions", category: "SDP", reason: "Transitions are the animations of the slide handover." },
  { question: "Which database property provides a 'label' for a field that differs from the technical name?", options: ["Format", "Caption", "Required", "Indexed"], answer: "Caption", category: "SDP", reason: "Captions allow technical names like 'Emp_Name' to appear as 'Employee Name' on forms." },
  { question: "To select an entire 'Column' in Excel, press:", options: ["Shift + Space", "Ctrl + Space", "Alt + Space", "Ctrl + A"], answer: "Ctrl + Space", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Space highlights the whole column; Shift + Space highlights the whole row." },
  { question: "What is the file extension of a 'Word template'?", options: [".docx", ".docm", ".dotx", ".rtf"], answer: ".dotx", category: "SDP", reason: "Non-macro template files use .dotx (Word) or .potx (PowerPoint)." },
  { question: "Which chart component serves as a 'Key' to the colors used?", options: ["Axis", "Data label", "Legend", "Plot area"], answer: "Legend", category: "SDP", reason: "The legend identifies which data belongs to which series." },
  { question: "To start a 'New Presentation' in PowerPoint, press:", options: ["Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + M", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Ctrl + N", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + N creates a new file; Ctrl + M adds a new slide to the current file." },
  { question: "Which database key refers to the Primary key of 'another' table?", options: ["Primary Key", "Foreign Key", "Shared Key", "Master Key"], answer: "Foreign Key", category: "SDP", reason: "Foreign keys establish links between different entities." },
  { question: "Which feature in Excel summarizes data using 'Total' rows in groups?", options: ["Filter", "Sort", "Subtotal", "Consolidate"], answer: "Subtotal", category: "SDP", reason: "Subtotal tool automates grouping and summation calculations." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Undo' in all MS Office apps?", options: ["Ctrl + U", "Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + X", "Ctrl + P"], answer: "Ctrl + Z", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Z reverses the most recent change." },
  { question: "Which database view is the 'blueprint' for the table structure?", options: ["Datasheet", "Design", "Pivot", "Layout"], answer: "Design", category: "SDP", reason: "Design view is where fields and data types are defined." },
  { question: "What is the base of 'Binary'?", options: ["2", "8", "10", "16"], answer: "2", category: "SDP", reason: "Binary uses digits 0 and 1." },
  { question: "Which Windows element is used to change system-level settings like user accounts, display, and hardware configurations?", options: ["My Computer", "Recycle Bin", "Control Panel", "Windows Explorer"], answer: "Control Panel", category: "SDP", reason: "The Control Panel is the centralized management hub for the Windows operating system settings." },
  { question: "How can you access the Taskbar properties to customize its behavior?", options: ["Double click the Desktop", "Right-click an empty area of the Taskbar and select Settings/Properties", "Press Alt + F4", "Open MS Paint"], answer: "Right-click an empty area of the Taskbar and select Settings/Properties", category: "SDP", reason: "The context menu of the Taskbar provides direct access to its customization settings." },
  { question: "What does 'Lock the taskbar' do?", options: ["Turns off the computer", "Prevents the taskbar from being moved or resized", "Hides all icons", "Sets a password for the taskbar"], answer: "Prevents the taskbar from being moved or resized", category: "SDP", reason: "Locking the taskbar ensures that its position and size remain fixed on the desktop." },
  { question: "Which setting allows the Taskbar to disappear when not in use and reappear when the mouse moves to its edge?", options: ["Lock the taskbar", "Automatically hide the taskbar", "Use small taskbar buttons", "Show badges"], answer: "Automatically hide the taskbar", category: "SDP", reason: "Auto-hide is a customization feature that maximizes available screen space." },
  { question: "Where is the option to 'Clear the contents of the document menu' (recent items) usually managed for privacy?", options: ["Recycle Bin properties", "Taskbar and Start Menu properties", "Character Map", "Disk Defragmenter"], answer: "Taskbar and Start Menu properties", category: "SDP", reason: "The history of recently opened files is tracked by the Start Menu and can be cleared via its privacy settings." },
  { question: "Which Control Panel item is used to uninstall software from the computer?", options: ["Programs and Features", "System", "Personalization", "Ease of Access"], answer: "Programs and Features", category: "SDP", reason: "This applet lists all installed applications and provides the option to change or remove them." },
  { question: "Which Control Panel applet is used to configure 'Sticky Keys' or a 'Magnifier' for accessibility?", options: ["Appearance", "Ease of Access Center", "Hardware and Sound", "User Accounts"], answer: "Ease of Access Center", category: "SDP", reason: "Ease of Access provides specialized settings for users with different physical or visual requirements." },
  { question: "To change the 'Date and Time' format of your system, you should visit which category in the Control Panel?", options: ["Clock and Region", "System and Security", "Network and Internet", "Hardware and Sound"], answer: "Clock and Region", category: "SDP", reason: "This section handles time zones, calendar types, and regional formatting." },
  { question: "Which feature allows you to change the 'Desktop Wallpaper' in Windows?", options: ["System", "Personalization", "Programs", "Update & Security"], answer: "Personalization", category: "SDP", reason: "Personalization settings control visual elements like themes, backgrounds, and colors." },
  { question: "In the Windows Taskbar, what is the 'Notification Area' also known as?", options: ["Quick Launch", "System Tray", "Start Menu", "Address Bar"], answer: "System Tray", category: "SDP", reason: "The System Tray (at the far right) displays background system icons like volume and clock." },
  { question: "What is the primary concept of 'Word Processing'?", options: ["Calculating complex formulas", "Designing hardware", "The use of software to create, edit, format, and print text documents", "Connecting to a network"], answer: "The use of software to create, edit, format, and print text documents", category: "SDP", reason: "Word processing is focused on the electronic creation and manipulation of text-based documents." },
  { question: "Which of the following is a 'Text Editor' rather than a full Word Processor?", options: ["MS Word", "Notepad", "WordPerfect", "WordPad"], answer: "Notepad", category: "SDP", reason: "Notepad is a plain text editor; it lacks the advanced layout and formatting tools of a word processor." },
  { question: "Which type of Word Processor is MS Word classified as?", options: ["Text Editor", "WYSIWYG Word Processor", "Compiler", "Database Manager"], answer: "WYSIWYG Word Processor", category: "SDP", reason: "WYSIWYG (What You See Is What You Get) means the screen display matches the printed output." },
  { question: "Which keyboard shortcut key is used to open the 'Find' pane in MS Word?", options: ["Ctrl + H", "Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + G", "Ctrl + K"], answer: "Ctrl + F", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + F is the standard shortcut to search for text within a document." },
  { question: "To find a word and 'Replace' it with another throughout the entire document, which shortcut is used?", options: ["Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + R", "Ctrl + H", "Ctrl + K"], answer: "Ctrl + H", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + H opens the 'Find and Replace' dialog box." },
  { question: "In 'Find and Replace', what is the purpose of the 'Match Case' option?", options: ["To check spelling", "To find words only with exact matching capitalization", "To change the font", "To ignore punctuation"], answer: "To find words only with exact matching capitalization", category: "SDP", reason: "Match Case differentiates between 'Nepal' and 'nepal' during a search." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Layout' setting determines the vertical or horizontal orientation of the paper?", options: ["Margins", "Size", "Orientation", "Columns"], answer: "Orientation", category: "SDP", reason: "Orientation can be set to either Portrait (vertical) or Landscape (horizontal)." },
  { question: "What is 'Gutter' margin used for?", options: ["To add space for the header", "To add space to the binding side of a document", "To increase line spacing", "To create a border"], answer: "To add space to the binding side of a document", category: "SDP", reason: "Gutter margin ensures text isn't lost in the spine of a book or folder when bound." },
  { question: "Which view in MS Word shows the document exactly as it will look when printed?", options: ["Draft View", "Outline View", "Print Layout", "Web Layout"], answer: "Print Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Layout is the default editing view that displays margins, page breaks, and headers." },
  { question: "What is 'Print Preview' used for?", options: ["To delete the file", "To check the document layout and content before physical printing", "To change the font size", "To translate the text"], answer: "To check the document layout and content before physical printing", category: "SDP", reason: "Print Preview helps users verify margins and placement to save paper and ink." },
  { question: "Which toolbar allows for one-click access to common commands like Save, Undo, and Redo?", options: ["Status Bar", "Quick Access Toolbar", "Menu Bar", "Navigation Pane"], answer: "Quick Access Toolbar", category: "SDP", reason: "The Quick Access Toolbar (QAT) is a customizable toolbar that sits above or below the Ribbon." },
  { question: "How can you 'Customize' the MS Word Ribbon to add a new custom tab?", options: ["Press Ctrl + R", "Right-click the Ribbon and select 'Customize the Ribbon'", "Use the 'ATTRIB' command", "Restart the computer"], answer: "Right-click the Ribbon and select 'Customize the Ribbon'", category: "SDP", reason: "Users can personalize the Ribbon by adding, removing, or reordering tabs and groups." },
  { question: "To change the 'Default Font' for all new blank documents, where do you go?", options: ["Insert Tab", "Design Tab", "Font Dialog Box -> Set as Default", "Review Tab"], answer: "Font Dialog Box -> Set as Default", category: "SDP", reason: "Setting a font as default updates the 'Normal.dotm' template used for new files." },
  { question: "Which 'Security Technique' prevents a user from even opening a document without the correct key?", options: ["Mark as Final", "Restrict Editing", "Encrypt with Password (Password to Open)", "Read-only recommended"], answer: "Encrypt with Password (Password to Open)", category: "SDP", reason: "Encryption ensures the document data is unreadable without the specific password." },
  { question: "What is the function of 'Mark as Final' in MS Word?", options: ["Deletes the document", "Makes the document read-only and notifies readers that it is the finished version", "Automatically prints the file", "Checks for viruses"], answer: "Makes the document read-only and notifies readers that it is the finished version", category: "SDP", reason: "Mark as Final is a 'soft' security measure to discourage further editing." },
  { question: "Which 'Restrict Editing' option allows users to only fill in pre-defined fields?", options: ["No changes (Read only)", "Tracked changes", "Comments", "Filling in forms"], answer: "Filling in forms", category: "SDP", reason: "This is used for creating digital forms where only specific areas are editable." },
  { question: "Which 'Wildcard' represents any single character in a Word 'Find' operation?", options: ["*", "?", "^", "#"], answer: "?", category: "SDP", reason: "In search syntax, '?' represents one character, and '*' represents multiple characters." },
  { question: "To change the 'Page Size' from Letter to A4, you go to the ______ tab.", options: ["Home", "Insert", "Layout / Page Layout", "Review"], answer: "Layout / Page Layout", category: "SDP", reason: "The Page Layout tab handles all physical paper settings." },
  { question: "In the Control Panel, which item manages the 'Region' settings like currency symbols and date formats?", options: ["Programs", "System", "Region", "User Accounts"], answer: "Region", category: "SDP", reason: "Region settings define the local formats for data presentation." },
  { question: "Which Taskbar setting allows you to use 'smaller' icons to save space?", options: ["Lock the taskbar", "Use small taskbar buttons", "Combine taskbar buttons", "Show desktop"], answer: "Use small taskbar buttons", category: "SDP", reason: "This visual setting reduces the height of the taskbar." },
  { question: "To add a 'Digital Signature' to a Word document, you visit which menu area?", options: ["Home Tab", "Review Tab", "File -> Info -> Protect Document", "Layout Tab"], answer: "File -> Info -> Protect Document", category: "SDP", reason: "Advanced security like digital IDs and encryption are found in the Backstage view." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Layout' tool allows you to divide text into two or more vertical sections on a page?", options: ["Columns", "Indentation", "Margins", "Hyphenation"], answer: "Columns", category: "SDP", reason: "Columns create a newspaper-style layout where text flows vertically." },
  { question: "In 'Find and Replace', what does the 'Sounds Like' option do?", options: ["Plays a sound when text is found", "Finds words that are spelled similarly but pronounced differently", "Finds words that are phonetically similar (e.g., 'Smith' and 'Smyth')", "Corrects grammar"], answer: "Finds words that are phonetically similar (e.g., 'Smith' and 'Smyth')", category: "SDP", reason: "Phonetic searching helps find content when exact spelling is uncertain." },
  { question: "Which view shows the 'text only' outline of a document for easy reorganization?", options: ["Draft View", "Outline View", "Web Layout", "Read Mode"], answer: "Outline View", category: "SDP", reason: "Outline view displays document structure based on heading levels." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut key for 'Repeat' or 'Redo'?", options: ["Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + Y", "Ctrl + K", "Ctrl + Shift + R"], answer: "Ctrl + Y", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Y reverses an Undo or repeats the last formatting command." },
  { question: "Which specific 'Control Panel' item is used to configure a printer that is not working?", options: ["System", "Devices and Printers", "Programs", "Security"], answer: "Devices and Printers", category: "SDP", reason: "This applet manages all connected external hardware peripherals." },
  { question: "To 'Clear the contents of the document menu', you are essentially deleting:", options: ["The original files", "The shortcuts to recently opened files", "The entire hard drive", "The BIOS settings"], answer: "The shortcuts to recently opened files", category: "SDP", reason: "Clearing recent items only removes the history links, not the data itself." },
  { question: "Which 'Word Processing' type allows multiple users to edit the same document in real-time over the web?", options: ["Desktop Word Processors", "Web-based / Cloud Word Processors (e.g., Google Docs)", "Text Editors", "Batch Processors"], answer: "Web-based / Cloud Word Processors (e.g., Google Docs)", category: "SDP", reason: "Cloud-based tools facilitate online collaboration and automatic syncing." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Layout' option is used to set the vertical alignment of text on a page (e.g., Top, Center)?", options: ["Margins", "Columns", "Page Setup -> Layout -> Vertical alignment", "Orientation"], answer: "Page Setup -> Layout -> Vertical alignment", category: "SDP", reason: "This setting centers text between the top and bottom margins of a page." },
  { question: "To add a command like 'Macros' to the Ribbon if it is not visible, you must enable which tab?", options: ["Insert", "References", "Developer", "View"], answer: "Developer", category: "SDP", reason: "The Developer tab is hidden by default and contains tools for macros and forms." },
  { question: "Which 'Find' option would you use to search for words that start with a specific prefix?", options: ["Match prefix", "Match suffix", "Wildcards", "Whole words only"], answer: "Wildcards", category: "SDP", reason: "Using wildcards like 'pre*' allows for searching specific prefixes." },
  { question: "Where can you change the 'Taskbar Location' (Top, Bottom, Left, Right)?", options: ["Control Panel -> Display", "Taskbar Settings", "My Computer", "Recycle Bin"], answer: "Taskbar Settings", category: "SDP", reason: "Taskbar properties allow you to choose its screen orientation." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' option prevents a user from 'changing' document content but allows them to fill out a questionnaire?", options: ["Mark as Final", "Editing Restrictions -> Filling in forms", "Password to Open", "Read-only recommended"], answer: "Editing Restrictions -> Filling in forms", category: "SDP", reason: "This is the standard way to protect official templates while allowing user input." },
  { question: "What happens if you right-click the Ribbon and select 'Collapse the Ribbon'?", options: ["The document is closed", "The command icons are hidden to show only tab names", "The program is uninstalled", "The font changes"], answer: "The command icons are hidden to show only tab names", category: "SDP", reason: "Collapsing the Ribbon provides more vertical space for viewing the document." },
  { question: "Which Control Panel applet would you use to check the amount of 'installed RAM' and CPU speed?", options: ["User Accounts", "System", "Programs", "Clock"], answer: "System", category: "SDP", reason: "The System applet (or 'About' in Settings) provides basic hardware specifications." },
  { question: "In 'Page Layout', what is the purpose of 'Hyphenation'?", options: ["To check spelling", "To break words at the end of a line to create more even spacing", "To count syllables", "To add page numbers"], answer: "To break words at the end of a line to create more even spacing", category: "SDP", reason: "Hyphenation improves text flow, especially in justified or narrow columns." },
  { question: "Which shortcut opens the 'Navigation Pane' to easily search and jump to headings?", options: ["Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + G", "Ctrl + K"], answer: "Ctrl + F", category: "SDP", reason: "In modern MS Word versions, Ctrl + F triggers the Navigation pane." },
  { question: "To remove a custom toolbar button from the Quick Access Toolbar, you should:", options: ["Format the hard drive", "Right-click the icon and select 'Remove from Quick Access Toolbar'", "Restart Word", "Delete the Normal.dotm file"], answer: "Right-click the icon and select 'Remove from Quick Access Toolbar'", category: "SDP", reason: "The QAT can be modified instantly by right-clicking its icons." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' feature adds a digital stamp that proves the document has not been tampered with since it was signed?", options: ["Watermark", "Digital Signature", "Page Border", "Password"], answer: "Digital Signature", category: "SDP", reason: "Digital signatures ensure integrity and authenticity through cryptographic hashes." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Start' menu in Windows?", options: ["To provide a central portal for applications and settings", "To empty the recycle bin", "To browse the internet only", "To physical turn off the monitor"], answer: "To provide a central portal for applications and settings", category: "SDP", reason: "The Start menu is the starting point for user interaction with the OS." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item is used to change the 'Mouse click speed'?", options: ["Keyboard", "Mouse", "Display", "Sound"], answer: "Mouse", category: "SDP", reason: "Mouse settings handle sensitivity, button swapping, and double-click timing." },
  { question: "To find 'bold' text specifically and replace it with 'italic' text, you use:", options: ["Format Painter", "Find and Replace -> More -> Format", "Thesaurus", "AutoCorrect"], answer: "Find and Replace -> More -> Format", category: "SDP", reason: "Advanced Find and Replace allows searching for specific font and paragraph formatting." },
  { question: "To start a 'New Slide' in PowerPoint (syllabus cross-reference), you press:", options: ["Ctrl + N", "Ctrl + M", "Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Ctrl + M", category: "SDP", reason: "This is a standard Microsoft keyboard shortcut for presentations." },
  { question: "What is the primary goal of an 'Operating System'?", options: ["To make computer hardware more efficient and convenient to use", "To make hardware more expensive", "To restrict the user from seeing any files", "To stop all network access"], answer: "To make computer hardware more efficient and convenient to use", category: "SDP", reason: "The OS acts as the vital bridge between users and physical hardware." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item is used to set up 'Bluetooth' devices?", options: ["Programs", "Devices and Printers / Bluetooth Settings", "Clock", "Security"], answer: "Devices and Printers / Bluetooth Settings", category: "SDP", reason: "External wireless hardware is managed via the devices section." },
  { question: "In 'Page Layout', the 'Margin' setting controls:", options: ["The color of the page", "The white space around the edges of the document content", "The font size", "The number of images"], answer: "The white space around the edges of the document content", category: "SDP", reason: "Margins ensure the content is positioned correctly on the paper." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' feature allows you to restrict others from copying text from your document?", options: ["Mark as Final", "Editing Restrictions", "Password to Open", "Digital Signature"], answer: "Editing Restrictions", category: "SDP", reason: "Restricting editing allows the owner to control exactly how the file is interacted with." },
  { question: "The 'Find and Replace' dialog box can be reached by pressing:", options: ["Ctrl + F", "Ctrl + H", "Ctrl + G", "All of the above"], answer: "All of the above", category: "SDP", reason: "Find, Replace, and Go To are all different tabs within the same specialized dialog window." },
  { question: "To 'Customize' the Quick Access Toolbar, you click the:", options: ["Large arrow next to the QAT", "Right-click the Taskbar", "Control Panel", "Status Bar"], answer: "Large arrow next to the QAT", category: "SDP", reason: "A small dropdown menu at the end of the toolbar allows for quick customization." },
  { question: "Which 'Word Processor' is the most popular globally for professional office work?", options: ["Notepad", "MS Word", "WordPad", "Google Sheets"], answer: "MS Word", category: "SDP", reason: "Microsoft Word is the industry standard for document processing." },
  { question: "Where is the 'Taskbar' typically located?", options: ["At the top of the screen", "At the bottom of the screen", "On the right side", "In the center"], answer: "At the bottom of the screen", category: "SDP", reason: "The default location for the Windows taskbar is at the base of the screen." },
  { question: "What is the shortcut to 'Select All' in Windows Explorer?", options: ["Ctrl + S", "Ctrl + A", "Ctrl + L", "Ctrl + Enter"], answer: "Ctrl + A", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + A stands for Select All." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item is used to check the computer's 'Battery' status on a laptop?", options: ["User Accounts", "Power Options", "Appearance", "Network"], answer: "Power Options", category: "SDP", reason: "Power Options manage sleep, battery life, and energy performance." },
  { question: "To 'Start a program by command line operation' in Windows, which app do you use?", options: ["Paint", "Recycle Bin", "Command Prompt / Run Dialog", "Character Map"], answer: "Command Prompt / Run Dialog", category: "SDP", reason: "Text-based commands are entered in the prompt or the run box." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Layout' setting determines the 'size' of the paper (e.g. Legal, A4)?", options: ["Orientation", "Size", "Margins", "Columns"], answer: "Size", category: "SDP", reason: "Paper size settings must match the printer's capabilities." },
  { question: "In 'Page Layout', 'A4' and 'Letter' are types of:", options: ["Orientation", "Margins", "Paper Size", "Gutter"], answer: "Paper Size", category: "SDP", reason: "Paper size settings ensure the document layout matches the physical paper in the printer." },
  { question: "Which 'Windows Setting' allows you to 'pin' frequently used folders to the left side of File Explorer?", options: ["Quick Access", "Recycle Bin", "Control Panel", "Taskbar"], answer: "Quick Access", category: "SDP", reason: "Quick Access acts as a list of favorite or recent shortcuts in the file manager." },
  { question: "To prevent an unauthorized user from reading a document, you should use a 'Password to ______'.", options: ["Modify", "Open", "Delete", "Format"], answer: "Open", category: "SDP", reason: "A password to open provides the highest level of confidentiality." },
  { question: "What is the result of selecting 'Landscape' in the Orientation settings?", options: ["The page becomes taller", "The page becomes wider horizontally", "The text turns green", "The margins are deleted"], answer: "The page becomes wider horizontally", category: "SDP", reason: "Landscape orientation is used for wide tables or charts." },
  { question: "Where can you 'Manage User Accounts' and passwords in Windows?", options: ["Taskbar", "Control Panel -> User Accounts", "Recycle Bin", "MS Paint"], answer: "Control Panel -> User Accounts", category: "SDP", reason: "User security and profile management is a core Control Panel task." },
  { question: "Which key combination 'Redoes' an action in most Windows programs?", options: ["Ctrl + Z", "Ctrl + Y", "Ctrl + R", "Ctrl + P"], answer: "Ctrl + Y", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + Y is the standard Redo command." },
  { question: "In 'Print Preview', the 'Magnifier' tool is used to:", options: ["Change the font", "Zoom in on a specific part of the page for detailed inspection", "Delete text", "Add a border"], answer: "Zoom in on a specific part of the page for detailed inspection", category: "SDP", reason: "Magnification allows the user to see fine details before printing." },
  { question: "To add a 'Separator' line between columns, you look in the ______ dialog box.", options: ["Margins", "Columns", "Indents", "Borders"], answer: "Columns", category: "SDP", reason: "The Columns dialog (Layout tab) contains the 'Line between' checkbox." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item manages the screen resolution?", options: ["Display / Personalization", "Hardware", "Security", "Clock"], answer: "Display / Personalization", category: "SDP", reason: "Visual output settings are managed in the display properties." },
  { question: "A 'Template' file is different from a regular document because:", options: ["It is smaller", "It contains pre-set formatting and structure to be used as a starting point", "It cannot be saved", "It only contains images"], answer: "It contains pre-set formatting and structure to be used as a starting point", category: "SDP", reason: "Templates save time by providing a skeleton for common document types." },
  { question: "Which shortcut key combination closes the active 'Word' window?", options: ["Ctrl + C", "Ctrl + W", "Ctrl + Q", "Alt + F4"], answer: "Ctrl + W", category: "SDP", reason: "Ctrl + W (or Ctrl + F4) closes the specific document but keeps the application running." },
  { question: "To 'Customize' which items appear on the Start Menu, you visit which settings area?", options: ["Control Panel -> Personalization -> Start", "Recycle Bin Properties", "MS Paint", "Disk Defragmenter"], answer: "Control Panel -> Personalization -> Start", category: "SDP", reason: "Modern Windows versions manage Start Menu behavior under Personalization." },
  { question: "What is the primary function of the 'Find' tool?", options: ["To format text", "To locate specific occurrences of text or formatting within a document", "To delete files", "To check the time"], answer: "To locate specific occurrences of text or formatting within a document", category: "SDP", reason: "Find searches for strings to help with navigation or editing." },
  { question: "Which 'Security' technique provides a 'read-only' copy while maintaining a record of original authorship?", options: ["Digital Signature", "Mark as Final", "Hidden text", "Password"], answer: "Mark as Final", category: "SDP", reason: "Mark as Final is a way to indicate that a document is a finalized version." },
  { question: "The 'Draft View' in MS Word is unique because it:", options: ["Hides all images and layout elements to focus on text entry", "Shows how the document will look on a web browser", "Shows headers and footers", "Is for printing only"], answer: "Hides all images and layout elements to focus on text entry", category: "SDP", reason: "Draft view removes visual distractions to speed up typing and content editing." },
  { question: "To 'Clear the contents of the document menu' in older Windows (XP/7), you used the ______ tab in Taskbar properties.", options: ["Taskbar", "Start Menu", "Toolbars", "General"], answer: "Start Menu", category: "SDP", reason: "The history of recent files was traditionally managed under the Start Menu tab of the Taskbar Properties dialog." },
  { question: "Which 'Page Layout' setting defines the distance between the main text and the physical edge of the paper?", options: ["Margins", "Orientation", "Columns", "Indents"], answer: "Margins", category: "SDP", reason: "Margins define the printable area boundary on the sheet." },
  { question: "What does 'AutoCorrect' do in Word?", options: ["Checks for viruses", "Automatically fixes common typos and symbols as you type", "Deletes old files", "Formats the whole page"], answer: "Automatically fixes common typos and symbols as you type", category: "SDP", reason: "AutoCorrect is a productivity tool for fixing errors in real-time." },
  { question: "Where is the 'Vertical Scroll Bar' located in Word?", options: ["At the bottom", "On the right side of the window", "At the top", "Inside the Ribbon"], answer: "On the right side of the window", category: "SDP", reason: "The vertical scroll bar allows for movement through document pages." },
  { question: "To change the 'Measurement Units' on the ruler (Inches to cm), you visit:", options: ["Home Tab", "View Tab", "File -> Options -> Advanced -> Display", "Layout Tab"], answer: "File -> Options -> Advanced -> Display", category: "SDP", reason: "Unit measurements are a system-level configuration in Word Options." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' category manages the 'Sound' of the computer?", options: ["System", "Hardware and Sound", "Programs", "Ease of Access"], answer: "Hardware and Sound", category: "SDP", reason: "Audio and device settings are grouped under Hardware and Sound." },
  { question: "What is 'Find and Replace' most useful for?", options: ["Adding images", "Changing multiple occurrences of a word consistently across a long document", "Checking the time", "Formatting a table"], answer: "Changing multiple occurrences of a word consistently across a long document", category: "SDP", reason: "It ensures consistency and saves significant time in editing." },
  { question: "In 'Page Layout', what is 'Landscape'?", options: ["A vertical page", "A horizontal page layout", "A type of font", "A green border"], answer: "A horizontal page layout", category: "SDP", reason: "Landscape orientation is wider than it is tall." },
  { question: "Which tool would you use to 'Copy' formatting from one heading and apply it to others?", options: ["Copy/Paste", "Format Painter", "AutoCorrect", "Find/Replace"], answer: "Format Painter", category: "SDP", reason: "Format Painter replicates visual attributes effortlessly." },
  { question: "Where can you see the 'Total Number of Pages' in a document instantly?", options: ["Title Bar", "Status Bar", "Formula Bar", "Quick Access Toolbar"], answer: "Status Bar", category: "SDP", reason: "The status bar at the bottom provides document metrics." },
  { question: "What is the keyboard shortcut for 'Print Preview'?", options: ["Ctrl + P", "Ctrl + F2", "Alt + P", "Shift + P"], answer: "Ctrl + F2", category: "SDP", reason: "While Ctrl+P opens the full print menu, Ctrl+F2 is the traditional shortcut for previewing." },
  { question: "Which of the following is an example of an 'Online' Word Processor?", options: ["Microsoft Word Desktop", "Google Docs", "Notepad", "VIM"], answer: "Google Docs", category: "SDP", reason: "Google Docs is a cloud-native word processor." },
  { question: "To change the 'Ribbon' visibility to show only tabs, you:", options: ["Delete the ribbon", "Double-click an active tab", "Format the drive", "Restart Word"], answer: "Double-click an active tab", category: "SDP", reason: "Double-clicking any tab toggles between expanded and collapsed Ribbon states." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item would you use to fix a 'Network Connection' that is not working?", options: ["Network and Sharing Center", "Appearance", "Programs", "Clock"], answer: "Network and Sharing Center", category: "SDP", reason: "Network configuration and troubleshooting are handled here." },
  { question: "In 'Find and Replace', the wildcard '*' matches:", options: ["One character", "Any number of characters", "Only numbers", "Only capital letters"], answer: "Any number of characters", category: "SDP", reason: "The asterisk is the most common wildcard for varying lengths of strings." },
  { question: "What is 'Word Processing Environment'?", options: ["The room where you type", "The combination of the user interface (Ribbon, Rulers, bars) provided by the software", "A type of printer", "The internet speed"], answer: "The combination of the user interface (Ribbon, Rulers, bars) provided by the software", category: "SDP", reason: "The 'environment' is the GUI provided to the user for interacting with the document." },
  { question: "To create a 'Password to Modify', you visit which dialog box?", options: ["Font Dialog", "Save As -> Tools -> General Options", "Paragraph Dialog", "Columns Dialog"], answer: "Save As -> Tools -> General Options", category: "SDP", reason: "Settings for modifications and open passwords are found in the General Options of the Save menu." },
  { question: "Which 'Word Processing' feature allows you to insert a small comment that appears in the margin for review?", options: ["Footnote", "Endnote", "Comment", "Caption"], answer: "Comment", category: "SDP", reason: "Comments are used for collaboration and peer review." },
  { question: "Which 'Control Panel' item is used to set the 'Primary Mouse Button' for left-handed users?", options: ["System", "Ease of Access", "Mouse", "Keyboard"], answer: "Mouse", category: "SDP", reason: "The button configuration is found in Mouse properties." },
  { question: "In Word, 'Portrait' orientation is standard for:", options: ["Legal letters and reports", "Wide spreadsheets", "Panoramic photos", "Large banners"], answer: "Legal letters and reports", category: "SDP", reason: "Vertical orientation is the standard for most business documentation." },
  { question: "To find a word and change its 'Font Color' throughout a document, you use the ______ button in the Replace dialog.", options: ["Search", "Format", "Special", "options"], answer: "Format", category: "SDP", reason: "The Format button allows for searching and replacing specific styles and colors." },
  { question: "Which Windows element displays the 'System Clock'?", options: ["Start Button", "Taskbar (Notification Area)", "Title Bar", "Formula Bar"], answer: "Taskbar (Notification Area)", category: "SDP", reason: "The clock is always located in the bottom right (by default) of the taskbar." }
